60SpellDestination::SpellDestination()
61{
62 _position.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
63 _transportGUID.Clear();
64 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
65}
66
67SpellDestination::SpellDestination(float x, float y, float z, float orientation, uint32 mapId)
68{
69 _position.Relocate(x, y, z, orientation);
70 _transportGUID.Clear();
71 _position.m_mapId = mapId;
72 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
73}
74
75SpellDestination::SpellDestination(Position const& pos)
76{
77 _position.Relocate(pos);
78 _transportGUID.Clear();
79 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
80}
81
82SpellDestination::SpellDestination(WorldObject const& wObj)
83{
84 _transportGUID = wObj.GetTransGUID();
85 _transportOffset.Relocate(wObj.GetTransOffsetX(), wObj.GetTransOffsetY(), wObj.GetTransOffsetZ(), wObj.GetTransOffsetO());
86 _position.Relocate(wObj);
87}
88
89void SpellDestination::Relocate(Position const& pos)
90{
91 if (_transportGUID)
92 {
93 Position offset;
94 _position.GetPositionOffsetTo(pos, offset);
95 _transportOffset.RelocateOffset(offset);
96 }
97 _position.Relocate(pos);
98}
99
100void SpellDestination::RelocateOffset(Position const& offset)
101{
102 if (_transportGUID)
103 _transportOffset.RelocateOffset(offset);
104
105 _position.RelocateOffset(offset);
106}

108SpellCastTargets::SpellCastTargets() : m_elevation(0), m_speed(0), m_strTarget()
109{
110 m_objectTarget = NULL;
111 m_itemTarget = NULL;
112
113 m_itemTargetEntry = 0;
114
115 m_targetMask = 0;
116}
117
118SpellCastTargets::~SpellCastTargets() { }
119
120void SpellCastTargets::Read(ByteBuffer& data, Unit* caster)
121{
122 data >> m_targetMask;
123
124 if (m_targetMask == TARGET_FLAG_NONE)
125 return;
126
127 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY))
128 data >> m_objectTargetGUID.ReadAsPacked();
129
130 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM))
131 data >> m_itemTargetGUID.ReadAsPacked();
132
133 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
134 {
135 data >> m_src._transportGUID.ReadAsPacked();
136 if (m_src._transportGUID)
137 data >> m_src._transportOffset.PositionXYZStream();
138 else
139 data >> m_src._position.PositionXYZStream();
140 }
141 else
142 {
143 m_src._transportGUID = caster->GetTransGUID();
144 if (m_src._transportGUID)
145 m_src._transportOffset.Relocate(caster->GetTransOffsetX(), caster->GetTransOffsetY(), caster->GetTransOffsetZ(), caster->GetTransOffsetO());
146 else
147 m_src._position.Relocate(caster);
148 }
149
150 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
151 {
152 data >> m_dst._transportGUID.ReadAsPacked();
153 if (m_dst._transportGUID)
154 data >> m_dst._transportOffset.PositionXYZStream();
155 else
156 data >> m_dst._position.PositionXYZStream();
157 }
158 else
159 {
160 m_dst._transportGUID = caster->GetTransGUID();
161 if (m_dst._transportGUID)
162 m_dst._transportOffset.Relocate(caster->GetTransOffsetX(), caster->GetTransOffsetY(), caster->GetTransOffsetZ(), caster->GetTransOffsetO());
163 else
164 m_dst._position.Relocate(caster);
165 }
166
167 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_STRING)
168 data >> m_strTarget;
169
170 Update(caster);
171}
172
173void SpellCastTargets::Write(ByteBuffer& data)
174{
175 data << uint32(m_targetMask);
176
177 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET))
178 data << m_objectTargetGUID.WriteAsPacked();
179
180 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM))
181 {
182 if (m_itemTarget)
183 data << m_itemTarget->GetPackGUID();
184 else
185 data << uint8(0);
186 }
187
188 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
189 {
190 data << m_src._transportGUID.WriteAsPacked(); // relative position guid here - transport for example
191 if (m_src._transportGUID)
192 data << m_src._transportOffset.PositionXYZStream();
193 else
194 data << m_src._position.PositionXYZStream();
195 }
196
197 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
198 {
199 data << m_dst._transportGUID.WriteAsPacked(); // relative position guid here - transport for example
200 if (m_dst._transportGUID)
201 data << m_dst._transportOffset.PositionXYZStream();
202 else
203 data << m_dst._position.PositionXYZStream();
204 }
205
206 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_STRING)
207 data << m_strTarget;
208}
209
210ObjectGuid SpellCastTargets::GetOrigUnitTargetGUID() const
211{
212 switch (m_origObjectTargetGUID.GetHigh())
213 {
214 case HighGuid::Player:
215 case HighGuid::Vehicle:
216 case HighGuid::Unit:
217 case HighGuid::Pet:
218 return m_origObjectTargetGUID;
219 default:
220 return ObjectGuid();
221 }
222}
223
224void SpellCastTargets::SetOrigUnitTarget(Unit* target)
225{
226 if (!target)
227 return;
228
229 m_origObjectTargetGUID = target->GetGUID();
230}
231
232ObjectGuid SpellCastTargets::GetUnitTargetGUID() const
233{
234 if (m_objectTargetGUID.IsUnit())
235 return m_objectTargetGUID;
236
237 return ObjectGuid::Empty;
238}

310void SpellCastTargets::RemoveObjectTarget()
311{

315}

317void SpellCastTargets::SetItemTarget(Item* item)
318{
319 if (!item)
320 return;
321
322 m_itemTarget = item;
323 m_itemTargetGUID = item->GetGUID();
324 m_itemTargetEntry = item->GetEntry();
325 m_targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
326}

328void SpellCastTargets::SetTradeItemTarget(Player* caster)
329{
330 m_itemTargetGUID.Set(uint64(TRADE_SLOT_NONTRADED));
331 m_itemTargetEntry = 0;
332 m_targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM;
333
334 Update(caster);
335}

337void SpellCastTargets::UpdateTradeSlotItem()
338{

340 {
341 m_itemTargetGUID = m_itemTarget->GetGUID();
342 m_itemTargetEntry = m_itemTarget->GetEntry();
343 }

441
442void SpellCastTargets::Update(Unit* caster)
443{
444 m_objectTarget = m_objectTargetGUID ? ((m_objectTargetGUID == caster->GetGUID()) ? caster : ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_objectTargetGUID)) : NULL;
445
446 m_itemTarget = NULL;
447 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
448 {
449 Player* player = caster->ToPlayer();
450 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
451 m_itemTarget = player->GetItemByGuid(m_itemTargetGUID);
452 else if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
453 if (m_itemTargetGUID.GetRawValue() == TRADE_SLOT_NONTRADED) // here it is not guid but slot. Also prevents hacking slots
454 if (TradeData* pTrade = player->GetTradeData())
455 m_itemTarget = pTrade->GetTraderData()->GetItem(TRADE_SLOT_NONTRADED);
456
457 if (m_itemTarget)
458 m_itemTargetEntry = m_itemTarget->GetEntry();
459 }
460
461 // update positions by transport move
462 if (HasSrc() && m_src._transportGUID)
463 {
464 if (WorldObject* transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_src._transportGUID))
465 {
466 m_src._position.Relocate(transport);
467 m_src._position.RelocateOffset(m_src._transportOffset);
468 }
469 }
470
471 if (HasDst() && m_dst._transportGUID)
472 {
473 if (WorldObject* transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_dst._transportGUID))
474 {
475 m_dst._position.Relocate(transport);
476 m_dst._position.RelocateOffset(m_dst._transportOffset);
477 }
478 }
479}
480
481void SpellCastTargets::OutDebug() const
482{
483 if (!m_targetMask)
484 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "No targets");
485
486 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "target mask: %u", m_targetMask);
487 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK))
488 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Object target: %s", m_objectTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
489 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
490 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Item target: %s", m_itemTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
491 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
492 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Trade item target: %s", m_itemTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
493 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
494 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Source location: transport guid:%s trans offset: %s position: %s", m_src._transportGUID.ToString().c_str(), m_src._transportOffset.ToString().c_str(), m_src._position.ToString().c_str());
495 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
496 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Destination location: transport guid:%s trans offset: %s position: %s", m_dst._transportGUID.ToString().c_str(), m_dst._transportOffset.ToString().c_str(), m_dst._position.ToString().c_str());
497 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_STRING)
498 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "String: %s", m_strTarget.c_str());
499 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "speed: %f", m_speed);
500 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "elevation: %f", m_elevation);
501}
502
503SpellValue::SpellValue(SpellInfo const* proto)
504{
505 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
506 EffectBasePoints[i] = proto->Effects[i].BasePoints;
507 MaxAffectedTargets = proto->MaxAffectedTargets;
508 RadiusMod = 1.0f;
509 AuraStackAmount = 1;
510}
511
512Spell::Spell(Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* info, TriggerCastFlags triggerFlags, ObjectGuid originalCasterGUID, bool skipCheck) :
513m_spellInfo(sSpellMgr->GetSpellForDifficultyFromSpell(info, caster)),
514m_caster((info->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CAST_BY_CHARMER) && caster->GetCharmerOrOwner()) ? caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() : caster)
515, m_spellValue(new SpellValue(m_spellInfo)), m_preGeneratedPath(PathGenerator(m_caster))
516{
517 m_customError = SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_NONE;
518 m_skipCheck = skipCheck;
519 m_selfContainer = NULL;
520 m_referencedFromCurrentSpell = false;
521 m_executedCurrently = false;
522 m_needComboPoints = m_spellInfo->NeedsComboPoints();
523 m_comboPointGain = 0;
524 m_delayStart = 0;
525 m_delayAtDamageCount = 0;
526
527 m_applyMultiplierMask = 0;
528 m_auraScaleMask = 0;
529 memset(m_damageMultipliers, 0, sizeof(m_damageMultipliers));
530
531 // Get data for type of attack
532 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
533 {
534 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
535 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND))
536 m_attackType = OFF_ATTACK;
537 else
538 m_attackType = BASE_ATTACK;
539 break;
540 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
541 m_attackType = m_spellInfo->IsRangedWeaponSpell() ? RANGED_ATTACK : BASE_ATTACK;
542 break;
543 default:
544 // Wands
545 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG))
546 m_attackType = RANGED_ATTACK;
547 else
548 m_attackType = BASE_ATTACK;
549 break;
550 }
551
552 m_spellSchoolMask = info->GetSchoolMask(); // Can be override for some spell (wand shoot for example)
553
554 if (m_attackType == RANGED_ATTACK)
555 // wand case
556 if ((m_caster->getClassMask() & CLASSMASK_WAND_USERS) != 0 && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
557 if (Item* pItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(RANGED_ATTACK))
558 m_spellSchoolMask = SpellSchoolMask(1 << pItem->GetTemplate()->Damage[0].DamageType);
559
560 if (originalCasterGUID)
561 m_originalCasterGUID = originalCasterGUID;
562 else
563 m_originalCasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
564
565 if (m_originalCasterGUID == m_caster->GetGUID())
566 m_originalCaster = m_caster;
567 else
568 {
569 m_originalCaster = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCasterGUID);
570 if (m_originalCaster && !m_originalCaster->IsInWorld())
571 m_originalCaster = NULL;
572 }
573
574 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_NULL;
575 _triggeredCastFlags = triggerFlags;
576 if (info->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_CAN_CAST_WHILE_CASTING))
577 _triggeredCastFlags = TriggerCastFlags(uint32(_triggeredCastFlags) | TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS | TRIGGERED_CAST_DIRECTLY);
578
579 m_CastItem = NULL;
580 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
581 m_castItemEntry = 0;
582
583 unitTarget = NULL;
584 itemTarget = NULL;
585 gameObjTarget = NULL;
586 destTarget = NULL;
587 damage = 0;
588 effectHandleMode = SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH;
589 m_diminishLevel = DIMINISHING_LEVEL_1;
590 m_diminishGroup = DIMINISHING_NONE;
591 m_damage = 0;
592 m_healing = 0;
593 m_procAttacker = 0;
594 m_procVictim = 0;
595 m_procEx = 0;
596 focusObject = NULL;
597 m_cast_count = 0;
598 m_glyphIndex = 0;
599 m_preCastSpell = 0;
600 m_triggeredByAuraSpell = NULL;
601 m_spellAura = NULL;
602
603 //Auto Shot & Shoot (wand)
604 m_autoRepeat = m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell();
605
606 m_isDelayedInstantCast = false;
607
608 m_runesState = 0;
609 m_powerCost = 0; // setup to correct value in Spell::prepare, must not be used before.
610 m_casttime = 0; // setup to correct value in Spell::prepare, must not be used before.
611 m_timer = 0; // will set to castime in prepare
612 m_channeledDuration = 0; // will be setup in Spell::handle_immediate
613 m_immediateHandled = false;
614
615 m_channelTargetEffectMask = 0;
616
617 // Determine if spell can be reflected back to the caster
618 // Patch 1.2 notes: Spell Reflection no longer reflects abilities
619 m_canReflect = m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_ABILITY)
620 && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_BE_REFLECTED) && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY)
621 && !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive();
622
623 CleanupTargetList();
624 memset(m_effectExecuteData, 0, MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS * sizeof(ByteBuffer*));
625
626 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
627 m_destTargets[i] = SpellDestination(*m_caster);
628}
629
630Spell::~Spell()
631{
632 // unload scripts
633 while (!m_loadedScripts.empty())
634 {
635 std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin();
636 (*itr)->_Unload();
637 delete (*itr);
638 m_loadedScripts.erase(itr);
639 }
640
641 if (m_referencedFromCurrentSpell && m_selfContainer && *m_selfContainer == this)
642 {
643 // Clean the reference to avoid later crash.
644 // If this error is repeating, we may have to add an ASSERT to better track down how we get into this case.
645 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "SPELL: deleting spell for spell ID %u. However, spell still referenced.", m_spellInfo->Id);
646 *m_selfContainer = NULL;
647 }
648
649 if (m_caster && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
650 ASSERT(m_caster->ToPlayer()->m_spellModTakingSpell != this);
651
652 delete m_spellValue;
653
654 CheckEffectExecuteData();
655}
656
657void Spell::InitExplicitTargets(SpellCastTargets const& targets)
658{
659 m_targets = targets;
660 m_targets.SetOrigUnitTarget(m_targets.GetUnitTarget());
661 // this function tries to correct spell explicit targets for spell
662 // client doesn't send explicit targets correctly sometimes - we need to fix such spells serverside
663 // this also makes sure that we correctly send explicit targets to client (removes redundant data)
664 uint32 neededTargets = m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask();
665
666 if (WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
667 {
668 // check if object target is valid with needed target flags
669 // for unit case allow corpse target mask because player with not released corpse is a unit target
670 if ((target->ToUnit() && !(neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)))
671 || (target->ToGameObject() && !(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK))
672 || (target->ToCorpse() && !(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)))
673 m_targets.RemoveObjectTarget();
674 }
675 else
676 {
677 // try to select correct unit target if not provided by client or by serverside cast
678 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK))
679 {
680 Unit* unit = NULL;
681 // try to use player selection as a target
682 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
683 {
684 // selection has to be found and to be valid target for the spell
685 if (Unit* selectedUnit = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, playerCaster->GetTarget()))
686 if (m_spellInfo->CheckExplicitTarget(m_caster, selectedUnit) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
687 unit = selectedUnit;
688 }
689 // try to use attacked unit as a target
690 else if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT) && neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT))
691 unit = m_caster->GetVictim();
692
693 // didn't find anything - let's use self as target
694 if (!unit && neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY))
695 unit = m_caster;
696
697 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(unit);
698 }
699 }
700
701 // check if spell needs dst target
702 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
703 {
704 // and target isn't set
705 if (!m_targets.HasDst())
706 {
707 // try to use unit target if provided
708 if (WorldObject* target = targets.GetObjectTarget())
709 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
710 // or use self if not available
711 else
712 m_targets.SetDst(*m_caster);
713 }
714 }
715 else
716 m_targets.RemoveDst();
717
718 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
719 {
720 if (!targets.HasSrc())
721 m_targets.SetSrc(*m_caster);
722 }
723 else
724 m_targets.RemoveSrc();
725}
726
727void Spell::SelectExplicitTargets()
728{
729 // here go all explicit target changes made to explicit targets after spell prepare phase is finished
730 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
731 {
732 // check for explicit target redirection, for Grounding Totem for example
733 if (m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY
734 || (m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT && !m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(target)))
735 {
736 Unit* redirect;
737 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
738 {
739 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
740 redirect = m_caster->GetMagicHitRedirectTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
741 break;
742 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
743 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
744 redirect = m_caster->GetMeleeHitRedirectTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
745 break;
746 default:
747 redirect = NULL;
748 break;
749 }
750 if (redirect && (redirect != target))
751 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(redirect);
752 }
753 }
754}
755
756void Spell::SelectSpellTargets()
757{
758 // select targets for cast phase
759 SelectExplicitTargets();
760
761 uint32 processedAreaEffectsMask = 0;
762 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
763 {
764 // not call for empty effect.
765 // Also some spells use not used effect targets for store targets for dummy effect in triggered spells
766 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsEffect())
767 continue;
768
769 // set expected type of implicit targets to be sent to client
770 uint32 implicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetB.GetObjectType());
771 if (implicitTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT)
772 m_targets.SetTargetFlag(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT);
773 if (implicitTargetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM))
774 m_targets.SetTargetFlag(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT);
775
776 SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex(i), m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA, processedAreaEffectsMask);
777 SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex(i), m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetB, processedAreaEffectsMask);
778
779 // Select targets of effect based on effect type
780 // those are used when no valid target could be added for spell effect based on spell target type
781 // some spell effects use explicit target as a default target added to target map (like SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL)
782 // some spell effects add target to target map only when target type specified (like SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON)
783 // some spell effects don't add anything to target map (confirmed with sniffs) (like SPELL_EFFECT_DESTROY_ALL_TOTEMS)
784 SelectEffectTypeImplicitTargets(i);
785
786 if (m_targets.HasDst())
787 AddDestTarget(*m_targets.GetDst(), i);
788
789 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
790 {
791 uint8 mask = (1 << i);
792 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
793 {
794 if (ihit->effectMask & mask)
795 {
796 m_channelTargetEffectMask |= mask;
797 break;
798 }
799 }
800 }
801 else if (m_auraScaleMask)
802 {
803 bool checkLvl = !m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty();
804 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end();)
805 {
806 // remove targets which did not pass min level check
807 if (m_auraScaleMask && ihit->effectMask == m_auraScaleMask)
808 {
809 // Do not check for selfcast
810 if (!ihit->scaleAura && ihit->targetGUID != m_caster->GetGUID())
811 {
812 m_UniqueTargetInfo.erase(ihit++);
813 continue;
814 }
815 }
816 ++ihit;
817 }
818 if (checkLvl && m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty())
819 {
820 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL);
821 finish(false);
822 }
823 }
824 }
825
826 if (m_targets.HasDst())
827 {
828 if (m_targets.HasTraj())
829 {
830 float speed = m_targets.GetSpeedXY();
831 if (speed > 0.0f)
832 m_delayMoment = (uint64)floor(m_targets.GetDist2d() / speed * 1000.0f);
833 }
834 else if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f)
835 {
836 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(*m_targets.GetDstPos());
837 m_delayMoment = (uint64) std::floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f);
838 }
839 }
840}
841
842void Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32& processedEffectMask)
843{
844 if (!targetType.GetTarget())
845 return;
846
847 uint32 effectMask = 1 << effIndex;
848 // set the same target list for all effects
849 // some spells appear to need this, however this requires more research
850 switch (targetType.GetSelectionCategory())
851 {
852 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY:
853 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE:
854 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA:
855 // targets for effect already selected
856 if (effectMask & processedEffectMask)
857 return;
858 // choose which targets we can select at once
859 for (uint32 j = effIndex + 1; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
860 {
861 SpellEffectInfo const* effects = GetSpellInfo()->Effects;
862 if (effects[j].IsEffect() &&
863 effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() == effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() &&
864 effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget() == effects[j].TargetB.GetTarget() &&
865 effects[effIndex].ImplicitTargetConditions == effects[j].ImplicitTargetConditions &&
866 effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster) == effects[j].CalcRadius(m_caster) &&
867 CheckScriptEffectImplicitTargets(effIndex, j))
868 {
869 effectMask |= 1 << j;
870 }
871 }
872 processedEffectMask |= effectMask;
873 break;
874 default:
875 break;
876 }
877
878 switch (targetType.GetSelectionCategory())
879 {
880 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL:
881 SelectImplicitChannelTargets(effIndex, targetType);
882 break;
883 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY:
884 SelectImplicitNearbyTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
885 break;
886 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE:
887 SelectImplicitConeTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
888 break;
889 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA:
890 SelectImplicitAreaTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
891 break;
892 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_DEFAULT:
893 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
894 {
895 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
896 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
897 {
898 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
899 m_targets.SetSrc(*m_caster);
900 break;
901 default:
902 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT_SRC");
903 break;
904 }
905 break;
906 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
907 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
908 {
909 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
910 SelectImplicitCasterDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
911 break;
912 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
913 SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
914 break;
915 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
916 SelectImplicitDestDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
917 break;
918 default:
919 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT_DEST");
920 break;
921 }
922 break;
923 default:
924 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
925 {
926 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
927 SelectImplicitCasterObjectTargets(effIndex, targetType);
928 break;
929 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
930 SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets(effIndex, targetType);
931 break;
932 default:
933 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT");
934 break;
935 }
936 break;
937 }
938 break;
939 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NYI:
940 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: target type %u, found in spellID %u, effect %u is not implemented yet!", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex, targetType.GetTarget());
941 break;
942 default:
943 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target category");
944 break;
945 }
946}
947
948void Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
949{
950 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
951 {
952 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
953 return;
954 }
955
956 Spell* channeledSpell = m_originalCaster->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
957 if (!channeledSpell)
958 {
959 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: cannot find channel spell for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
960 return;
961 }
962 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
963 {
964 case TARGET_UNIT_CHANNEL_TARGET:
965 {
966 WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCaster->GetChannelObjectGuid());
967 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
968 // unit target may be no longer avalible - teleported out of map for example
969 if (target && target->ToUnit())
970 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex);
971 else
972 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: cannot find channel spell target for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
973 break;
974 }
975 case TARGET_DEST_CHANNEL_TARGET:
976 if (channeledSpell->m_targets.HasDst())
977 m_targets.SetDst(channeledSpell->m_targets);
978 else if (WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*m_caster, m_originalCaster->GetChannelObjectGuid()))
979 {
980 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
981 if (target)
982 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
983 }
984 else
985 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: cannot find channel spell destination for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
986 break;
987 case TARGET_DEST_CHANNEL_CASTER:
988 m_targets.SetDst(*channeledSpell->GetCaster());
989 break;
990 default:
991 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: received not implemented target type");
992 break;
993 }
994}
995
996void Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
997{
998 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
999 {
1000 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1001 return;
1002 }
1003
1004 float range = 0.0f;
1005 switch (targetType.GetCheckType())
1006 {
1007 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
1008 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(false, m_caster, this);
1009 break;
1010 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
1011 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
1012 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
1013 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
1014 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true, m_caster, this);
1015 break;
1016 case TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY:
1017 case TARGET_CHECK_DEFAULT:
1018 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(m_spellInfo->IsPositive(), m_caster, this);
1019 break;
1020 default:
1021 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented selection check type");
1022 break;
1023 }
1024
1025 ConditionContainer* condList = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].ImplicitTargetConditions;
1026
1027 // handle emergency case - try to use other provided targets if no conditions provided
1028 if (targetType.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY && (!condList || condList->empty()))
1029 {
1030 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: no conditions entry for target with TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY of spell ID %u, effect %u - selecting default targets", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1031 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
1032 {
1033 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1034 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
1035 {
1036 if (focusObject)
1037 AddGOTarget(focusObject, effMask);
1038 return;
1039 }
1040 break;
1041 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
1042 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
1043 {
1044 if (focusObject)
1045 m_targets.SetDst(*focusObject);
1046 return;
1047 }
1048 break;
1049 default:
1050 break;
1051 }
1052 }
1053
1054 WorldObject* target = SearchNearbyTarget(range, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType(), condList);
1055 if (!target)
1056 {
1057 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: cannot find nearby target for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1058 return;
1059 }
1060
1061 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1062 if (!target)
1063 {
1064 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set NULL target, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1065 return;
1066 }
1067
1068 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
1069 {
1070 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
1071 {
1072 if (Unit* unit = target->ToUnit())
1073 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, true, false);
1074 else
1075 {
1076 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set object of wrong type, expected unit, got %s, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, target->GetGUID().GetTypeName(), effMask);
1077 return;
1078 }
1079 break;
1080 }
1081 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1082 if (GameObject* gobjTarget = target->ToGameObject())
1083 AddGOTarget(gobjTarget, effMask);
1084 else
1085 {
1086 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set object of wrong type, expected gameobject, got %s, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, target->GetGUID().GetTypeName(), effMask);
1087 return;
1088 }
1089 break;
1090 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
1091 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
1092 break;
1093 default:
1094 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented target object type");
1095 break;
1096 }
1097
1098 SelectImplicitChainTargets(effIndex, targetType, target, effMask);
1099}
1100
1101void Spell::SelectImplicitConeTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
1102{
1103 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
1104 {
1105 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitConeTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1106 return;
1107 }
1108 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1109 SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType = targetType.GetObjectType();
1110 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType = targetType.GetCheckType();
1111 ConditionContainer* condList = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].ImplicitTargetConditions;
1112 float coneAngle = float(M_PI) / 2;
1113 float radius = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster) * m_spellValue->RadiusMod;
1114
1115 if (uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList))
1116 {
1117 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck check(coneAngle, radius, m_caster, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1118 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, containerTypeMask);
1119 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck> >(searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, m_caster, radius);
1120
1121 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1122
1123 if (!targets.empty())
1124 {
1125 // Other special target selection goes here
1126 if (uint32 maxTargets = m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets)
1127 {
1128 Unit::AuraEffectList const& Auras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_MAX_AFFECTED_TARGETS);
1129 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator j = Auras.begin(); j != Auras.end(); ++j)
1130 if ((*j)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
1131 maxTargets += (*j)->GetAmount();
1132
1133 Trinity::Containers::RandomResizeList(targets, maxTargets);
1134 }
1135
1136 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1137 {
1138 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1139 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false);
1140 else if (GameObject* gObjTarget = (*itr)->ToGameObject())
1141 AddGOTarget(gObjTarget, effMask);
1142 }
1143 }
1144 }
1145}
1146
1147void Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
1148{
1149 Unit* referer = NULL;
1150 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
1151 {
1152 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
1153 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
1154 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
1155 referer = m_caster;
1156 break;
1157 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
1158 referer = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
1159 break;
1160 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_LAST:
1161 {
1162 // find last added target for this effect
1163 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::reverse_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.rbegin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.rend(); ++ihit)
1164 {
1165 if (ihit->effectMask & (1<<effIndex))
1166 {
1167 referer = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
1168 break;
1169 }
1170 }
1171 break;
1172 }
1173 default:
1174 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1175 return;
1176 }
1177 if (!referer)
1178 return;
1179
1180 Position const* center = NULL;
1181 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
1182 {
1183 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
1184 center = m_targets.GetSrcPos();
1185 break;
1186 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
1187 center = m_targets.GetDstPos();
1188 break;
1189 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
1190 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
1191 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_LAST:
1192 center = referer;
1193 break;
1194 default:
1195 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1196 return;
1197 }
1198 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1199 float radius = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster) * m_spellValue->RadiusMod;
1200 SearchAreaTargets(targets, radius, center, referer, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType(), m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].ImplicitTargetConditions);
1201
1202 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1203
1204 if (!targets.empty())
1205 {
1206 // Other special target selection goes here
1207 if (uint32 maxTargets = m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets)
1208 {
1209 Unit::AuraEffectList const& Auras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_MAX_AFFECTED_TARGETS);
1210 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator j = Auras.begin(); j != Auras.end(); ++j)
1211 if ((*j)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
1212 maxTargets += (*j)->GetAmount();
1213
1214 Trinity::Containers::RandomResizeList(targets, maxTargets);
1215 }
1216
1217 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1218 {
1219 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1220 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false, true, center);
1221 else if (GameObject* gObjTarget = (*itr)->ToGameObject())
1222 AddGOTarget(gObjTarget, effMask);
1223 }
1224 }
1225}
1226
1227void Spell::SelectImplicitCasterDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1228{
1229 SpellDestination dest(*m_caster);
1230
1231 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1232 {
1233 case TARGET_DEST_CASTER:
1234 break;
1235 case TARGET_DEST_HOME:
1236 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
1237 dest = SpellDestination(playerCaster->m_homebindX, playerCaster->m_homebindY, playerCaster->m_homebindZ, playerCaster->GetOrientation(), playerCaster->m_homebindMapId);
1238 break;
1239 case TARGET_DEST_DB:
1240 if (SpellTargetPosition const* st = sSpellMgr->GetSpellTargetPosition(m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex))
1241 {
1242 /// @todo fix this check
1243 if (m_spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_TELEPORT_UNITS) || m_spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_BIND))
1244 dest = SpellDestination(st->target_X, st->target_Y, st->target_Z, st->target_Orientation, (int32)st->target_mapId);
1245 else if (st->target_mapId == m_caster->GetMapId())
1246 dest = SpellDestination(st->target_X, st->target_Y, st->target_Z, st->target_Orientation);
1247 }
1248 else
1249 {
1250 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: unknown target coordinates for spell ID %u", m_spellInfo->Id);
1251 if (WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
1252 dest = SpellDestination(*target);
1253 }
1254 break;
1255 case TARGET_DEST_CASTER_FISHING:
1256 {
1257 float minDist = m_spellInfo->GetMinRange(true);
1258 float maxDist = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true);
1259 float dist = frand(minDist, maxDist);
1260 float x, y, z;
1261 float angle = float(rand_norm()) * static_cast<float>(M_PI * 35.0f / 180.0f) - static_cast<float>(M_PI * 17.5f / 180.0f);
1262 m_caster->GetClosePoint(x, y, z, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE, dist, angle);
1263
1264 float ground = m_caster->GetMap()->GetHeight(m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), x, y, z, true, 50.0f);
1265 float liquidLevel = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
1266 LiquidData liquidData;
1267 if (m_caster->GetMap()->getLiquidStatus(x, y, z, MAP_ALL_LIQUIDS, &liquidData))
1268 liquidLevel = liquidData.level;
1269
1270 if (liquidLevel <= ground) // When there is no liquid Map::GetWaterOrGroundLevel returns ground level
1271 {
1272 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_NOT_HERE);
1273 SendChannelUpdate(0);
1274 finish(false);
1275 return;
1276 }
1277
1278 if (ground + 0.75 > liquidLevel)
1279 {
1280 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_TOO_SHALLOW);
1281 SendChannelUpdate(0);
1282 finish(false);
1283 return;
1284 }
1285
1286 dest = SpellDestination(x, y, liquidLevel, m_caster->GetOrientation());
1287 break;
1288 }
1289 default:
1290 {
1291 float dist;
1292 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1293 float objSize = m_caster->GetObjectSize();
1294 if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_CASTER_SUMMON)
1295 dist = PET_FOLLOW_DIST;
1296 else
1297 dist = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster);
1298
1299 if (dist < objSize)
1300 dist = objSize;
1301 else if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_CASTER_RANDOM)
1302 dist = objSize + (dist - objSize) * float(rand_norm());
1303
1304 Position pos = dest._position;
1305 m_caster->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1306
1307 dest.Relocate(pos);
1308 break;
1309 }
1310 }
1311
1312 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1313 m_targets.SetDst(dest);
1314}
1315
1316void Spell::SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1317{
1318 ASSERT(m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && "Spell::SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets - no explicit object target available!");
1319 WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget();
1320
1321 SpellDestination dest(*target);
1322
1323 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1324 {
1325 case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY:
1326 case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ANY:
1327 break;
1328 default:
1329 {
1330 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1331 float objSize = target->GetObjectSize();
1332 float dist = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster);
1333 if (dist < objSize)
1334 dist = objSize;
1335 else if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_RANDOM)
1336 dist = objSize + (dist - objSize) * float(rand_norm());
1337
1338 Position pos = dest._position;
1339 target->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1340
1341 dest.Relocate(pos);
1342 break;
1343 }
1344 }
1345
1346 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1347 m_targets.SetDst(dest);
1348}
1349
1350void Spell::SelectImplicitDestDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1351{
1352 // set destination to caster if no dest provided
1353 // can only happen if previous destination target could not be set for some reason
1354 // (not found nearby target, or channel target for example
1355 // maybe we should abort the spell in such case?
1356 CheckDst();
1357
1358 SpellDestination dest(*m_targets.GetDst());
1359
1360 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1361 {
1362 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY:
1363 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ALLY:
1364 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_NONE:
1365 case TARGET_DEST_DEST:
1366 return;
1367 case TARGET_DEST_TRAJ:
1368 SelectImplicitTrajTargets(effIndex);
1369 return;
1370 default:
1371 {
1372 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1373 float dist = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(m_caster);
1374 if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DEST_RANDOM)
1375 dist *= float(rand_norm());
1376
1377 Position pos = dest._position;
1378 m_caster->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1379
1380 dest.Relocate(pos);
1381 break;
1382 }
1383 }
1384
1385 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1386 m_targets.ModDst(dest);
1387}
1388
1389void Spell::SelectImplicitCasterObjectTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1390{
1391 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1392 bool checkIfValid = true;
1393
1394 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1395 {
1396 case TARGET_UNIT_CASTER:
1397 target = m_caster;
1398 checkIfValid = false;
1399 break;
1400 case TARGET_UNIT_MASTER:
1401 target = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner();
1402 break;
1403 case TARGET_UNIT_PET:
1404 target = m_caster->GetGuardianPet();
1405 break;
1406 case TARGET_UNIT_SUMMONER:
1407 if (m_caster->IsSummon())
1408 target = m_caster->ToTempSummon()->GetSummoner();
1409 break;
1410 case TARGET_UNIT_VEHICLE:
1411 target = m_caster->GetVehicleBase();
1412 break;
1413 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_0:
1414 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_1:
1415 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_2:
1416 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_3:
1417 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_4:
1418 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_5:
1419 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_6:
1420 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_7:
1421 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsVehicle())
1422 target = m_caster->GetVehicleKit()->GetPassenger(targetType.GetTarget() - TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_0);
1423 break;
1424 default:
1425 break;
1426 }
1427
1428 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1429
1430 if (target && target->ToUnit())
1431 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, checkIfValid);
1432}
1433
1434void Spell::SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1435{
1436 ASSERT((m_targets.GetObjectTarget() || m_targets.GetItemTarget()) && "Spell::SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets - no explicit object or item target available!");
1437
1438 WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget();
1439
1440 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1441
1442 if (target)
1443 {
1444 if (Unit* unit = target->ToUnit())
1445 AddUnitTarget(unit, 1 << effIndex, true, false);
1446 else if (GameObject* gobj = target->ToGameObject())
1447 AddGOTarget(gobj, 1 << effIndex);
1448
1449 SelectImplicitChainTargets(effIndex, targetType, target, 1 << effIndex);
1450 }
1451 // Script hook can remove object target and we would wrongly land here
1452 else if (Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
1453 AddItemTarget(item, 1 << effIndex);
1454}
1455
1456void Spell::SelectImplicitChainTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, WorldObject* target, uint32 effMask)
1457{
1458 uint32 maxTargets = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].ChainTarget;
1459 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1460 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_JUMP_TARGETS, maxTargets, this);
1461
1462 if (maxTargets > 1)
1463 {
1464 // mark damage multipliers as used
1465 for (uint32 k = effIndex; k < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++k)
1466 if (effMask & (1 << k))
1467 m_damageMultipliers[k] = 1.0f;
1468 m_applyMultiplierMask |= effMask;
1469
1470 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1471 SearchChainTargets(targets, maxTargets - 1, target, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType()
1472 , m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].ImplicitTargetConditions, targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_CHAINHEAL_ALLY);
1473
1474 // Chain primary target is added earlier
1475 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1476
1477 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1478 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1479 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false);
1480 }
1481}
1482
1483float tangent(float x)
1484{
1485 x = std::tan(x);
1486 //if (x < std::numeric_limits<float>::max() && x > -std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return x;
1487 //if (x >= std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
1488 //if (x <= -std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return -std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
1489 if (x < 100000.0f && x > -100000.0f) return x;
1490 if (x >= 100000.0f) return 100000.0f;
1491 if (x <= 100000.0f) return -100000.0f;
1492 return 0.0f;
1493}
1494
1495#define DEBUG_TRAJ(a) //a
1496
1497void Spell::SelectImplicitTrajTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
1498{
1499 if (!m_targets.HasTraj())
1500 return;
1501
1502 float dist2d = m_targets.GetDist2d();
1503 if (!dist2d)
1504 return;
1505
1506 float srcToDestDelta = m_targets.GetDstPos()->m_positionZ - m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ;
1507
1508 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1509 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck check(dist2d, m_targets.GetSrcPos(), m_caster, m_spellInfo);
1510 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL);
1511 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck> > (searcher, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL, m_caster, m_targets.GetSrcPos(), dist2d);
1512 if (targets.empty())
1513 return;
1514
1515 targets.sort(Trinity::ObjectDistanceOrderPred(m_caster));
1516
1517 float b = tangent(m_targets.GetElevation());
1518 float a = (srcToDestDelta - dist2d * b) / (dist2d * dist2d);
1519 if (a > -0.0001f)
1520 a = 0;
1521 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: a %f b %f", a, b);)
1522
1523 float bestDist = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(false);
1524
1525 std::list<WorldObject*>::const_iterator itr = targets.begin();
1526 for (; itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1527 {
1528 if (!m_caster->HasInLine(*itr, 5.0f))
1529 continue;
1530
1531 if (m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, *itr, true) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
1532 continue;
1533
1534 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1535 {
1536 if (m_caster == *itr || m_caster->IsOnVehicle(unit) || unit->GetVehicle())
1537 continue;
1538
1539 if (Creature* creatureTarget = unit->ToCreature())
1540 {
1541 if (!(creatureTarget->GetCreatureTemplate()->type_flags & CREATURE_TYPEFLAGS_PROJECTILE_COLLISION))
1542 continue;
1543 }
1544 }
1545
1546 const float size = std::max((*itr)->GetObjectSize() * 0.7f, 1.0f); // 1/sqrt(3)
1547 /// @todo all calculation should be based on src instead of m_caster
1548 const float objDist2d = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetExactDist2d(*itr) * std::cos(m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetRelativeAngle(*itr));
1549 const float dz = (*itr)->GetPositionZ() - m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ;
1550
1551 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: check %u, dist between %f %f, height between %f %f.", (*itr)->GetEntry(), objDist2d - size, objDist2d + size, dz - size, dz + size);)
1552
1553 float dist = objDist2d - size;
1554 float height = dist * (a * dist + b);
1555 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: dist %f, height %f.", dist, height);)
1556 if (dist < bestDist && height < dz + size && height > dz - size)
1557 {
1558 bestDist = dist > 0 ? dist : 0;
1559 break;
1560 }
1561
1562#define CHECK_DIST {\
1563 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: dist %f, height %f.", dist, height);)\
1564 if (dist > bestDist)\
1565 continue;\
1566 if (dist < objDist2d + size && dist > objDist2d - size)\
1567 {\
1568 bestDist = dist;\
1569 break;\
1570 }\
1571 }
1572
1573 if (!a)
1574 {
1575 height = dz - size;
1576 dist = height / b;
1577 CHECK_DIST;
1578
1579 height = dz + size;
1580 dist = height / b;
1581 CHECK_DIST;
1582
1583 continue;
1584 }
1585
1586 height = dz - size;
1587 float sqrt1 = b * b + 4 * a * height;
1588 if (sqrt1 > 0)
1589 {
1590 sqrt1 = std::sqrt(sqrt1);
1591 dist = (sqrt1 - b) / (2 * a);
1592 CHECK_DIST;
1593 }
1594
1595 height = dz + size;
1596 float sqrt2 = b * b + 4 * a * height;
1597 if (sqrt2 > 0)
1598 {
1599 sqrt2 = std::sqrt(sqrt2);
1600 dist = (sqrt2 - b) / (2 * a);
1601 CHECK_DIST;
1602
1603 dist = (-sqrt2 - b) / (2 * a);
1604 CHECK_DIST;
1605 }
1606
1607 if (sqrt1 > 0)
1608 {
1609 dist = (-sqrt1 - b) / (2 * a);
1610 CHECK_DIST;
1611 }
1612 }
1613
1614 if (m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetExactDist2d(m_targets.GetDstPos()) > bestDist)
1615 {
1616 float x = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionX + std::cos(m_caster->GetOrientation()) * bestDist;
1617 float y = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionY + std::sin(m_caster->GetOrientation()) * bestDist;
1618 float z = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ + bestDist * (a * bestDist + b);
1619
1620 if (itr != targets.end())
1621 {
1622 float distSq = (*itr)->GetExactDistSq(x, y, z);
1623 float sizeSq = (*itr)->GetObjectSize();
1624 sizeSq *= sizeSq;
1625 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Initial %f %f %f %f %f", x, y, z, distSq, sizeSq);)
1626 if (distSq > sizeSq)
1627 {
1628 float factor = 1 - std::sqrt(sizeSq / distSq);
1629 x += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionX() - x);
1630 y += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionY() - y);
1631 z += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionZ() - z);
1632
1633 distSq = (*itr)->GetExactDistSq(x, y, z);
1634 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Initial %f %f %f %f %f", x, y, z, distSq, sizeSq);)
1635 }
1636 }
1637
1638 Position trajDst;
1639 trajDst.Relocate(x, y, z, m_caster->GetOrientation());
1640 SpellDestination dest(*m_targets.GetDst());
1641 dest.Relocate(trajDst);
1642
1643 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo(TARGET_DEST_TRAJ));
1644 m_targets.ModDst(dest);
1645 }
1646}
1647
1648void Spell::SelectEffectTypeImplicitTargets(uint8 effIndex)
1649{
1650 // special case for SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND and SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER
1651 /// @todo this is a workaround - target shouldn't be stored in target map for those spells
1652 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].Effect)
1653 {
1654 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND:
1655 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER:
1656 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->GetTarget())
1657 {
1658 WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(m_caster->GetTarget());
1659
1660 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, SpellEffIndex(effIndex), SpellImplicitTargetInfo());
1661
1662 if (target && target->ToPlayer())
1663 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, false);
1664 }
1665 return;
1666 default:
1667 break;
1668 }
1669
1670 // select spell implicit targets based on effect type
1671 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].GetImplicitTargetType())
1672 return;
1673
1674 uint32 targetMask = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].GetMissingTargetMask();
1675
1676 if (!targetMask)
1677 return;
1678
1679 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1680
1681 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].GetImplicitTargetType())
1682 {
1683 // add explicit object target or self to the target map
1684 case EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT:
1685 // player which not released his spirit is Unit, but target flag for it is TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK
1686 if (targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
1687 {
1688 if (Unit* unit = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
1689 target = unit;
1690 else if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
1691 {
1692 if (Corpse* corpseTarget = m_targets.GetCorpseTarget())
1693 {
1694 /// @todo this is a workaround - corpses should be added to spell target map too, but we can't do that so we add owner instead
1695 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1696 target = owner;
1697 }
1698 }
1699 else //if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1700 target = m_caster;
1701 }
1702 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM_MASK)
1703 {
1704 if (Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
1705 AddItemTarget(item, 1 << effIndex);
1706 return;
1707 }
1708 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK)
1709 target = m_targets.GetGOTarget();
1710 break;
1711 // add self to the target map
1712 case EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_CASTER:
1713 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1714 target = m_caster;
1715 break;
1716 default:
1717 break;
1718 }
1719
1720 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, SpellEffIndex(effIndex), SpellImplicitTargetInfo());
1721
1722 if (target)
1723 {
1724 if (target->ToUnit())
1725 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, false);
1726 else if (target->ToGameObject())
1727 AddGOTarget(target->ToGameObject(), 1 << effIndex);
1728 }
1729}
1730
1731uint32 Spell::GetSearcherTypeMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1732{
1733 // this function selects which containers need to be searched for spell target
1734 uint32 retMask = GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL;
1735
1736 // filter searchers based on searched object type
1737 switch (objType)
1738 {
1739 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
1740 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
1741 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
1742 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
1743 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
1744 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE;
1745 break;
1746 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1747 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
1748 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT;
1749 break;
1750 default:
1751 break;
1752 }
1753 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_DEAD))
1754 retMask &= ~GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE;
1755 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_PLAYERS))
1756 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER;
1757 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS))
1758 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER;
1759
1760 if (condList)
1761 retMask &= sConditionMgr->GetSearcherTypeMaskForConditionList(*condList);
1762 return retMask;
1763}
1764
1765template<class SEARCHER>
1766void Spell::SearchTargets(SEARCHER& searcher, uint32 containerMask, Unit* referer, Position const* pos, float radius)
1767{
1768 if (!containerMask)
1769 return;
1770
1771 // search world and grid for possible targets
1772 bool searchInGrid = (containerMask & (GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT)) != 0;
1773 bool searchInWorld = (containerMask & (GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE)) != 0;
1774 if (searchInGrid || searchInWorld)
1775 {
1776 float x, y;
1777 x = pos->GetPositionX();
1778 y = pos->GetPositionY();
1779
1780 CellCoord p(Trinity::ComputeCellCoord(x, y));
1781 Cell cell(p);
1782 cell.SetNoCreate();
1783
1784 Map& map = *(referer->GetMap());
1785
1786 if (searchInWorld)
1787 {
1788 TypeContainerVisitor<SEARCHER, WorldTypeMapContainer> world_object_notifier(searcher);
1789 cell.Visit(p, world_object_notifier, map, radius, x, y);
1790 }
1791 if (searchInGrid)
1792 {
1793 TypeContainerVisitor<SEARCHER, GridTypeMapContainer > grid_object_notifier(searcher);
1794 cell.Visit(p, grid_object_notifier, map, radius, x, y);
1795 }
1796 }
1797}
1798
1799WorldObject* Spell::SearchNearbyTarget(float range, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1800{
1801 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1802 uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList);
1803 if (!containerTypeMask)
1804 return NULL;
1805 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck check(range, m_caster, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1806 Trinity::WorldObjectLastSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, target, check, containerTypeMask);
1807 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectLastSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck> > (searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, m_caster, range);
1808 return target;
1809}
1810
1811void Spell::SearchAreaTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, float range, Position const* position, Unit* referer, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1812{
1813 uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList);
1814 if (!containerTypeMask)
1815 return;
1816 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck check(range, position, m_caster, referer, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1817 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, containerTypeMask);
1818 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck> > (searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, position, range);
1819}
1820
1821void Spell::SearchChainTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, uint32 chainTargets, WorldObject* target, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectType, ConditionContainer* condList, bool isChainHeal)
1822{
1823 // max dist for jump target selection
1824 float jumpRadius = 0.0f;
1825 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
1826 {
1827 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
1828 // 7.5y for multi shot
1829 jumpRadius = 7.5f;
1830 break;
1831 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
1832 // 5y for swipe, cleave and similar
1833 jumpRadius = 5.0f;
1834 break;
1835 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE:
1836 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
1837 // 12.5y for chain heal spell since 3.2 patch
1838 if (isChainHeal)
1839 jumpRadius = 12.5f;
1840 // 10y as default for magic chain spells
1841 else
1842 jumpRadius = 10.0f;
1843 break;
1844 }
1845
1846 // chain lightning/heal spells and similar - allow to jump at larger distance and go out of los
1847 bool isBouncingFar = (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_AREA_TARGET_CHAIN)
1848 || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE
1849 || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC);
1850
1851 // max dist which spell can reach
1852 float searchRadius = jumpRadius;
1853 if (isBouncingFar)
1854 searchRadius *= chainTargets;
1855
1856 std::list<WorldObject*> tempTargets;
1857 SearchAreaTargets(tempTargets, searchRadius, target, m_caster, objectType, selectType, condList);
1858 tempTargets.remove(target);
1859
1860 // remove targets which are always invalid for chain spells
1861 // for some spells allow only chain targets in front of caster (swipe for example)
1862 if (!isBouncingFar)
1863 {
1864 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end();)
1865 {
1866 std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator checkItr = itr++;
1867 if (!m_caster->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), *checkItr))
1868 tempTargets.erase(checkItr);
1869 }
1870 }
1871
1872 while (chainTargets)
1873 {
1874 // try to get unit for next chain jump
1875 std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator foundItr = tempTargets.end();
1876 // get unit with highest hp deficit in dist
1877 if (isChainHeal)
1878 {
1879 uint32 maxHPDeficit = 0;
1880 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end(); ++itr)
1881 {
1882 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1883 {
1884 uint32 deficit = unit->GetMaxHealth() - unit->GetHealth();
1885 if ((deficit > maxHPDeficit || foundItr == tempTargets.end()) && target->IsWithinDist(unit, jumpRadius) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(unit))
1886 {
1887 foundItr = itr;
1888 maxHPDeficit = deficit;
1889 }
1890 }
1891 }
1892 }
1893 // get closest object
1894 else
1895 {
1896 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end(); ++itr)
1897 {
1898 if (foundItr == tempTargets.end())
1899 {
1900 if ((!isBouncingFar || target->IsWithinDist(*itr, jumpRadius)) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(*itr))
1901 foundItr = itr;
1902 }
1903 else if (target->GetDistanceOrder(*itr, *foundItr) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(*itr))
1904 foundItr = itr;
1905 }
1906 }
1907 // not found any valid target - chain ends
1908 if (foundItr == tempTargets.end())
1909 break;
1910 target = *foundItr;
1911 tempTargets.erase(foundItr);
1912 targets.push_back(target);
1913 --chainTargets;
1914 }
1915}
1916
1917GameObject* Spell::SearchSpellFocus()
1918{
1919 GameObject* focus = NULL;
1920 Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck check(m_caster, m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus);
1921 Trinity::GameObjectSearcher<Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck> searcher(m_caster, focus, check);
1922 SearchTargets<Trinity::GameObjectSearcher<Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck> > (searcher, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT, m_caster, m_caster, m_caster->GetVisibilityRange());
1923 return focus;
1924}
1925
1926void Spell::prepareDataForTriggerSystem(AuraEffect const* /*triggeredByAura*/)
1927{
1928 //==========================================================================================
1929 // Now fill data for trigger system, need know:
1930 // can spell trigger another or not (m_canTrigger)
1931 // Create base triggers flags for Attacker and Victim (m_procAttacker, m_procVictim and m_procEx)
1932 //==========================================================================================
1933
1934 m_procVictim = m_procAttacker = 0;
1935 // Get data for type of attack and fill base info for trigger
1936 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
1937 {
1938 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
1939 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MELEE_DMG_CLASS;
1940 if (m_attackType == OFF_ATTACK)
1941 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_OFFHAND_ATTACK;
1942 else
1943 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_MAINHAND_ATTACK;
1944 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MELEE_DMG_CLASS;
1945 break;
1946 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
1947 // Auto attack
1948 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG))
1949 {
1950 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1951 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1952 }
1953 else // Ranged spell attack
1954 {
1955 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_RANGED_DMG_CLASS;
1956 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_RANGED_DMG_CLASS;
1957 }
1958 break;
1959 default:
1960 if (m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON &&
1961 m_spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask & (1<<ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_WAND)
1962 && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG)) // Wands auto attack
1963 {
1964 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1965 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1966 }
1967 // For other spells trigger procflags are set in Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget
1968 // Because spell positivity is dependant on target
1969 }
1970 m_procEx = PROC_EX_NONE;
1971
1972 // Hunter trap spells - activation proc for Lock and Load, Entrapment and Misdirection
1973 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER &&
1974 (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x18 || // Freezing and Frost Trap, Freezing Arrow
1975 m_spellInfo->Id == 57879 || // Snake Trap - done this way to avoid double proc
1976 m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00024000)) // Explosive and Immolation Trap
1977
1978 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_TRAP_ACTIVATION;
1979
1980 /* Effects which are result of aura proc from triggered spell cannot proc
1981 to prevent chain proc of these spells */
1982
1983 // Hellfire Effect - trigger as DOT
1984 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000040)
1985 {
1986 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
1987 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
1988 }
1989
1990 // Ranged autorepeat attack is set as triggered spell - ignore it
1991 if (!(m_procAttacker & PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK))
1992 {
1993 if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DISALLOW_PROC_EVENTS &&
1994 (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_TRIGGERED_CAN_TRIGGER_PROC) ||
1995 m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_TRIGGERED_CAN_TRIGGER_PROC_2)))
1996 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_CANT_PROC;
1997 else if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DISALLOW_PROC_EVENTS)
1998 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_TRIGGERED;
1999 }
2000 // Totem casts require spellfamilymask defined in spell_proc_event to proc
2001 if (m_originalCaster && m_caster != m_originalCaster && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsTotem() && m_caster->IsControlledByPlayer())
2002 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_REQ_FAMILY;
2003}
2004
2005void Spell::CleanupTargetList()
2006{
2007 m_UniqueTargetInfo.clear();
2008 m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.clear();
2009 m_UniqueItemInfo.clear();
2010 m_delayMoment = 0;
2011}
2012
2013void Spell::AddUnitTarget(Unit* target, uint32 effectMask, bool checkIfValid /*= true*/, bool implicit /*= true*/, Position const* losPosition /*= nullptr*/)
2014{
2015 for (uint32 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2016 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].IsEffect() || !CheckEffectTarget(target, effIndex, losPosition))
2017 effectMask &= ~(1 << effIndex);
2018
2019 // no effects left
2020 if (!effectMask)
2021 return;
2022
2023 if (checkIfValid)
2024 if (m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, target, implicit) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
2025 return;
2026
2027 // Check for effect immune skip if immuned
2028 for (uint32 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2029 if (target->IsImmunedToSpellEffect(m_spellInfo, effIndex))
2030 effectMask &= ~(1 << effIndex);
2031
2032 ObjectGuid targetGUID = target->GetGUID();
2033
2034 // Lookup target in already in list
2035 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2036 {
2037 if (targetGUID == ihit->targetGUID) // Found in list
2038 {
2039 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Immune effects removed from mask
2040 ihit->scaleAura = false;
2041 if (m_auraScaleMask && ihit->effectMask == m_auraScaleMask && m_caster != target)
2042 {
2043 SpellInfo const* auraSpell = m_spellInfo->GetFirstRankSpell();
2044 if (uint32(target->getLevel() + 10) >= auraSpell->SpellLevel)
2045 ihit->scaleAura = true;
2046 }
2047 return;
2048 }
2049 }
2050
2051 // This is new target calculate data for him
2052
2053 // Get spell hit result on target
2054 TargetInfo targetInfo;
2055 targetInfo.targetGUID = targetGUID; // Store target GUID
2056 targetInfo.effectMask = effectMask; // Store all effects not immune
2057 targetInfo.processed = false; // Effects not apply on target
2058 targetInfo.alive = target->IsAlive();
2059 targetInfo.damage = 0;
2060 targetInfo.crit = false;
2061 targetInfo.scaleAura = false;
2062 if (m_auraScaleMask && targetInfo.effectMask == m_auraScaleMask && m_caster != target)
2063 {
2064 SpellInfo const* auraSpell = m_spellInfo->GetFirstRankSpell();
2065 if (uint32(target->getLevel() + 10) >= auraSpell->SpellLevel)
2066 targetInfo.scaleAura = true;
2067 }
2068
2069 // Calculate hit result
2070 if (m_originalCaster)
2071 {
2072 targetInfo.missCondition = m_originalCaster->SpellHitResult(target, m_spellInfo, m_canReflect);
2073 if (m_skipCheck && targetInfo.missCondition != SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE)
2074 targetInfo.missCondition = SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2075 }
2076 else
2077 targetInfo.missCondition = SPELL_MISS_EVADE; //SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2078
2079 // Spell have speed - need calculate incoming time
2080 // Incoming time is zero for self casts. At least I think so.
2081 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && m_caster != target)
2082 {
2083 // calculate spell incoming interval
2084 /// @todo this is a hack
2085 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ());
2086
2087 if (dist < 5.0f)
2088 dist = 5.0f;
2089 targetInfo.timeDelay = (uint64)std::floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f);
2090
2091 // Calculate minimum incoming time
2092 if (m_delayMoment == 0 || m_delayMoment > targetInfo.timeDelay)
2093 m_delayMoment = targetInfo.timeDelay;
2094 }
2095 else
2096 targetInfo.timeDelay = 0LL;
2097
2098 // If target reflect spell back to caster
2099 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2100 {
2101 // Calculate reflected spell result on caster
2102 targetInfo.reflectResult = m_caster->SpellHitResult(m_caster, m_spellInfo, m_canReflect);
2103
2104 if (targetInfo.reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT) // Impossible reflect again, so simply deflect spell
2105 targetInfo.reflectResult = SPELL_MISS_PARRY;
2106
2107 // Increase time interval for reflected spells by 1.5
2108 targetInfo.timeDelay += targetInfo.timeDelay >> 1;
2109 }
2110 else
2111 targetInfo.reflectResult = SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2112
2113 // Add target to list
2114 m_UniqueTargetInfo.push_back(targetInfo);
2115}
2116
2117void Spell::AddGOTarget(GameObject* go, uint32 effectMask)
2118{
2119 for (uint32 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2120 {
2121 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].IsEffect())
2122 effectMask &= ~(1 << effIndex);
2123 else
2124 {
2125 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].Effect)
2126 {
2127 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE:
2128 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_REPAIR:
2129 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_SET_DESTRUCTION_STATE:
2130 if (go->GetGoType() != GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_DESTRUCTIBLE_BUILDING)
2131 effectMask &= ~(1 << effIndex);
2132 break;
2133 default:
2134 break;
2135 }
2136 }
2137 }
2138
2139 if (!effectMask)
2140 return;
2141
2142 ObjectGuid targetGUID = go->GetGUID();
2143
2144 // Lookup target in already in list
2145 for (std::list<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2146 {
2147 if (targetGUID == ihit->targetGUID) // Found in list
2148 {
2149 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Add only effect mask
2150 return;
2151 }
2152 }
2153
2154 // This is new target calculate data for him
2155
2156 GOTargetInfo target;
2157 target.targetGUID = targetGUID;
2158 target.effectMask = effectMask;
2159 target.processed = false; // Effects not apply on target
2160
2161 // Spell have speed - need calculate incoming time
2162 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f)
2163 {
2164 // calculate spell incoming interval
2165 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(go->GetPositionX(), go->GetPositionY(), go->GetPositionZ());
2166 if (dist < 5.0f)
2167 dist = 5.0f;
2168 target.timeDelay = uint64(floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f));
2169 if (m_delayMoment == 0 || m_delayMoment > target.timeDelay)
2170 m_delayMoment = target.timeDelay;
2171 }
2172 else
2173 target.timeDelay = 0LL;
2174
2175 // Add target to list
2176 m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.push_back(target);
2177}
2178
2179void Spell::AddItemTarget(Item* item, uint32 effectMask)
2180{
2181 for (uint32 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2182 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].IsEffect())
2183 effectMask &= ~(1 << effIndex);
2184
2185 // no effects left
2186 if (!effectMask)
2187 return;
2188
2189 // Lookup target in already in list
2190 for (std::list<ItemTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2191 {
2192 if (item == ihit->item) // Found in list
2193 {
2194 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Add only effect mask
2195 return;
2196 }
2197 }
2198
2199 // This is new target add data
2200
2201 ItemTargetInfo target;
2202 target.item = item;
2203 target.effectMask = effectMask;
2204
2205 m_UniqueItemInfo.push_back(target);
2206}
2207
2208void Spell::AddDestTarget(SpellDestination const& dest, uint32 effIndex)
2209{
2210 m_destTargets[effIndex] = dest;
2211}
2212
2213void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(TargetInfo* target)
2214{
2215 if (!target || target->processed)
2216 return;
2217
2218 target->processed = true; // Target checked in apply effects procedure
2219
2220 // Get mask of effects for target
2221 uint8 mask = target->effectMask;
2222
2223 Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == target->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, target->targetGUID);
2224 if (!unit && !target->targetGUID.IsPlayer()) // only players may be targeted across maps
2225 return;
2226
2227 if (!unit)
2228 {
2229 uint8 farMask = 0;
2230 // create far target mask
2231 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2232 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsFarUnitTargetEffect())
2233 if ((1 << i) & mask)
2234 farMask |= (1 << i);
2235
2236 if (!farMask)
2237 return;
2238 // find unit in world
2239 unit = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(target->targetGUID);
2240 if (!unit)
2241 return;
2242
2243 // do far effects on the unit
2244 // can't use default call because of threading, do stuff as fast as possible
2245 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2246 if (farMask & (1 << i))
2247 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, i, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2248 return;
2249 }
2250
2251 if (unit->IsAlive() != target->alive)
2252 return;
2253
2254 if (getState() == SPELL_STATE_DELAYED && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive() && (getMSTime() - target->timeDelay) <= unit->m_lastSanctuaryTime)
2255 return; // No missinfo in that case
2256
2257 // Get original caster (if exist) and calculate damage/healing from him data
2258 Unit* caster = m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster : m_caster;
2259
2260 // Skip if m_originalCaster not avaiable
2261 if (!caster)
2262 return;
2263
2264 SpellMissInfo missInfo = target->missCondition;
2265
2266 // Need init unitTarget by default unit (can changed in code on reflect)
2267 // Or on missInfo != SPELL_MISS_NONE unitTarget undefined (but need in trigger subsystem)
2268 unitTarget = unit;
2269
2270 // Reset damage/healing counter
2271 m_damage = target->damage;
2272 m_healing = -target->damage;
2273
2274 // Fill base trigger info
2275 uint32 procAttacker = m_procAttacker;
2276 uint32 procVictim = m_procVictim;
2277 uint32 procEx = m_procEx;
2278
2279 m_spellAura = NULL; // Set aura to null for every target-make sure that pointer is not used for unit without aura applied
2280
2281 //Spells with this flag cannot trigger if effect is cast on self
2282 bool canEffectTrigger = !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_CANT_TRIGGER_PROC) && unitTarget->CanProc() && (CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(mask) || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2);
2283 Unit* spellHitTarget = NULL;
2284
2285 if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // In case spell hit target, do all effect on that target
2286 spellHitTarget = unit;
2287 else if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT) // In case spell reflect from target, do all effect on caster (if hit)
2288 {
2289 if (target->reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // If reflected spell hit caster -> do all effect on him
2290 {
2291 spellHitTarget = m_caster;
2292 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2293 m_caster->ToCreature()->LowerPlayerDamageReq(target->damage);
2294 }
2295 }
2296
2297 if (spellHitTarget)
2298 {
2299 SpellMissInfo missInfo2 = DoSpellHitOnUnit(spellHitTarget, mask, target->scaleAura);
2300 if (missInfo2 != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
2301 {
2302 if (missInfo2 != SPELL_MISS_MISS)
2303 m_caster->SendSpellMiss(unit, m_spellInfo->Id, missInfo2);
2304 m_damage = 0;
2305 spellHitTarget = NULL;
2306 }
2307 }
2308
2309 // Do not take combo points on dodge and miss
2310 if (missInfo != SPELL_MISS_NONE && m_needComboPoints &&
2311 m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID() == target->targetGUID)
2312 {
2313 m_needComboPoints = false;
2314 // Restore spell mods for a miss/dodge/parry Cold Blood
2315 /// @todo check how broad this rule should be
2316 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_MISS ||
2317 missInfo == SPELL_MISS_DODGE || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_PARRY))
2318 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this, 14177);
2319 }
2320
2321 // Trigger info was not filled in spell::preparedatafortriggersystem - we do it now
2322 if (canEffectTrigger && !procAttacker && !procVictim)
2323 {
2324 bool positive = true;
2325 if (m_damage > 0)
2326 positive = false;
2327 else if (!m_healing)
2328 positive = m_spellInfo->IsPositive();
2329
2330 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
2331 {
2332 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
2333 if (positive)
2334 {
2335 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2336 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2337 }
2338 else
2339 {
2340 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2341 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2342 }
2343 break;
2344 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE:
2345 if (positive)
2346 {
2347 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2348 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2349 }
2350 else
2351 {
2352 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2353 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2354 }
2355 break;
2356 }
2357 }
2358 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2359
2360 // All calculated do it!
2361 // Do healing and triggers
2362 if (m_healing > 0)
2363 {
2364 bool crit = target->crit;
2365 uint32 addhealth = m_healing;
2366 if (crit)
2367 {
2368 procEx |= PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT;
2369 addhealth = caster->SpellCriticalHealingBonus(m_spellInfo, addhealth, NULL);
2370 }
2371 else
2372 procEx |= PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT;
2373
2374 int32 gain = caster->HealBySpell(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, addhealth, crit);
2375 unitTarget->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(caster, float(gain) * 0.5f, m_spellInfo);
2376 m_healing = gain;
2377
2378 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2379 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2380 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unitTarget, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, addhealth, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2381 }
2382 // Do damage and triggers
2383 else if (m_damage > 0)
2384 {
2385 // Fill base damage struct (unitTarget - is real spell target)
2386 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(caster, unitTarget, m_spellInfo->Id, m_spellSchoolMask);
2387
2388 // Add bonuses and fill damageInfo struct
2389 caster->CalculateSpellDamageTaken(&damageInfo, m_damage, m_spellInfo, m_attackType, target->crit);
2390 caster->DealDamageMods(damageInfo.target, damageInfo.damage, &damageInfo.absorb);
2391
2392 // Send log damage message to client
2393 caster->SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(&damageInfo);
2394
2395 procEx |= createProcExtendMask(&damageInfo, missInfo);
2396 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_DAMAGE;
2397
2398 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2399 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2400 {
2401 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unitTarget, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, damageInfo.damage, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2402 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_STOP_ATTACK_TARGET) == 0 &&
2403 (m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED))
2404 caster->ToPlayer()->CastItemCombatSpell(unitTarget, m_attackType, procVictim, procEx);
2405 }
2406
2407 m_damage = damageInfo.damage;
2408
2409 caster->DealSpellDamage(&damageInfo, true);
2410 }
2411 // Passive spell hits/misses or active spells only misses (only triggers)
2412 else
2413 {
2414 // Fill base damage struct (unitTarget - is real spell target)
2415 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(caster, unitTarget, m_spellInfo->Id, m_spellSchoolMask);
2416 procEx |= createProcExtendMask(&damageInfo, missInfo);
2417 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2418 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2419 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unit, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, 0, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2420
2421 // Failed Pickpocket, reveal rogue
2422 if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_RESIST && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2423 {
2424 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_TALK);
2425 if (unitTarget->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2426 unitTarget->ToCreature()->AI()->AttackStart(m_caster);
2427 }
2428 }
2429
2430 if (missInfo != SPELL_MISS_EVADE && !m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(unit) && (!m_spellInfo->IsPositive() || m_spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_DISPEL)))
2431 {
2432 m_caster->CombatStart(unit, m_spellInfo->HasInitialAggro());
2433
2434 if (!unit->IsStandState())
2435 unit->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
2436 }
2437
2438 if (spellHitTarget)
2439 {
2440 //AI functions
