2441 if (spellHitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2442 if (spellHitTarget->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2443 spellHitTarget->ToCreature()->AI()->SpellHit(m_caster, m_spellInfo);
2444
2445 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2446 m_caster->ToCreature()->AI()->SpellHitTarget(spellHitTarget, m_spellInfo);
2447
2448 // Needs to be called after dealing damage/healing to not remove breaking on damage auras
2449 DoTriggersOnSpellHit(spellHitTarget, mask);
2450
2451 // if target is fallged for pvp also flag caster if a player
2452 if (unit->IsPvP() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2453 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePvP(true);
2454
2455 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2456 }
2457}
2458
2459SpellMissInfo Spell::DoSpellHitOnUnit(Unit* unit, uint32 effectMask, bool scaleAura)
2460{
2461 if (!unit || !effectMask)
2462 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2463
2464 // For delayed spells immunity may be applied between missile launch and hit - check immunity for that case
2465 if (m_spellInfo->Speed && (unit->IsImmunedToDamage(m_spellInfo) || unit->IsImmunedToSpell(m_spellInfo)))
2466 return SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2467
2468 // disable effects to which unit is immune
2469 SpellMissInfo returnVal = SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2470 for (uint32 effectNumber = 0; effectNumber < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effectNumber)
2471 {
2472 if (effectMask & (1 << effectNumber))
2473 {
2474 if (unit->IsImmunedToSpellEffect(m_spellInfo, effectNumber))
2475 effectMask &= ~(1 << effectNumber);
2476 else if (m_spellInfo->Effects[effectNumber].IsAura() && !m_spellInfo->IsPositiveEffect(effectNumber))
2477 {
2478 int32 debuff_resist_chance = unit->GetMaxPositiveAuraModifierByMiscValue(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DEBUFF_RESISTANCE, int32(m_spellInfo->Dispel));
2479 debuff_resist_chance += unit->GetMaxNegativeAuraModifierByMiscValue(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DEBUFF_RESISTANCE, int32(m_spellInfo->Dispel));
2480
2481 if (debuff_resist_chance > 0)
2482 if (irand(0, 10000) <= (debuff_resist_chance * 100))
2483 {
2484 effectMask &= ~(1 << effectNumber);
2485 returnVal = SPELL_MISS_RESIST;
2486 }
2487 }
2488 }
2489 }
2490
2491 if (!effectMask)
2492 return returnVal;
2493
2494 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2495 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2496
2497 if (Player* player = unit->ToPlayer())
2498 {
2499 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_SPELL_TARGET, m_spellInfo->Id);
2500 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_BE_SPELL_TARGET, m_spellInfo->Id, 0, m_caster);
2501 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_BE_SPELL_TARGET2, m_spellInfo->Id);
2502 }
2503
2504 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
2505 {
2506 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_SPELL_CASTER, m_spellInfo->Id);
2507 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_CAST_SPELL2, m_spellInfo->Id, 0, unit);
2508 }
2509
2510 if (m_caster != unit)
2511 {
2512 // Recheck UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE for delayed spells
2513 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && unit->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE) && unit->GetCharmerOrOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
2514 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2515
2516 if (m_caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unit, m_spellInfo))
2517 {
2518 unit->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_HITBYSPELL);
2519
2520 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_DONT_BREAK_STEALTH))
2521 unit->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH);
2522 }
2523 else if (m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(unit))
2524 {
2525 // for delayed spells ignore negative spells (after duel end) for friendly targets
2526 /// @todo this cause soul transfer bugged
2527 // 63881 - Malady of the Mind jump spell (Yogg-Saron)
2528 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && unit->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive() && m_spellInfo->Id != 63881)
2529 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2530
2531 // assisting case, healing and resurrection
2532 if (unit->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ATTACK_PLAYER))
2533 {
2534 m_caster->SetContestedPvP();
2535 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2536 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePvP(true);
2537 }
2538 if (unit->IsInCombat() && m_spellInfo->HasInitialAggro())
2539 {
2540 m_caster->SetInCombatState(unit->GetCombatTimer() > 0, unit);
2541 unit->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(m_caster, 0.0f);
2542 }
2543 }
2544 }
2545
2546 uint8 aura_effmask = 0;
2547 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2548 if (effectMask & (1 << i) && m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsUnitOwnedAuraEffect())
2549 aura_effmask |= 1 << i;
2550
2551 // Get Data Needed for Diminishing Returns, some effects may have multiple auras, so this must be done on spell hit, not aura add
2552 m_diminishGroup = GetDiminishingReturnsGroupForSpell(m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell != nullptr);
2553 if (m_diminishGroup && aura_effmask)
2554 {
2555 m_diminishLevel = unit->GetDiminishing(m_diminishGroup);
2556 DiminishingReturnsType type = GetDiminishingReturnsGroupType(m_diminishGroup);
2557 // Increase Diminishing on unit, current informations for actually casts will use values above
2558 if ((type == DRTYPE_PLAYER &&
2559 (unit->GetCharmerOrOwnerPlayerOrPlayerItself() || (unit->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && unit->ToCreature()->GetCreatureTemplate()->flags_extra & CREATURE_FLAG_EXTRA_ALL_DIMINISH))) ||
2560 type == DRTYPE_ALL)
2561 unit->IncrDiminishing(m_diminishGroup);
2562 }
2563
2564 if (aura_effmask)
2565 {
2566 // Select rank for aura with level requirements only in specific cases
2567 // Unit has to be target only of aura effect, both caster and target have to be players, target has to be other than unit target
2568 SpellInfo const* aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo;
2569 int32 basePoints[3];
2570 if (scaleAura)
2571 {
2572 aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo->GetAuraRankForLevel(unitTarget->getLevel());
2573 ASSERT(aurSpellInfo);
2574 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2575 {
2576 basePoints[i] = aurSpellInfo->Effects[i].BasePoints;
2577 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect != aurSpellInfo->Effects[i].Effect)
2578 {
2579 aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo;
2580 break;
2581 }
2582 }
2583 }
2584
2585 if (m_originalCaster)
2586 {
2587 bool refresh = false;
2588 m_spellAura = Aura::TryRefreshStackOrCreate(aurSpellInfo, effectMask, unit,
2589 m_originalCaster, (aurSpellInfo == m_spellInfo) ? &m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[0] : &basePoints[0], m_CastItem, ObjectGuid::Empty, &refresh);
2590 if (m_spellAura)
2591 {
2592 // Set aura stack amount to desired value
2593 if (m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount > 1)
2594 {
2595 if (!refresh)
2596 m_spellAura->SetStackAmount(m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount);
2597 else
2598 m_spellAura->ModStackAmount(m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount);
2599 }
2600
2601 // Now Reduce spell duration using data received at spell hit
2602 int32 duration = m_spellAura->GetMaxDuration();
2603 int32 limitduration = GetDiminishingReturnsLimitDuration(m_diminishGroup, aurSpellInfo);
2604 float diminishMod = unit->ApplyDiminishingToDuration(m_diminishGroup, duration, m_originalCaster, m_diminishLevel, limitduration);
2605
2606 // unit is immune to aura if it was diminished to 0 duration
2607 if (diminishMod == 0.0f)
2608 {
2609 m_spellAura->Remove();
2610 bool found = false;
2611 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2612 if (effectMask & (1 << i) && m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2613 found = true;
2614 if (!found)
2615 return SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2616 }
2617 else
2618 {
2619 ((UnitAura*)m_spellAura)->SetDiminishGroup(m_diminishGroup);
2620
2621 bool positive = m_spellAura->GetSpellInfo()->IsPositive();
2622 if (AuraApplication* aurApp = m_spellAura->GetApplicationOfTarget(m_originalCaster->GetGUID()))
2623 positive = aurApp->IsPositive();
2624
2625 duration = m_originalCaster->ModSpellDuration(aurSpellInfo, unit, duration, positive, effectMask);
2626
2627 // Haste modifies duration of channeled spells
2628 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
2629 m_originalCaster->ModSpellDurationTime(aurSpellInfo, duration, this);
2630 // and duration of auras affected by SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HASTE
2631 else if (m_originalCaster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HASTE, aurSpellInfo) || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HASTE_AFFECT_DURATION))
2632 duration = int32(duration * m_originalCaster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
2633
2634 if (duration != m_spellAura->GetMaxDuration())
2635 {
2636 m_spellAura->SetMaxDuration(duration);
2637 m_spellAura->SetDuration(duration);
2638 }
2639 m_spellAura->_RegisterForTargets();
2640 }
2641 }
2642 }
2643 }
2644
2645 for (uint32 effectNumber = 0; effectNumber < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effectNumber)
2646 if (effectMask & (1 << effectNumber))
2647 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, effectNumber, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2648
2649 return SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2650}
2651
2652void Spell::DoTriggersOnSpellHit(Unit* unit, uint8 effMask)
2653{
2654 // Apply additional spell effects to target
2655 /// @todo move this code to scripts
2656 if (m_preCastSpell)
2657 {
2658 // Paladin immunity shields
2659 if (m_preCastSpell == 61988)
2660 {
2661 // Cast Forbearance
2662 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, 25771, true);
2663 // Cast Avenging Wrath Marker
2664 unit->CastSpell(unit, 61987, true);
2665 }
2666
2667 // Avenging Wrath
2668 if (m_preCastSpell == 61987)
2669 // Cast the serverside immunity shield marker
2670 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, 61988, true);
2671
2672 if (sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_preCastSpell))
2673 // Blizz seems to just apply aura without bothering to cast
2674 m_caster->AddAura(m_preCastSpell, unit);
2675 }
2676
2677 // handle SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras
2678 // this is executed after spell proc spells on target hit
2679 // spells are triggered for each hit spell target
2680 // info confirmed with retail sniffs of permafrost and shadow weaving
2681 if (!m_hitTriggerSpells.empty())
2682 {
2683 int _duration = 0;
2684 for (HitTriggerSpellList::const_iterator i = m_hitTriggerSpells.begin(); i != m_hitTriggerSpells.end(); ++i)
2685 {
2686 if (CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(effMask, i->triggeredByAura) && roll_chance_i(i->chance))
2687 {
2688 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, i->triggeredSpell, true);
2689 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %d triggered spell %d by SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER aura", m_spellInfo->Id, i->triggeredSpell->Id);
2690
2691 // SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras shouldn't trigger auras without duration
2692 // set duration of current aura to the triggered spell
2693 if (i->triggeredSpell->GetDuration() == -1)
2694 {
2695 if (Aura* triggeredAur = unit->GetAura(i->triggeredSpell->Id, m_caster->GetGUID()))
2696 {
2697 // get duration from aura-only once
2698 if (!_duration)
2699 {
2700 Aura* aur = unit->GetAura(m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster->GetGUID());
2701 _duration = aur ? aur->GetDuration() : -1;
2702 }
2703 triggeredAur->SetDuration(_duration);
2704 }
2705 }
2706 }
2707 }
2708 }
2709
2710 // trigger linked auras remove/apply
2711 /// @todo remove/cleanup this, as this table is not documented and people are doing stupid things with it
2712 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(m_spellInfo->Id + SPELL_LINK_HIT))
2713 {
2714 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator i = spellTriggered->begin(); i != spellTriggered->end(); ++i)
2715 {
2716 if (*i < 0)
2717 unit->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(-(*i));
2718 else
2719 unit->CastSpell(unit, *i, true, nullptr, nullptr, m_caster->GetGUID());
2720 }
2721 }
2722}
2723
2724void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(GOTargetInfo* target)
2725{
2726 if (target->processed) // Check target
2727 return;
2728 target->processed = true; // Target checked in apply effects procedure
2729
2730 uint32 effectMask = target->effectMask;
2731 if (!effectMask)
2732 return;
2733
2734 GameObject* go = m_caster->GetMap()->GetGameObject(target->targetGUID);
2735 if (!go)
2736 return;
2737
2738 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2739 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2740
2741 for (uint32 effectNumber = 0; effectNumber < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effectNumber)
2742 if (effectMask & (1 << effectNumber))
2743 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, go, effectNumber, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2744
2745 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2746 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2747}
2748
2749void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(ItemTargetInfo* target)
2750{
2751 uint32 effectMask = target->effectMask;
2752 if (!target->item || !effectMask)
2753 return;
2754
2755 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2756 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2757
2758 for (uint32 effectNumber = 0; effectNumber < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effectNumber)
2759 if (effectMask & (1 << effectNumber))
2760 HandleEffects(NULL, target->item, NULL, effectNumber, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2761
2762 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2763
2764 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2765}
2766
2767bool Spell::UpdateChanneledTargetList()
2768{
2769 // Not need check return true
2770 if (m_channelTargetEffectMask == 0)
2771 return true;
2772
2773 uint8 channelTargetEffectMask = m_channelTargetEffectMask;
2774 uint8 channelAuraMask = 0;
2775 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2776 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2777 channelAuraMask |= 1<<i;
2778
2779 channelAuraMask &= channelTargetEffectMask;
2780
2781 float range = 0;
2782 if (channelAuraMask)
2783 {
2784 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(m_spellInfo->IsPositive());
2785 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2786 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RANGE, range, this);
2787 }
2788
2789 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2790 {
2791 if (ihit->missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE && (channelTargetEffectMask & ihit->effectMask))
2792 {
2793 Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
2794
2795 if (!unit)
2796 continue;
2797
2798 if (IsValidDeadOrAliveTarget(unit))
2799 {
2800 if (channelAuraMask & ihit->effectMask)
2801 {
2802 if (AuraApplication * aurApp = unit->GetAuraApplication(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID))
2803 {
2804 if (m_caster != unit && !m_caster->IsWithinDistInMap(unit, range))
2805 {
2806 ihit->effectMask &= ~aurApp->GetEffectMask();
2807 unit->RemoveAura(aurApp);
2808 continue;
2809 }
2810 }
2811 else // aura is dispelled
2812 continue;
2813 }
2814
2815 channelTargetEffectMask &= ~ihit->effectMask; // remove from need alive mask effect that have alive target
2816 }
2817 }
2818 }
2819
2820 // is all effects from m_needAliveTargetMask have alive targets
2821 return channelTargetEffectMask == 0;
2822}
2823
2824void Spell::prepare(SpellCastTargets const* targets, AuraEffect const* triggeredByAura)
2825{
2826 if (m_CastItem)
2827 {
2828 m_castItemGUID = m_CastItem->GetGUID();
2829 m_castItemEntry = m_CastItem->GetEntry();
2830 }
2831 else
2832 {
2833 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
2834 m_castItemEntry = 0;
2835 }
2836
2837 InitExplicitTargets(*targets);
2838
2839 // Fill aura scaling information
2840 if (m_caster->IsControlledByPlayer() && !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && m_spellInfo->SpellLevel && !m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_AURA_SCALING))
2841 {
2842 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2843 {
2844 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2845 {
2846 // Change aura with ranks only if basepoints are taken from spellInfo and aura is positive
2847 if (m_spellInfo->IsPositiveEffect(i))
2848 {
2849 m_auraScaleMask |= (1 << i);
2850 if (m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[i] != m_spellInfo->Effects[i].BasePoints)
2851 {
2852 m_auraScaleMask = 0;
2853 break;
2854 }
2855 }
2856 }
2857 }
2858 }
2859
2860 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_PREPARING;
2861
2862 if (triggeredByAura)
2863 m_triggeredByAuraSpell = triggeredByAura->GetSpellInfo();
2864
2865 // create and add update event for this spell
2866 SpellEvent* Event = new SpellEvent(this);
2867 m_caster->m_Events.AddEvent(Event, m_caster->m_Events.CalculateTime(1));
2868
2869 //Prevent casting at cast another spell (ServerSide check)
2870 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS) && m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, true, true) && m_cast_count)
2871 {
2872 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS);
2873 finish(false);
2874 return;
2875 }
2876
2877 if (DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster))
2878 {
2879 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_UNAVAILABLE);
2880 finish(false);
2881 return;
2882 }
2883 LoadScripts();
2884
2885 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2886 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
2887 // Fill cost data (not use power for item casts
2888 m_powerCost = m_CastItem ? 0 : m_spellInfo->CalcPowerCost(m_caster, m_spellSchoolMask);
2889 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2890 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2891
2892 // Set combo point requirement
2893 if ((_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_COMBO_POINTS) || m_CastItem || !m_caster->m_movedPlayer)
2894 m_needComboPoints = false;
2895
2896 SpellCastResult result = CheckCast(true);
2897 if (result != SPELL_CAST_OK && !IsAutoRepeat()) //always cast autorepeat dummy for triggering
2898 {
2899 // Periodic auras should be interrupted when aura triggers a spell which can't be cast
2900 // for example bladestorm aura should be removed on disarm as of patch 3.3.5
2901 // channeled periodic spells should be affected by this (arcane missiles, penance, etc)
2902 // a possible alternative sollution for those would be validating aura target on unit state change
2903 if (triggeredByAura && triggeredByAura->IsPeriodic() && !triggeredByAura->GetBase()->IsPassive())
2904 {
2905 SendChannelUpdate(0);
2906 triggeredByAura->GetBase()->SetDuration(0);
2907 }
2908
2909 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2910 {
2911 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
2912 // cleanup after mod system
2913 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
2914 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2915 }
2916
2917 SendCastResult(result);
2918
2919 finish(false);
2920 return;
2921 }
2922
2923 // Prepare data for triggers
2924 prepareDataForTriggerSystem(triggeredByAura);
2925
2926 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
2927 {
2928 if (!player->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_CASTTIME))
2929 {
2930 player->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
2931 // calculate cast time (calculated after first CheckCast check to prevent charge counting for first CheckCast fail)
2932 m_casttime = m_spellInfo->CalcCastTime(this);
2933 player->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2934 }
2935 else
2936 m_casttime = 0; // Set cast time to 0 if .cheat casttime is enabled.
2937 }
2938 else
2939 m_casttime = m_spellInfo->CalcCastTime(this);
2940
2941 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && !m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED)) // _UNIT actually means creature. for some reason.
2942 if (!(IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() || IsAutoRepeat() || _triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SET_FACING))
2943 {
2944 if (m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && m_caster != m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
2945 {
2946 if (m_caster->ToCreature()->FocusTarget(this, m_targets.GetObjectTarget()))
2947 {
2948 m_isDelayedInstantCast = true;
2949 m_timer = 100; // 100ms delay ensures client has updated creature orientation when cast goes off
2950 }
2951 }
2952 else if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_DONT_TURN_DURING_CAST))
2953 {
2954 if (m_caster->ToCreature()->FocusTarget(this, nullptr))
2955 {
2956 m_isDelayedInstantCast = true;
2957 m_timer = 100;
2958 }
2959 }
2960 }
2961
2962 // don't allow channeled spells / spells with cast time to be cast while moving
2963 // (even if they are interrupted on moving, spells with almost immediate effect get to have their effect processed before movement interrupter kicks in)
2964 if ((m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() || m_casttime) && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->isMoving() && m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_MOVEMENT)
2965 {
2966 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_MOVING);
2967 finish(false);
2968 return;
2969 }
2970
2971 // set timer base at cast time
2972 ReSetTimer();
2973
2974 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::prepare: spell id %u source %u caster %d customCastFlags %u mask %u", m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster->GetEntry(), m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster->GetEntry() : -1, _triggeredCastFlags, m_targets.GetTargetMask());
2975
2976 //Containers for channeled spells have to be set
2977 /// @todoApply this to all cast spells if needed
2978 // Why check duration? 29350: channelled triggers channelled
2979 if ((_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_CAST_DIRECTLY) && (!m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() || !m_spellInfo->GetMaxDuration()))
2980 cast(true);
2981 else
2982 {
2983 // stealth must be removed at cast starting (at show channel bar)
2984 // skip triggered spell (item equip spell casting and other not explicit character casts/item uses)
2985 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAGS) && m_spellInfo->IsBreakingStealth())
2986 {
2987 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_CAST);
2988 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2989 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].GetUsedTargetObjectType() == TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT)
2990 {
2991 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_SPELL_ATTACK);
2992 break;
2993 }
2994 }
2995
2996 m_caster->SetCurrentCastSpell(this);
2997 if (!m_isDelayedInstantCast)
2998 SendSpellStart();
2999
3000 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_GCD))
3001 TriggerGlobalCooldown();
3002
3003 //item: first cast may destroy item and second cast causes crash
3004 if (!m_casttime && !m_isDelayedInstantCast && !m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime && !m_castItemGUID && GetCurrentContainer() == CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL)
3005 cast(true);
3006 }
3007}
3008
3009void Spell::cancel()
3010{
3011 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3012 return;
3013 // delayed instant casts are used for client-side visual orientation; they are treated as instant for all intents and purposes server-side, and thus cannot be interrupted by another cast
3014 if (m_isDelayedInstantCast)
3015 return;
3016
3017 uint32 oldState = m_spellState;
3018 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_FINISHED;
3019
3020 m_autoRepeat = false;
3021 switch (oldState)
3022 {
3023 case SPELL_STATE_PREPARING:
3024 CancelGlobalCooldown();
3025 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3026 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3027 // no break
3028 case SPELL_STATE_DELAYED:
3029 SendInterrupted(0);
3030 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_INTERRUPTED);
3031 break;
3032
3033 case SPELL_STATE_CASTING:
3034 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3035 if ((*ihit).missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
3036 if (Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID))
3037 unit->RemoveOwnedAura(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID, 0, AURA_REMOVE_BY_CANCEL);
3038
3039 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3040 SendInterrupted(0);
3041 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_INTERRUPTED);
3042
3043 // spell is canceled-take mods and clear list
3044 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3045 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RemoveSpellMods(this);
3046
3047 m_appliedMods.clear();
3048 break;
3049
3050 default:
3051 break;
3052 }
3053
3054 SetReferencedFromCurrent(false);
3055 if (m_selfContainer && *m_selfContainer == this)
3056 *m_selfContainer = NULL;
3057
3058 m_caster->RemoveDynObject(m_spellInfo->Id);
3059 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled()) // if not channeled then the object for the current cast wasn't summoned yet
3060 m_caster->RemoveGameObject(m_spellInfo->Id, true);
3061
3062 //set state back so finish will be processed
3063 m_spellState = oldState;
3064
3065 finish(false);
3066}
3067
3068void Spell::cast(bool skipCheck)
3069{
3070 // update pointers base at GUIDs to prevent access to non-existed already object
3071 if (!UpdatePointers())
3072 {
3073 // cancel the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3074 cancel();
3075 return;
3076 }
3077
3078 // cancel at lost explicit target during cast
3079 if (m_targets.GetObjectTargetGUID() && !m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3080 {
3081 cancel();
3082 return;
3083 }
3084
3085 if (m_isDelayedInstantCast)
3086 SendSpellStart();
3087
3088 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3089 {
3090 // now that we've done the basic check, now run the scripts
3091 // should be done before the spell is actually executed
3092 sScriptMgr->OnPlayerSpellCast(playerCaster, this, skipCheck);
3093
3094 // As of 3.0.2 pets begin attacking their owner's target immediately
3095 // Let any pets know we've attacked something. Check DmgClass for harmful spells only
3096 // This prevents spells such as Hunter's Mark from triggering pet attack
3097 if (this->GetSpellInfo()->DmgClass != SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE)
3098 if (Pet* playerPet = playerCaster->GetPet())
3099 if (playerPet->IsAlive() && playerPet->isControlled() && (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT))
3100 playerPet->AI()->OwnerAttacked(m_targets.GetUnitTarget());
3101 }
3102
3103 SetExecutedCurrently(true);
3104
3105 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SET_FACING))
3106 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && m_caster != m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3107 m_caster->SetInFront(m_targets.GetObjectTarget());
3108
3109 // Should this be done for original caster?
3110 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3111 {
3112 // Set spell which will drop charges for triggered cast spells
3113 // if not successfully cast, will be remove in finish(false)
3114 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3115 }
3116
3117 CallScriptBeforeCastHandlers();
3118
3119 // skip check if done already (for instant cast spells for example)
3120 if (!skipCheck)
3121 {
3122 SpellCastResult castResult = CheckCast(false);
3123 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
3124 {
3125 SendCastResult(castResult);
3126 SendInterrupted(0);
3127 //restore spell mods
3128 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3129 {
3130 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3131 // cleanup after mod system
3132 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3133 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3134 }
3135 finish(false);
3136 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3137 return;
3138 }
3139
3140 // additional check after cast bar completes (must not be in CheckCast)
3141 // if trade not complete then remember it in trade data
3142 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
3143 {
3144 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3145 {
3146 if (TradeData* my_trade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData())
3147 {
3148 if (!my_trade->IsInAcceptProcess())
3149 {
3150 // Spell will be cast after completing the trade. Silently ignore at this place
3151 my_trade->SetSpell(m_spellInfo->Id, m_CastItem);
3152 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT);
3153 SendInterrupted(0);
3154 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3155 // cleanup after mod system
3156 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3157 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3158 finish(false);
3159 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3160 return;
3161 }
3162 }
3163 }
3164 }
3165 }
3166
3167 // if the spell allows the creature to turn while casting, then adjust server-side orientation to face the target now
3168 // client-side orientation is handled by the client itself, as the cast target is targeted due to Creature::FocusTarget
3169 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && !m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
3170 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_DONT_TURN_DURING_CAST))
3171 if (WorldObject* objTarget = m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3172 {
3173 m_caster->SetInFront(objTarget);
3174 m_caster->SetFacingToObject(objTarget);
3175 }
3176
3177 SelectSpellTargets();
3178
3179 // Spell may be finished after target map check
3180 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3181 {
3182 SendInterrupted(0);
3183 //restore spell mods
3184 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3185 {
3186 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3187 // cleanup after mod system
3188 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3189 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3190 }
3191 finish(false);
3192 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3193 return;
3194 }
3195
3196 PrepareTriggersExecutedOnHit();
3197
3198 CallScriptOnCastHandlers();
3199
3200 // traded items have trade slot instead of guid in m_itemTargetGUID
3201 // set to real guid to be sent later to the client
3202 m_targets.UpdateTradeSlotItem();
3203
3204 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3205 {
3206 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_ITEM) && m_CastItem)
3207 {
3208 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_ITEM, m_CastItem->GetEntry());
3209 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_USE_ITEM, m_CastItem->GetEntry());
3210 }
3211
3212 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_CAST_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
3213 }
3214
3215 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
3216 {
3217 // Powers have to be taken before SendSpellGo
3218 TakePower();
3219 TakeReagents(); // we must remove reagents before HandleEffects to allow place crafted item in same slot
3220 }
3221 else if (Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
3222 {
3223 /// Not own traded item (in trader trade slot) req. reagents including triggered spell case
3224 if (targetItem->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
3225 TakeReagents();
3226 }
3227
3228 // CAST SPELL
3229 SendSpellCooldown();
3230
3231 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
3232
3233 HandleLaunchPhase();
3234
3235 // we must send smsg_spell_go packet before m_castItem delete in TakeCastItem()...
3236 SendSpellGo();
3237
3238 // Okay, everything is prepared. Now we need to distinguish between immediate and evented delayed spells
3239 if ((m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && !m_spellInfo->IsChanneled()) || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_UNK4))
3240 {
3241 // Remove used for cast item if need (it can be already NULL after TakeReagents call
3242 // in case delayed spell remove item at cast delay start
3243 TakeCastItem();
3244
3245 // Okay, maps created, now prepare flags
3246 m_immediateHandled = false;
3247 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_DELAYED;
3248 SetDelayStart(0);
3249
3250 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, false, true))
3251 m_caster->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING);
3252 }
3253 else
3254 {
3255 // Immediate spell, no big deal
3256 handle_immediate();
3257 }
3258
3259 CallScriptAfterCastHandlers();
3260
3261 if (const std::vector<int32> *spell_triggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(m_spellInfo->Id))
3262 {
3263 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator i = spell_triggered->begin(); i != spell_triggered->end(); ++i)
3264 if (*i < 0)
3265 m_caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(-(*i));
3266 else
3267 m_caster->CastSpell(m_targets.GetUnitTarget() ? m_targets.GetUnitTarget() : m_caster, *i, true);
3268 }
3269
3270 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3271 {
3272 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3273
3274 //Clear spell cooldowns after every spell is cast if .cheat cooldown is enabled.
3275 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_COOLDOWN))
3276 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->ResetCooldown(m_spellInfo->Id, true);
3277 }
3278
3279 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3280
3281 if (Creature* creatureCaster = m_caster->ToCreature())
3282 creatureCaster->ReleaseFocus(this);
3283}
3284
3285void Spell::handle_immediate()
3286{
3287 // start channeling if applicable
3288 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
3289 {
3290 int32 duration = m_spellInfo->GetDuration();
3291 if (duration > 0)
3292 {
3293 // First mod_duration then haste - see Missile Barrage
3294 // Apply duration mod
3295 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
3296 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_DURATION, duration);
3297
3298 // Apply haste mods
3299 m_caster->ModSpellDurationTime(m_spellInfo, duration, this);
3300
3301 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_CASTING;
3302 m_caster->AddInterruptMask(m_spellInfo->ChannelInterruptFlags);
3303 m_channeledDuration = duration;
3304 SendChannelStart(duration);
3305 }
3306 else if (duration == -1)
3307 {
3308 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_CASTING;
3309 m_caster->AddInterruptMask(m_spellInfo->ChannelInterruptFlags);
3310 SendChannelStart(duration);
3311 }
3312 }
3313
3314 PrepareTargetProcessing();
3315
3316 // process immediate effects (items, ground, etc.) also initialize some variables
3317 _handle_immediate_phase();
3318
3319 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3320 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3321
3322 for (std::list<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3323 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3324
3325 FinishTargetProcessing();
3326
3327 // spell is finished, perform some last features of the spell here
3328 _handle_finish_phase();
3329
3330 // Remove used for cast item if need (it can be already NULL after TakeReagents call
3331 TakeCastItem();
3332
3333 // handle ammo consumption for Hunter's volley spell
3334 if (m_spellInfo->IsRangedWeaponSpell() && m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
3335 TakeAmmo();
3336
3337 if (m_spellState != SPELL_STATE_CASTING)
3338 finish(true); // successfully finish spell cast (not last in case autorepeat or channel spell)
3339}
3340
3341uint64 Spell::handle_delayed(uint64 t_offset)
3342{
3343 if (!UpdatePointers())
3344 {
3345 // finish the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3346 finish(false);
3347 return 0;
3348 }
3349
3350 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3351 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3352
3353 uint64 next_time = 0;
3354
3355 PrepareTargetProcessing();
3356
3357 if (!m_immediateHandled)
3358 {
3359 _handle_immediate_phase();
3360 m_immediateHandled = true;
3361 }
3362
3363 bool single_missile = (m_targets.HasDst());
3364
3365 // now recheck units targeting correctness (need before any effects apply to prevent adding immunity at first effect not allow apply second spell effect and similar cases)
3366 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3367 {
3368 if (ihit->processed == false)
3369 {
3370 if (single_missile || ihit->timeDelay <= t_offset)
3371 {
3372 ihit->timeDelay = t_offset;
3373 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3374 }
3375 else if (next_time == 0 || ihit->timeDelay < next_time)
3376 next_time = ihit->timeDelay;
3377 }
3378 }
3379
3380 // now recheck gameobject targeting correctness
3381 for (std::list<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ighit= m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ighit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ighit)
3382 {
3383 if (ighit->processed == false)
3384 {
3385 if (single_missile || ighit->timeDelay <= t_offset)
3386 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ighit));
3387 else if (next_time == 0 || ighit->timeDelay < next_time)
3388 next_time = ighit->timeDelay;
3389 }
3390 }
3391
3392 FinishTargetProcessing();
3393
3394 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3395 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3396
3397 // All targets passed - need finish phase
3398 if (next_time == 0)
3399 {
3400 // spell is finished, perform some last features of the spell here
3401 _handle_finish_phase();
3402
3403 finish(true); // successfully finish spell cast
3404
3405 // return zero, spell is finished now
3406 return 0;
3407 }
3408 else
3409 {
3410 // spell is unfinished, return next execution time
3411 return next_time;
3412 }
3413}
3414
3415void Spell::_handle_immediate_phase()
3416{
3417 m_spellAura = NULL;
3418 // initialize Diminishing Returns Data
3419 m_diminishLevel = DIMINISHING_LEVEL_1;
3420 m_diminishGroup = DIMINISHING_NONE;
3421
3422 // handle some immediate features of the spell here
3423 HandleThreatSpells();
3424
3425 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
3426
3427 // handle effects with SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT mode
3428 for (uint32 j = 0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
3429 {
3430 // don't do anything for empty effect
3431 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[j].IsEffect())
3432 continue;
3433
3434 // call effect handlers to handle destination hit
3435 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, NULL, j, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT);
3436 }
3437
3438 // process items
3439 for (std::list<ItemTargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3440 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3441
3442 if (!m_originalCaster)
3443 return;
3444 // Handle procs on cast
3445 /// @todo finish new proc system:P
3446 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty() && m_targets.HasDst())
3447 {
3448 uint32 procAttacker = m_procAttacker;
3449 if (!procAttacker)
3450 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
3451
3452 // Proc the spells that have DEST target
3453 m_originalCaster->ProcDamageAndSpell(NULL, procAttacker, 0, m_procEx | PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT, 0, BASE_ATTACK, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
3454 }
3455}
3456
3457void Spell::_handle_finish_phase()
3458{
3459 if (m_caster->m_movedPlayer)
3460 {
3461 // Take for real after all targets are processed
3462 if (m_needComboPoints)
3463 m_caster->m_movedPlayer->ClearComboPoints();
3464
3465 // Real add combo points from effects
3466 if (m_comboPointGain)
3467 m_caster->m_movedPlayer->GainSpellComboPoints(m_comboPointGain);
3468 }
3469
3470 if (m_caster->m_extraAttacks && m_spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_ADD_EXTRA_ATTACKS))
3471 {
3472 if (Unit* victim = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_targets.GetOrigUnitTargetGUID()))
3473 m_caster->HandleProcExtraAttackFor(victim);
3474 else
3475 m_caster->m_extraAttacks = 0;
3476 }
3477
3478 /// @todo trigger proc phase finish here
3479}
3480
3481void Spell::SendSpellCooldown()
3482{
3483 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HandleCooldowns(m_spellInfo, m_CastItem, this);
3484}
3485
3486void Spell::update(uint32 difftime)
3487{
3488 // update pointers based at it's GUIDs
3489 if (!UpdatePointers())
3490 {
3491 // cancel the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3492 cancel();
3493 return;
3494 }
3495
3496 if (m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID() && !m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
3497 {
3498 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u is cancelled due to removal of target.", m_spellInfo->Id);
3499 cancel();
3500 return;
3501 }
3502
3503 // check if the player caster has moved before the spell finished
3504 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_timer != 0) &&
3505 m_caster->isMoving() && (m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_MOVEMENT) &&
3506 (m_spellInfo->Effects[0].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_STUCK || !m_caster->HasUnitMovementFlag(MOVEMENTFLAG_FALLING_FAR)))
3507 {
3508 // don't cancel for melee, autorepeat, triggered and instant spells
3509 if (!IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() && !IsAutoRepeat() && !IsTriggered())
3510 cancel();
3511 }
3512
3513 switch (m_spellState)
3514 {
3515 case SPELL_STATE_PREPARING:
3516 {
3517 if (m_timer > 0)
3518 {
3519 if (difftime >= (uint32)m_timer)
3520 m_timer = 0;
3521 else
3522 m_timer -= difftime;
3523 }
3524
3525 if (m_timer == 0 && !IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() && !IsAutoRepeat())
3526 // don't CheckCast for instant spells - done in spell::prepare, skip duplicate checks, needed for range checks for example
3527 cast(!m_casttime);
3528 break;
3529 }
3530 case SPELL_STATE_CASTING:
3531 {
3532 if (m_timer)
3533 {
3534 // check if there are alive targets left
3535 if (!UpdateChanneledTargetList())
3536 {
3537 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Channeled spell %d is removed due to lack of targets", m_spellInfo->Id);
3538 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3539 finish();
3540 }
3541
3542 if (m_timer > 0)
3543 {
3544 if (difftime >= (uint32)m_timer)
3545 m_timer = 0;
3546 else
3547 m_timer -= difftime;
3548 }
3549 }
3550
3551 if (m_timer == 0)
3552 {
3553 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3554 finish();
3555 }
3556 break;
3557 }
3558 default:
3559 break;
3560 }
3561}
3562
3563void Spell::finish(bool ok)
3564{
3565 if (!m_caster)
3566 return;
3567
3568 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3569 return;
3570 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_FINISHED;
3571
3572 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
3573 m_caster->UpdateInterruptMask();
3574
3575 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, false, true))
3576 m_caster->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING);
3577
3578 // Unsummon summon as possessed creatures on spell cancel
3579 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3580 {
3581 if (Unit* charm = m_caster->GetCharm())
3582 if (charm->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT
3583 && charm->ToCreature()->HasUnitTypeMask(UNIT_MASK_PUPPET)
3584 && charm->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL) == m_spellInfo->Id)
3585 ((Puppet*)charm)->UnSummon();
3586 }
3587
3588 if (Creature* creatureCaster = m_caster->ToCreature())
3589 creatureCaster->ReleaseFocus(this);
3590
3591 if (!ok)
3592 return;
3593
3594 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsSummon())
3595 {
3596 // Unsummon statue
3597 uint32 spell = m_caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL);
3598 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(spell);
3599 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 2056)
3600 {
3601 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Statue %d is unsummoned in spell %d finish", m_caster->GetGUID().GetCounter(), m_spellInfo->Id);
3602 m_caster->setDeathState(JUST_DIED);
3603 return;
3604 }
3605 }
3606
3607 if (IsAutoActionResetSpell())
3608 {
3609 bool found = false;
3610 Unit::AuraEffectList const& vIgnoreReset = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_IGNORE_MELEE_RESET);
3611 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = vIgnoreReset.begin(); i != vIgnoreReset.end(); ++i)
3612 {
3613 if ((*i)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
3614 {
3615 found = true;
3616 break;
3617 }
3618 }
3619 if (!found && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NOT_RESET_AUTO_ACTIONS))
3620 {
3621 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(BASE_ATTACK);
3622 if (m_caster->haveOffhandWeapon())
3623 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(OFF_ATTACK);
3624 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(RANGED_ATTACK);
3625 }
3626 }
3627
3628 // potions disabled by client, send event "not in combat" if need
3629 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3630 {
3631 if (!m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3632 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePotionCooldown(this);
3633
3634 // triggered spell pointer can be not set in some cases
3635 // this is needed for proper apply of triggered spell mods
3636 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3637
3638 // Take mods after trigger spell (needed for 14177 to affect 48664)
3639 // mods are taken only on succesfull cast and independantly from targets of the spell
3640 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RemoveSpellMods(this);
3641 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3642 }
3643
3644 // Stop Attack for some spells
3645 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_STOP_ATTACK_TARGET))
3646 m_caster->AttackStop();
3647}
3648
3649void Spell::WriteCastResultInfo(WorldPacket& data, Player* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 castCount, SpellCastResult result, SpellCustomErrors customError)
3650{
3651 data << uint8(castCount); // single cast or multi 2.3 (0/1)
3652 data << uint32(spellInfo->Id);
3653 data << uint8(result); // problem
3654 switch (result)
3655 {
3656 case SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_SPELL_FOCUS:
3657 data << uint32(spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus); // SpellFocusObject.dbc id
3658 break;
3659 case SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA: // AreaTable.dbc id
3660 // hardcode areas limitation case
3661 switch (spellInfo->Id)
3662 {
3663 case 41617: // Cenarion Mana Salve
3664 case 41619: // Cenarion Healing Salve
3665 data << uint32(3905);
3666 break;
3667 case 41618: // Bottled Nethergon Energy
3668 case 41620: // Bottled Nethergon Vapor
3669 data << uint32(3842);
3670 break;
3671 case 45373: // Bloodberry Elixir
3672 data << uint32(4075);
3673 break;
3674 default: // default case (don't must be)
3675 data << uint32(0);
3676 break;
3677 }
3678 break;
3679 case SPELL_FAILED_TOTEMS:
3680 if (spellInfo->Totem[0])
3681 data << uint32(spellInfo->Totem[0]);
3682 if (spellInfo->Totem[1])
3683 data << uint32(spellInfo->Totem[1]);
3684 break;
3685 case SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY:
3686 if (spellInfo->TotemCategory[0])
3687 data << uint32(spellInfo->TotemCategory[0]);
3688 if (spellInfo->TotemCategory[1])
3689 data << uint32(spellInfo->TotemCategory[1]);
3690 break;
3691 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS:
3692 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS_MAINHAND:
3693 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS_OFFHAND:
3694 data << uint32(spellInfo->EquippedItemClass);
3695 data << uint32(spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask);
3696 break;
3697 case SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM:
3698 {
3699 uint32 item = 0;
3700 for (int8 eff = 0; eff < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; eff++)
3701 if (spellInfo->Effects[eff].ItemType)
3702 item = spellInfo->Effects[eff].ItemType;
3703 ItemTemplate const* proto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item);
3704 if (proto && proto->ItemLimitCategory)
3705 data << uint32(proto->ItemLimitCategory);
3706 break;
3707 }
3708 case SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR:
3709 data << uint32(customError);
3710 break;
3711 case SPELL_FAILED_REAGENTS:
3712 {
3713 uint32 missingItem = 0;
3714 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; i++)
3715 {
3716 if (spellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
3717 continue;
3718
3719 uint32 itemid = spellInfo->Reagent[i];
3720 uint32 itemcount = spellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
3721
3722 if (!caster->HasItemCount(itemid, itemcount))
3723 {
3724 missingItem = itemid;
3725 break;
3726 }
3727 }
3728
3729 data << uint32(missingItem); // first missing item
3730 break;
3731 }
3732 case SPELL_FAILED_PREVENTED_BY_MECHANIC:
3733 data << uint32(spellInfo->Mechanic);
3734 break;
3735 case SPELL_FAILED_NEED_EXOTIC_AMMO:
3736 data << uint32(spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask);
3737 break;
3738 case SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS:
3739 data << uint32(0); // Item entry
3740 data << uint32(0); // Count
3741 break;
3742 case SPELL_FAILED_MIN_SKILL:
3743 data << uint32(0); // SkillLine.dbc Id
3744 data << uint32(0); // Amount
3745 break;
3746 case SPELL_FAILED_FISHING_TOO_LOW:
3747 data << uint32(0); // Skill level
3748 break;
3749 default:
3750 break;
3751 }
3752}
3753
3754void Spell::SendCastResult(Player* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 castCount, SpellCastResult result, SpellCustomErrors customError /*= SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_NONE*/)
3755{
3756 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3757 return;
3758
3759 WorldPacket data(SMSG_CAST_FAILED, 1 + 4 + 1);
3760 WriteCastResultInfo(data, caster, spellInfo, castCount, result, customError);
3761
3762 caster->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
3763}
3764
3765void Spell::SendCastResult(SpellCastResult result)
3766{
3767 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3768 return;
3769
3770 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
3771 return;
3772
3773 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSession()->PlayerLoading()) // don't send cast results at loading time
3774 return;
3775
3776 SendCastResult(m_caster->ToPlayer(), m_spellInfo, m_cast_count, result, m_customError);
3777}
3778
3779void Spell::SendPetCastResult(SpellCastResult result)
3780{
3781 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3782 return;
3783
3784 Unit* owner = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner();
3785 if (!owner)
3786 return;
3787
3788 Player* player = owner->ToPlayer();
3789 if (!player)
3790 return;
3791
3792 WorldPacket data(SMSG_PET_CAST_FAILED, 1 + 4 + 1);
3793 WriteCastResultInfo(data, player, m_spellInfo, m_cast_count, result, m_customError);
3794
3795 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
3796}
3797
3798void Spell::SendSpellStart()
3799{
3800 if (!IsNeedSendToClient())
3801 return;
3802
3803 //TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Sending SMSG_SPELL_START id=%u", m_spellInfo->Id);
3804
3805 uint32 castFlags = CAST_FLAG_UNKNOWN_2;
3806 uint32 schoolImmunityMask = m_caster->GetSchoolImmunityMask();
3807 uint32 mechanicImmunityMask = m_caster->GetMechanicImmunityMask();
3808 if (schoolImmunityMask || mechanicImmunityMask)
3809 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_IMMUNITY;
3810
3811 if ((IsTriggered() && !m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell()) || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3812 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_PENDING;
3813
3814 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_REQ_AMMO))
3815 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_AMMO;
3816 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ||
3817 (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsPet()))
3818 && m_spellInfo->PowerType != POWER_HEALTH)
3819 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF;
3820
3821 if (m_spellInfo->RuneCostID && m_spellInfo->PowerType == POWER_RUNE)
3822 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD; // not needed, but Blizzard sends it
3823
3824 WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELL_START, (8+8+4+4+2));
3825 if (m_CastItem)
3826 data << m_CastItem->GetPackGUID();
3827 else
3828 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
3829
3830 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
3831 data << uint8(m_cast_count); // pending spell cast?
3832 data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // spellId
3833 data << uint32(castFlags); // cast flags
3834 data << int32(m_timer); // delay?
3835
3836 m_targets.Write(data);
3837
3838 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF)
3839 data << uint32(m_caster->GetPower((Powers)m_spellInfo->PowerType));
3840
3841 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_AMMO)
3842 WriteAmmoToPacket(&data);
3843
3844 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_IMMUNITY)
3845 {
3846 data << uint32(schoolImmunityMask);
3847 data << uint32(mechanicImmunityMask);
3848 }
3849
3850 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
3851}
3852
3853void Spell::SendSpellGo()
3854{
3855 // not send invisible spell casting
3856 if (!IsNeedSendToClient())
3857 return;
3858
3859 //TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Sending SMSG_SPELL_GO id=%u", m_spellInfo->Id);
3860
3861 uint32 castFlags = CAST_FLAG_UNKNOWN_9;
3862
3863 // triggered spells with spell visual != 0
3864 if ((IsTriggered() && !m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell()) || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3865 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_PENDING;
3866
3867 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_REQ_AMMO))
3868 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_AMMO; // arrows/bullets visual
3869
3870 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ||
3871 (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsPet()))
3872 && m_spellInfo->PowerType != POWER_HEALTH)
3873 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF; // should only be sent to self, but the current messaging doesn't make that possible
3874
3875 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3876 && (m_caster->getClass() == CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
3877 && m_spellInfo->RuneCostID
3878 && m_spellInfo->PowerType == POWER_RUNE
3879 && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
3880 {
3881 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD; // not needed, but Blizzard sends it
3882 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST; // rune cooldowns list
3883 }
3884
3885 if (m_spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_ACTIVATE_RUNE))
3886 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST; // rune cooldowns list
3887
3888 if (m_targets.HasTraj())
3889 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_ADJUST_MISSILE;
3890
3891 if (!m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime)
3892 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD;
3893
3894 WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELL_GO, 50); // guess size
3895
3896 if (m_CastItem)
3897 data << m_CastItem->GetPackGUID();
3898 else
3899 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
3900
3901 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
3902 data << uint8(m_cast_count); // pending spell cast?
3903 data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // spellId
3904 data << uint32(castFlags); // cast flags
3905 data << uint32(getMSTime()); // timestamp
3906
3907 WriteSpellGoTargets(&data);
3908
3909 m_targets.Write(data);
3910
3911 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF)
3912 data << uint32(m_caster->GetPower((Powers)m_spellInfo->PowerType));
3913
3914 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST) // rune cooldowns list
3915 {
3916 /// @todo There is a crash caused by a spell with CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST cast by a creature
3917 //The creature is the mover of a player, so HandleCastSpellOpcode uses it as the caster
3918 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3919 {
3920 uint8 runeMaskInitial = m_runesState;
3921 uint8 runeMaskAfterCast = player->GetRunesState();
3922 data << uint8(runeMaskInitial); // runes state before
3923 data << uint8(runeMaskAfterCast); // runes state after
3924 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
3925 {
3926 uint8 mask = (1 << i);
3927 if (mask & runeMaskInitial && !(mask & runeMaskAfterCast)) // usable before andon cooldown now...
3928 {
3929 // float casts ensure the division is performed on floats as we need float result
3930 float baseCd = float(player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i));
3931 data << uint8((baseCd - float(player->GetRuneCooldown(i))) / baseCd * 255); // rune cooldown passed
3932 }
3933 }
3934 }
3935 }
3936 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_ADJUST_MISSILE)
3937 {
3938 data << m_targets.GetElevation();
3939 data << uint32(m_delayMoment);
3940 }
3941
3942 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_AMMO)
3943 WriteAmmoToPacket(&data);
3944
3945 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_VISUAL_CHAIN)
3946 {
3947 data << uint32(0);
3948 data << uint32(0);
3949 }
3950
3951 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
3952 {
3953 data << uint8(0);
3954 }
3955
3956 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
3957}
3958
3959void Spell::WriteAmmoToPacket(WorldPacket* data)
3960{
3961 uint32 ammoInventoryType = 0;
3962 uint32 ammoDisplayID = 0;
3963
3964 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3965 {
3966 Item* pItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(RANGED_ATTACK);
3967 if (pItem)
3968 {
3969 ammoInventoryType = pItem->GetTemplate()->InventoryType;
3970 if (ammoInventoryType == INVTYPE_THROWN)
3971 ammoDisplayID = pItem->GetTemplate()->DisplayInfoID;
3972 else
3973 {
3974 uint32 ammoID = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_AMMO_ID);
3975 if (ammoID)
3976 {
3977 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(ammoID);
3978 if (pProto)
3979 {
3980 ammoDisplayID = pProto->DisplayInfoID;
3981 ammoInventoryType = pProto->InventoryType;
3982 }
3983 }
3984 else if (m_caster->HasAura(46699)) // Requires No Ammo
3985 {
3986 ammoDisplayID = 5996; // normal arrow
3987 ammoInventoryType = INVTYPE_AMMO;
3988 }
3989 }
3990 }
3991 }
3992 else
3993 {
3994 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
3995 {
3996 if (uint32 item_id = m_caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + i))
3997 {
3998 if (ItemEntry const* itemEntry = sItemStore.LookupEntry(item_id))
3999 {
4000 if (itemEntry->Class == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON)
4001 {
4002 switch (itemEntry->SubClass)
4003 {
4004 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_THROWN:
4005 ammoDisplayID = itemEntry->DisplayId;
4006 ammoInventoryType = itemEntry->InventoryType;
4007 break;
4008 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_BOW:
4009 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_CROSSBOW:
4010 ammoDisplayID = 5996; // is this need fixing?
4011 ammoInventoryType = INVTYPE_AMMO;
4012 break;
4013 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_GUN:
4014 ammoDisplayID = 5998; // is this need fixing?
4015 ammoInventoryType = INVTYPE_AMMO;
4016 break;
4017 }
4018
4019 if (ammoDisplayID)
4020 break;
4021 }
4022 }
4023 }
4024 }
4025 }
4026
4027 *data << uint32(ammoDisplayID);
4028 *data << uint32(ammoInventoryType);
4029}
4030
4031/// Writes miss and hit targets for a SMSG_SPELL_GO packet
4032void Spell::WriteSpellGoTargets(WorldPacket* data)
4033{
4034 // This function also fill data for channeled spells:
4035 // m_needAliveTargetMask req for stop channelig if one target die
4036 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
4037 {
4038 if ((*ihit).effectMask == 0) // No effect apply - all immuned add state
4039 // possibly SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2 for this??
4040 ihit->missCondition = SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2;
4041 }
4042
4043 // Hit and miss target counts are both uint8, that limits us to 255 targets for each
4044 // sending more than 255 targets crashes the client (since count sent would be wrong)
4045 // Spells like 40647 (with a huge radius) can easily reach this limit (spell might need
4046 // target conditions but we still need to limit the number of targets sent and keeping
4047 // correct count for both hit and miss).
4048
4049 uint32 hit = 0;
4050 size_t hitPos = data->wpos();
4051 *data << (uint8)0; // placeholder
4052 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end() && hit < 255; ++ihit)
4053 {
4054 if ((*ihit).missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // Add only hits
4055 {
4056 *data << uint64(ihit->targetGUID);
4057 m_channelTargetEffectMask |=ihit->effectMask;
4058 ++hit;
4059 }
4060 }
4061
4062 for (std::list<GOTargetInfo>::const_iterator ighit = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ighit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end() && hit < 255; ++ighit)
4063 {
4064 *data << uint64(ighit->targetGUID); // Always hits
4065 ++hit;
4066 }
4067
4068 uint32 miss = 0;
4069 size_t missPos = data->wpos();
4070 *data << (uint8)0; // placeholder
4071 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end() && miss < 255; ++ihit)
4072 {
4073 if (ihit->missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE) // Add only miss
4074 {
4075 *data << uint64(ihit->targetGUID);
4076 *data << uint8(ihit->missCondition);
4077 if (ihit->missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
4078 *data << uint8(ihit->reflectResult);
4079 ++miss;
4080 }
4081 }
4082 // Reset m_needAliveTargetMask for non channeled spell
4083 if (!m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
4084 m_channelTargetEffectMask = 0;
4085
4086 data->put<uint8>(hitPos, (uint8)hit);
4087 data->put<uint8>(missPos, (uint8)miss);
4088}
4089
4090void Spell::SendLogExecute()
4091{
4092 WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELLLOGEXECUTE, (8+4+4+4+4+8));
4093
4094 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
4095
4096 data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id);
4097
4098 uint8 effCount = 0;
4099 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
4100 {
4101 if (m_effectExecuteData[i])
4102 ++effCount;
4103 }
4104
4105 if (!effCount)
4106 return;
4107
4108 data << uint32(effCount);
4109 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
4110 {
4111 if (!m_effectExecuteData[i])
4112 continue;
4113
4114 data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect); // spell effect
4115
4116 data.append(*m_effectExecuteData[i]);
4117
4118 delete m_effectExecuteData[i];
4119 m_effectExecuteData[i] = NULL;
4120 }
4121 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
4122}

4208void Spell::SendChannelUpdate(uint32 time)
4209{
4210 if (time == 0)
4211 {
4212 m_caster->SetChannelObjectGuid(ObjectGuid::Empty);
4213 m_caster->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CHANNEL_SPELL, 0);
4214 }
4215

4219
4220 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);

4222
4223void Spell::SendChannelStart(uint32 duration)
4224{
4225 ObjectGuid channelTarget = m_targets.GetObjectTargetGUID();
4226 if (!channelTarget && !m_spellInfo->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
4227 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.size() + m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.size() == 1) // this is for TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY
4228 channelTarget = !m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty() ? m_UniqueTargetInfo.front().targetGUID : m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.front().targetGUID;
4229
4230 WorldPacket data(MSG_CHANNEL_START, (8+4+4));
4231 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
4232 data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id);
4233 data << uint32(duration);
4234
4235 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
4236
4237 m_timer = duration;
4238 if (channelTarget)
4239 m_caster->SetChannelObjectGuid(channelTarget);
4240
4241 m_caster->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CHANNEL_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
4242}
4243
4244void Spell::SendResurrectRequest(Player* target)
4245{
4246 // get resurrector name for creature resurrections, otherwise packet will be not accepted
4247 // for player resurrections the name is looked up by guid
4248 std::string const sentName(m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ?
4249 "" : m_caster->GetNameForLocaleIdx(target->GetSession()->GetSessionDbLocaleIndex()));
4250
4251 WorldPacket data(SMSG_RESURRECT_REQUEST, 8 + 4 + sentName.size() + 1 + 1 + 1);
4252 data << uint64(m_caster->GetGUID());
4253 data << uint32(sentName.size() + 1);
4254 data << sentName;
4255 data << uint8(m_caster->IsSpiritHealer()); // "you'll be afflicted with resurrection sickness"
4256 // override delay sent with SMSG_CORPSE_RECLAIM_DELAY, set instant resurrection for spells with this attribute
4257 data << uint8(!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_IGNORE_RESURRECTION_TIMER));
4258 target->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
4259}
4260
4261void Spell::TakeCastItem()
4262{
4263 if (!m_CastItem)
4264 return;
4265
4266 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4267 if (!player)
4268 return;
4269
4270 // not remove cast item at triggered spell (equipping, weapon damage, etc)
4271 if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_ITEM)
4272 return;
4273
4274 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
4275
4276 if (!proto)
4277 {
4278 // This code is to avoid a crash
4279 // I'm not sure, if this is really an error, but I guess every item needs a prototype
4280 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Cast item has no item prototype %s", m_CastItem->GetGUID().ToString().c_str());
4281 return;
4282 }
4283
4284 bool expendable = false;
4285 bool withoutCharges = false;
4286
4287 for (int i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
4288 {
4289 if (proto->Spells[i].SpellId > 0)
4290 {
4291 // item has limited charges
4292 if (proto->Spells[i].SpellCharges)
4293 {
4294 if (proto->Spells[i].SpellCharges < 0)
4295 expendable = true;
4296
4297 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(i);
4298
4299 // item has charges left
4300 if (charges)
4301 {
4302 (charges > 0) ? --charges : ++charges; // abs(charges) less at 1 after use
4303 if (proto->Stackable == 1)
4304 m_CastItem->SetSpellCharges(i, charges);
4305 m_CastItem->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, player);
4306 }
4307
4308 // all charges used
4309 withoutCharges = (charges == 0);
4310 }
4311 }
4312 }
4313
4314 if (expendable && withoutCharges)
4315 {
4316 uint32 count = 1;
4317 m_caster->ToPlayer()->DestroyItemCount(m_CastItem, count, true);
4318
4319 // prevent crash at access to deleted m_targets.GetItemTarget
4320 if (m_CastItem == m_targets.GetItemTarget())
4321 m_targets.SetItemTarget(NULL);
4322
4323 m_CastItem = NULL;
4324 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
4325 m_castItemEntry = 0;
4326 }
4327}
4328
4329void Spell::TakePower()
4330{
4331 if (m_CastItem || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4332 return;
4333
4334 //Don't take power if the spell is cast while .cheat power is enabled.
4335 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4336 {
4337 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_POWER))
4338 return;
4339 }
4340
4341 Powers powerType = Powers(m_spellInfo->PowerType);
4342 bool hit = true;
4343 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4344 {
4345 if (powerType == POWER_RAGE || powerType == POWER_ENERGY || powerType == POWER_RUNE)
4346 if (ObjectGuid targetGUID = m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID())
4347 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
4348 if (ihit->targetGUID == targetGUID)
4349 {
4350 if (ihit->missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
4351 {
4352 hit = false;
4353 //lower spell cost on fail (by talent aura)
4354 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSpellModOwner())
4355 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_SPELL_COST_REFUND_ON_FAIL, m_powerCost);
4356 }
4357 break;
4358 }
4359 }
4360
4361 if (powerType == POWER_RUNE)
4362 {
4363 TakeRunePower(hit);
4364 return;
4365 }
4366
4367 if (!m_powerCost)
4368 return;
4369
4370 // health as power used
4371 if (powerType == POWER_HEALTH)
4372 {
4373 m_caster->ModifyHealth(-(int32)m_powerCost);
4374 return;
4375 }
4376
4377 if (powerType >= MAX_POWERS)
4378 {
4379 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::TakePower: Unknown power type '%d'", powerType);
4380 return;
4381 }
4382
4383 if (hit)
4384 m_caster->ModifyPower(powerType, -m_powerCost);
4385 else
4386 m_caster->ModifyPower(powerType, -irand(0, m_powerCost/4));
4387
4388 // Set the five second timer
4389 if (powerType == POWER_MANA && m_powerCost > 0)
4390 m_caster->SetLastManaUse(getMSTime());
4391}
4392
4393void Spell::TakeAmmo()
4394{
4395 if (m_attackType == RANGED_ATTACK && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4396 {
4397 Item* pItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(RANGED_ATTACK);
4398
4399 // wands don't have ammo
4400 if (!pItem || pItem->IsBroken() || pItem->GetTemplate()->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_WAND)
4401 return;
4402
4403 if (pItem->GetTemplate()->InventoryType == INVTYPE_THROWN)
4404 {
4405 if (pItem->GetMaxStackCount() == 1)
4406 {
4407 // decrease durability for non-stackable throw weapon
4408 m_caster->ToPlayer()->DurabilityPointLossForEquipSlot(EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED);
4409 }
4410 else
4411 {
4412 // decrease items amount for stackable throw weapon
4413 uint32 count = 1;
4414 m_caster->ToPlayer()->DestroyItemCount(pItem, count, true);
4415 }
4416 }
4417 else if (uint32 ammo = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_AMMO_ID))
4418 m_caster->ToPlayer()->DestroyItemCount(ammo, 1, true);
4419 }
4420}
4421
4422SpellCastResult Spell::CheckRuneCost(uint32 runeCostID)
4423{
4424 if (m_spellInfo->PowerType != POWER_RUNE || !runeCostID)
4425 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4426
4427 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4428 if (!player)
4429 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4430
4431 if (player->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
4432 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4433
4434 SpellRuneCostEntry const* src = sSpellRuneCostStore.LookupEntry(runeCostID);
4435 if (!src)
4436 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4437
4438 if (src->NoRuneCost())
4439 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4440
4441 int32 runeCost[NUM_RUNE_TYPES]; // blood, frost, unholy, death
4442
4443 for (uint32 i = 0; i < RUNE_DEATH; ++i)
4444 {
4445 runeCost[i] = src->RuneCost[i];
4446 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
4447 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_COST, runeCost[i], this);
4448 }
4449
4450 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] = MAX_RUNES; // calculated later
4451
4452 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4453 {
4454 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4455 if ((player->GetRuneCooldown(i) == 0) && (runeCost[rune] > 0))
4456 runeCost[rune]--;
4457 }
4458
4459 for (uint32 i = 0; i < RUNE_DEATH; ++i)
4460 if (runeCost[i] > 0)
4461 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] += runeCost[i];
4462
4463 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > MAX_RUNES)
4464 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_POWER; // not sure if result code is correct
4465
4466 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4467}
4468
4469void Spell::TakeRunePower(bool didHit)
4470{
4471 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || m_caster->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
4472 return;
4473
4474 SpellRuneCostEntry const* runeCostData = sSpellRuneCostStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->RuneCostID);
4475 if (!runeCostData || (runeCostData->NoRuneCost() && runeCostData->NoRunicPowerGain()))
4476 return;
4477
4478 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4479 m_runesState = player->GetRunesState(); // store previous state
4480
4481 int32 runeCost[NUM_RUNE_TYPES]; // blood, frost, unholy, death
4482
4483 for (uint32 i = 0; i < RUNE_DEATH; ++i)
4484 {
4485 runeCost[i] = runeCostData->RuneCost[i];
4486 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
4487 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_COST, runeCost[i], this);
4488 }
4489
4490 // Let's say we use a skill that requires a Frost rune. This is the order:
4491 // - Frost rune
4492 // - Death rune, originally a Frost rune
4493 // - Death rune, any kind
4494 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] = 0; // calculated later
4495 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4496 {
4497 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4498 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && runeCost[rune] > 0)
4499 {
4500 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4501 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4502 runeCost[rune]--;
4503 }
4504 }
4505
4506 // Find a Death rune where the base rune matches the one we need
4507 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] = runeCost[RUNE_BLOOD] + runeCost[RUNE_UNHOLY] + runeCost[RUNE_FROST];
4508 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > 0)
4509 {
4510 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4511 {
4512 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4513 RuneType baseRune = player->GetBaseRune(i);
4514 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && rune == RUNE_DEATH && runeCost[baseRune] > 0)
4515 {
4516 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4517 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4518 runeCost[baseRune]--;
4519 runeCost[rune]--;
4520
4521 // keep Death Rune type if missed
4522 if (didHit)
4523 player->RestoreBaseRune(i);
4524
4525 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] == 0)
4526 break;
4527 }
4528 }
4529 }
4530
4531 // Grab any Death rune
4532 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > 0)
4533 {
4534 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4535 {
4536 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4537 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && rune == RUNE_DEATH)
4538 {
4539 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4540 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4541 runeCost[rune]--;
4542
4543 // keep Death Rune type if missed
4544 if (didHit)
4545 player->RestoreBaseRune(i);
4546
4547 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] == 0)
4548 break;
4549 }
4550 }
4551 }
4552
4553 // you can gain some runic power when use runes
4554 if (didHit)
4555 if (int32 rp = int32(runeCostData->runePowerGain * sWorld->getRate(RATE_POWER_RUNICPOWER_INCOME)))
4556 player->ModifyPower(POWER_RUNIC_POWER, int32(rp));
4557}
4558
4559void Spell::TakeReagents()
4560{
4561 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
4562 return;
4563
4564 ItemTemplate const* castItemTemplate = m_CastItem ? m_CastItem->GetTemplate() : NULL;
4565
4566 // do not take reagents for these item casts
4567 if (castItemTemplate && castItemTemplate->Flags & ITEM_PROTO_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST)
4568 return;
4569
4570 Player* p_caster = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4571 if (p_caster->CanNoReagentCast(m_spellInfo))
4572 return;
4573
4574 for (uint32 x = 0; x < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++x)
4575 {
4576 if (m_spellInfo->Reagent[x] <= 0)
4577 continue;
4578
4579 uint32 itemid = m_spellInfo->Reagent[x];
4580 uint32 itemcount = m_spellInfo->ReagentCount[x];
4581
4582 // if CastItem is also spell reagent
4583 if (castItemTemplate && castItemTemplate->ItemId == itemid)
4584 {
4585 for (int s = 0; s < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++s)
4586 {
4587 // CastItem will be used up and does not count as reagent
4588 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(s);
4589 if (castItemTemplate->Spells[s].SpellCharges < 0 && abs(charges) < 2)
4590 {
4591 ++itemcount;
4592 break;
4593 }
4594 }
4595
4596 m_CastItem = NULL;
4597 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
4598 m_castItemEntry = 0;
4599 }
4600
4601 // if GetItemTarget is also spell reagent
4602 if (m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry() == itemid)
4603 m_targets.SetItemTarget(NULL);
4604
4605 p_caster->DestroyItemCount(itemid, itemcount, true);
4606 }
4607}
4608
4609void Spell::HandleThreatSpells()
4610{
4611 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty())
4612 return;
4613
4614 if (!m_spellInfo->HasInitialAggro())
4615 return;
4616
4617 float threat = 0.0f;
4618 if (SpellThreatEntry const* threatEntry = sSpellMgr->GetSpellThreatEntry(m_spellInfo->Id))
4619 {
4620 if (threatEntry->apPctMod != 0.0f)
4621 threat += threatEntry->apPctMod * m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
4622
4623 threat += threatEntry->flatMod;
4624 }
4625 else if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_NO_INITIAL_THREAT))
4626 threat += m_spellInfo->SpellLevel;
4627
4628 // past this point only multiplicative effects occur
4629 if (threat == 0.0f)
4630 return;
4631
4632 // since 2.0.1 threat from positive effects also is distributed among all targets, so the overall caused threat is at most the defined bonus
4633 threat /= m_UniqueTargetInfo.size();
4634
4635 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
4636 {
4637 float threatToAdd = threat;
4638 if (ihit->missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
4639 threatToAdd = 0.0f;
4640
4641 Unit* target = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
4642 if (!target)
4643 continue;
4644
4645 // positive spells distribute threat among all units that are in combat with target, like healing
4646 if (m_spellInfo->_IsPositiveSpell())
4647 target->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(m_caster, threatToAdd, m_spellInfo);
4648 // for negative spells threat gets distributed among affected targets
4649 else
4650 {
4651 if (!target->CanHaveThreatList())
4652 continue;
4653
4654 target->AddThreat(m_caster, threatToAdd, m_spellInfo->GetSchoolMask(), m_spellInfo);
4655 }
4656 }
4657 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u, added an additional %f threat for %s %u target(s)", m_spellInfo->Id, threat, m_spellInfo->_IsPositiveSpell() ? "assisting" : "harming", uint32(m_UniqueTargetInfo.size()));
4658}
4659
4660void Spell::HandleEffects(Unit* pUnitTarget, Item* pItemTarget, GameObject* pGOTarget, uint32 i, SpellEffectHandleMode mode)
4661{
4662 effectHandleMode = mode;
4663 unitTarget = pUnitTarget;
4664 itemTarget = pItemTarget;
4665 gameObjTarget = pGOTarget;
4666 destTarget = &m_destTargets[i]._position;
4667
4668 uint8 eff = m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect;
4669
4670 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell: %u Effect : %u", m_spellInfo->Id, eff);
4671
4672 // we do not need DamageMultiplier here.
4673 damage = CalculateDamage(i, NULL);
4674
4675 bool preventDefault = CallScriptEffectHandlers((SpellEffIndex)i, mode);
4676
4677 if (!preventDefault && eff < TOTAL_SPELL_EFFECTS)
4678 {
4679 (this->*SpellEffects[eff])((SpellEffIndex)i);
4680 }
4681}
4682
4683SpellCastResult Spell::CheckCast(bool strict)
4684{
4685 // check death state
4686 if (!m_caster->IsAlive() && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE) && !(m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_DEAD) || (IsTriggered() && !m_triggeredByAuraSpell)))
4687 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_DEAD;
4688
4689 // check cooldowns to prevent cheating
4690 if (!m_spellInfo->IsPassive())
4691 {
4692 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4693 {
4694 //can cast triggered (by aura only?) spells while have this flag
4695 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURASTATE) && m_caster->ToPlayer()->HasFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_ALLOW_ONLY_ABILITY))
4696 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS;
4697
4698 // check if we are using a potion in combat for the 2nd+ time. Cooldown is added only after caster gets out of combat
4699 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetLastPotionId() && m_CastItem && (m_CastItem->IsPotion() || m_spellInfo->IsCooldownStartedOnEvent()))
4700 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4701 }
4702
4703 if (!m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->IsReady(m_spellInfo, m_castItemEntry, IsIgnoringCooldowns()))
4704 {
4705 if (m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4706 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4707 else
4708 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4709 }
4710 }
4711
4712 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_IS_CHEAT_SPELL) && !m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_ALLOW_CHEAT_SPELLS))
4713 {
4714 m_customError = SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_GM_ONLY;
4715 return SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR;
4716 }
4717
4718 // Check global cooldown
4719 if (strict && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_GCD) && HasGlobalCooldown())
4720 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4721
4722 // only triggered spells can be processed an ended battleground
4723 if (!IsTriggered() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4724 if (Battleground* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
4725 if (bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_LEAVE)
4726 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4727
4728 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapManager()->isLineOfSightCalcEnabled())
4729 {
4730 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_OUTDOORS_ONLY) &&
4731 !m_caster->GetMap()->IsOutdoors(m_caster->GetPositionX(), m_caster->GetPositionY(), m_caster->GetPositionZ()))
4732 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_OUTDOORS;
4733
4734 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_INDOORS_ONLY) &&
4735 m_caster->GetMap()->IsOutdoors(m_caster->GetPositionX(), m_caster->GetPositionY(), m_caster->GetPositionZ()))
4736 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_INDOORS;
4737 }
4738
4739 // only check at first call, Stealth auras are already removed at second call
4740 // for now, ignore triggered spells
4741 if (strict && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SHAPESHIFT))
4742 {
4743 bool checkForm = true;
4744 // Ignore form req aura
4745 Unit::AuraEffectList const& ignore = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_IGNORE_SHAPESHIFT);
4746 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = ignore.begin(); i != ignore.end(); ++i)
4747 {
4748 if (!(*i)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
4749 continue;
4750 checkForm = false;
4751 break;
4752 }
4753 if (checkForm)
4754 {
4755 // Cannot be used in this stance/form
4756 SpellCastResult shapeError = m_spellInfo->CheckShapeshift(m_caster->GetShapeshiftForm());
4757 if (shapeError != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4758 return shapeError;
4759
4760 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_ONLY_STEALTHED) && !(m_caster->HasStealthAura()))
4761 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_STEALTHED;
4762 }
4763 }
4764
4765 Unit::AuraEffectList const& blockSpells = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_BLOCK_SPELL_FAMILY);
4766 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator blockItr = blockSpells.begin(); blockItr != blockSpells.end(); ++blockItr)
4767 if (uint32((*blockItr)->GetMiscValue()) == m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
4768 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_UNAVAILABLE;
4769
4770 bool reqCombat = true;
4771 Unit::AuraEffectList const& stateAuras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_IGNORE_AURASTATE);
4772 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator j = stateAuras.begin(); j != stateAuras.end(); ++j)
4773 {
4774 if ((*j)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
4775 {
4776 m_needComboPoints = false;
4777 if ((*j)->GetMiscValue() == 1)
4778 {
4779 reqCombat=false;
4780 break;
4781 }
4782 }
4783 }
4784
4785 // caster state requirements
4786 // not for triggered spells (needed by execute)
4787 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURASTATE))
4788 {
4789 if (m_spellInfo->CasterAuraState && !m_caster->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(m_spellInfo->CasterAuraState), m_spellInfo, m_caster))
4790 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4791 if (m_spellInfo->CasterAuraStateNot && m_caster->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(m_spellInfo->CasterAuraStateNot), m_spellInfo, m_caster))
4792 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4793
4794 // Note: spell 62473 requres casterAuraSpell = triggering spell
4795 if (m_spellInfo->CasterAuraSpell && !m_caster->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(m_spellInfo->CasterAuraSpell, m_caster)))
4796 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4797 if (m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell && m_caster->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell, m_caster)))
4798 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4799
4800 if (reqCombat && m_caster->IsInCombat() && !m_spellInfo->CanBeUsedInCombat())
4801 return SPELL_FAILED_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
4802 }
4803
4804 // cancel autorepeat spells if cast start when moving
4805 // (not wand currently autorepeat cast delayed to moving stop anyway in spell update code)
4806 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->ToPlayer()->isMoving())
4807 {
4808 // skip stuck spell to allow use it in falling case and apply spell limitations at movement
4809 if ((!m_caster->HasUnitMovementFlag(MOVEMENTFLAG_FALLING_FAR) || m_spellInfo->Effects[0].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_STUCK) &&
4810 (IsAutoRepeat() || (m_spellInfo->AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED) != 0))
4811 return SPELL_FAILED_MOVING;
4812 }
4813
4814 // Check vehicle flags
4815 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_MOUNTED_OR_ON_VEHICLE))
4816 {
4817 SpellCastResult vehicleCheck = m_spellInfo->CheckVehicle(m_caster);
4818 if (vehicleCheck != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4819 return vehicleCheck;
4820 }
4821
4822 // check spell cast conditions from database
4823 {
