4824 ConditionSourceInfo condInfo = ConditionSourceInfo(m_caster, m_targets.GetObjectTarget());
4825 if (!sConditionMgr->IsObjectMeetingNotGroupedConditions(CONDITION_SOURCE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, condInfo))
4826 {
4827 // mLastFailedCondition can be NULL if there was an error processing the condition in Condition::Meets (i.e. wrong data for ConditionTarget or others)
4828 if (condInfo.mLastFailedCondition && condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType)
4829 {
4830 if (condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType == SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR)
4831 m_customError = SpellCustomErrors(condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorTextId);
4832 return SpellCastResult(condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType);
4833 }
4834 if (!condInfo.mLastFailedCondition || !condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ConditionTarget)
4835 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4836 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
4837 }
4838 }
4839
4840 // Don't check explicit target for passive spells (workaround) (check should be skipped only for learn case)
4841 // those spells may have incorrect target entries or not filled at all (for example 15332)
4842 // such spells when learned are not targeting anyone using targeting system, they should apply directly to caster instead
4843 // also, such casts shouldn't be sent to client
4844 if (!(m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE) && (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget() || m_targets.GetUnitTarget() == m_caster)))
4845 {
4846 // Check explicit target for m_originalCaster - todo: get rid of such workarounds
4847 SpellCastResult castResult = m_spellInfo->CheckExplicitTarget(m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster : m_caster, m_targets.GetObjectTarget(), m_targets.GetItemTarget());
4848 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4849 return castResult;
4850 }
4851
4852 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
4853 {
4854 SpellCastResult castResult = m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, target, false);
4855 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4856 return castResult;
4857
4858 if (target != m_caster)
4859 {
4860 // Must be behind the target
4861 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_REQ_CASTER_BEHIND_TARGET) && target->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), m_caster))
4862 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_BEHIND;
4863
4864 // Target must be facing you
4865 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_REQ_TARGET_FACING_CASTER) && !target->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), m_caster))
4866 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_INFRONT;
4867
4868 if (m_caster->GetEntry() != WORLD_TRIGGER) // Ignore LOS for gameobjects casts (wrongly cast by a trigger)
4869 {
4870 WorldObject* losTarget = m_caster;
4871 if (IsTriggered() && m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4872 if (DynamicObject* dynObj = m_caster->GetDynObject(m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id))
4873 losTarget = dynObj;
4874
4875 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) && !DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS) && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(losTarget))
4876 return SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
4877 }
4878 }
4879 }
4880
4881 // Check for line of sight for spells with dest
4882 if (m_targets.HasDst())
4883 {
4884 float x, y, z;
4885 m_targets.GetDstPos()->GetPosition(x, y, z);
4886
4887 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) && !DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS) && !m_caster->IsWithinLOS(x, y, z))
4888 return SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
4889 }
4890
4891 // check pet presence
4892 for (int j = 0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
4893 {
4894 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_PET)
4895 {
4896 if (!m_caster->GetGuardianPet())
4897 {
4898 if (m_triggeredByAuraSpell) // not report pet not existence for triggered spells
4899 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4900 else
4901 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
4902 }
4903 break;
4904 }
4905 }
4906
4907 // Spell cast only in battleground
4908 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_BATTLEGROUND) && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4909 if (!m_caster->ToPlayer()->InBattleground())
4910 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_BATTLEGROUNDS;
4911
4912 // do not allow spells to be cast in arenas
4913 // - with greater than 10 min CD without SPELL_ATTR4_USABLE_IN_ARENA flag
4914 // - with SPELL_ATTR4_NOT_USABLE_IN_ARENA flag
4915 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_NOT_USABLE_IN_ARENA) ||
4916 (m_spellInfo->GetRecoveryTime() > 10 * MINUTE * IN_MILLISECONDS && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_USABLE_IN_ARENA)))
4917 if (MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(m_caster->GetMapId()))
4918 if (mapEntry->IsBattleArena())
4919 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_ARENA;
4920
4921 // zone check
4922 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT || !m_caster->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
4923 {
4924 uint32 zone, area;
4925 m_caster->GetZoneAndAreaId(zone, area);
4926
4927 SpellCastResult locRes = m_spellInfo->CheckLocation(m_caster->GetMapId(), zone, area, m_caster->ToPlayer());
4928 if (locRes != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4929 return locRes;
4930 }
4931
4932 // not let players cast spells at mount (and let do it to creatures)
4933 if (m_caster->IsMounted() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_MOUNTED_OR_ON_VEHICLE) &&
4934 !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_MOUNTED))
4935 {
4936 if (m_caster->IsInFlight())
4937 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_ON_TAXI;
4938 else
4939 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_MOUNTED;
4940 }
4941
4942 // check spell focus object
4943 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
4944 {
4945 focusObject = SearchSpellFocus();
4946 if (!focusObject)
4947 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_SPELL_FOCUS;
4948 }
4949
4950 SpellCastResult castResult = SPELL_CAST_OK;
4951
4952 // always (except passive spells) check items (only player related checks)
4953 if (!m_spellInfo->IsPassive())
4954 {
4955 castResult = CheckItems();
4956 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4957 return castResult;
4958 }
4959
4960 // Triggered spells also have range check
4961 /// @todo determine if there is some flag to enable/disable the check
4962 castResult = CheckRange(strict);
4963 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4964 return castResult;
4965
4966 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
4967 {
4968 castResult = CheckPower();
4969 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4970 return castResult;
4971 }
4972
4973 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURAS))
4974 {
4975 castResult = CheckCasterAuras();
4976 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4977 return castResult;
4978 }
4979
4980 // script hook
4981 castResult = CallScriptCheckCastHandlers();
4982 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4983 return castResult;
4984
4985 bool hasDispellableAura = false;
4986 bool hasNonDispelEffect = false;
4987 uint32 dispelMask = 0;
4988 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
4989 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_DISPEL)
4990 {
4991 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsTargetingArea() || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_MELEE_COMBAT_START))
4992 {
4993 hasDispellableAura = true;
4994 break;
4995 }
4996
4997 dispelMask |= SpellInfo::GetDispelMask(DispelType(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue));
4998 }
4999 else if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsEffect())
5000 {
5001 hasNonDispelEffect = true;
5002 break;
5003 }
5004
5005 if (!hasNonDispelEffect && !hasDispellableAura && dispelMask && !IsTriggered())
5006 {
5007 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5008 {
5009 DispelChargesList dispelList;
5010 target->GetDispellableAuraList(m_caster, dispelMask, dispelList);
5011 if (dispelList.empty())
5012 return SPELL_FAILED_NOTHING_TO_DISPEL;
5013 }
5014 }
5015
5016 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
5017 {
5018 // for effects of spells that have only one target
5019 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect)
5020 {
5021 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
5022 {
5023 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5024 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5025
5026 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_PET)
5027 break;
5028
5029 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5030
5031 if (!pet)
5032 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5033
5034 SpellInfo const* learn_spellproto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TriggerSpell);
5035
5036 if (!learn_spellproto)
5037 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5038
5039 if (m_spellInfo->SpellLevel > pet->getLevel())
5040 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
5041
5042 break;
5043 }
5044 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_PET_SPELL:
5045 {
5046 // check target only for unit target case
5047 if (Unit* unit = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5048 {
5049 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5050 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5051
5052 Pet* pet = unit->ToPet();
5053 if (!pet || pet->GetOwner() != m_caster)
5054 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5055
5056 SpellInfo const* learn_spellproto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TriggerSpell);
5057
5058 if (!learn_spellproto)
5059 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5060
5061 if (m_spellInfo->SpellLevel > pet->getLevel())
5062 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
5063 }
5064 break;
5065 }
5066 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_GLYPH:
5067 {
5068 uint32 glyphId = m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue;
5069 if (GlyphPropertiesEntry const* gp = sGlyphPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(glyphId))
5070 if (m_caster->HasAura(gp->SpellId))
5071 return SPELL_FAILED_UNIQUE_GLYPH;
5072 break;
5073 }
5074 case SPELL_EFFECT_FEED_PET:
5075 {
5076 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5077 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5078
5079 Item* foodItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
5080 if (!foodItem)
5081 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5082
5083 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5084
5085 if (!pet)
5086 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5087
5088 if (!pet->HaveInDiet(foodItem->GetTemplate()))
5089 return SPELL_FAILED_WRONG_PET_FOOD;
5090
5091 if (!pet->GetCurrentFoodBenefitLevel(foodItem->GetTemplate()->ItemLevel))
5092 return SPELL_FAILED_FOOD_LOWLEVEL;
5093
5094 if (m_caster->IsInCombat() || pet->IsInCombat())
5095 return SPELL_FAILED_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
5096
5097 break;
5098 }
5099 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
5100 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
5101 {
5102 // Can be area effect, Check only for players and not check if target - caster (spell can have multiply drain/burn effects)
5103 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5104 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5105 if (target != m_caster && target->getPowerType() != Powers(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue))
5106 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5107 break;
5108 }
5109 case SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE:
5110 {
5111 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR)
5112 {
5113 // Warbringer - can't be handled in proc system - should be done before checkcast root check and charge effect process
5114 if (strict && m_caster->IsScriptOverriden(m_spellInfo, 6953))
5115 m_caster->RemoveMovementImpairingAuras();
5116 }
5117
5118 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ROOT))
5119 return SPELL_FAILED_ROOTED;
5120
5121 if (GetSpellInfo()->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
5122 {
5123 Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5124 if (!target)
5125 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5126
5127 float objSize = target->GetObjectSize();
5128 float range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true, m_caster, this) * 1.5f + objSize; // can't be overly strict
5129
5130 m_preGeneratedPath.SetPathLengthLimit(range);
5131 // first try with raycast, if it fails fall back to normal path
5132 float targetObjectSize = std::min(target->GetObjectSize(), 4.0f);
5133 bool result = m_preGeneratedPath.CalculatePath(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ() + targetObjectSize, false, true);
5134 if (m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & PATHFIND_SHORT)
5135 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5136 else if (!result || m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & (PATHFIND_NOPATH | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE))
5137 {
5138 result = m_preGeneratedPath.CalculatePath(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ() + targetObjectSize, false, false);
5139 if (m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & PATHFIND_SHORT)
5140 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5141 else if (!result || m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & (PATHFIND_NOPATH | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE))
5142 return SPELL_FAILED_NOPATH;
5143 }
5144
5145 m_preGeneratedPath.ReducePathLenghtByDist(objSize); // move back
5146 }
5147 break;
5148 }
5149 case SPELL_EFFECT_SKINNING:
5150 {
5151 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || !m_targets.GetUnitTarget() || m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT)
5152 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5153
5154 if (!(m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS) & UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
5155 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_UNSKINNABLE;
5156
5157 Creature* creature = m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->ToCreature();
5158 if (!creature->IsCritter() && !creature->loot.isLooted())
5159 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_LOOTED;
5160
5161 uint32 skill = creature->GetCreatureTemplate()->GetRequiredLootSkill();
5162
5163 int32 skillValue = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSkillValue(skill);
5164 int32 TargetLevel = m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->getLevel();
5165 int32 ReqValue = (skillValue < 100 ? (TargetLevel-10) * 10 : TargetLevel * 5);
5166 if (ReqValue > skillValue)
5167 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
5168
5169 // chance for fail at orange skinning attempt
5170 if ((m_selfContainer && (*m_selfContainer) == this) &&
5171 skillValue < sWorld->GetConfigMaxSkillValue() &&
5172 (ReqValue < 0 ? 0 : ReqValue) > irand(skillValue - 25, skillValue + 37))
5173 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5174
5175 break;
5176 }
5177 case SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK:
5178 {
5179 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET &&
5180 m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET)
5181 break;
5182
5183 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER // only players can open locks, gather etc.
5184 // we need a go target in case of TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET
5185 || (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET && !m_targets.GetGOTarget()))
5186 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5187
5188 Item* pTempItem = NULL;
5189 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
5190 {
5191 if (TradeData* pTrade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData())
5192 pTempItem = pTrade->GetTraderData()->GetItem(TradeSlots(m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID().GetRawValue())); // at this point item target guid contains the trade slot
5193 }
5194 else if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
5195 pTempItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetItemByGuid(m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID());
5196
5197 // we need a go target, or an openable item target in case of TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET
5198 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET &&
5199 !m_targets.GetGOTarget() &&
5200 (!pTempItem || !pTempItem->GetTemplate()->LockID || !pTempItem->IsLocked()))
5201 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5202
5203 if (m_spellInfo->Id != 1842 || (m_targets.GetGOTarget() &&
5204 m_targets.GetGOTarget()->GetGOInfo()->type != GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP))
5205 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->InBattleground() && // In Battleground players can use only flags and banners
5206 !m_caster->ToPlayer()->CanUseBattlegroundObject(m_targets.GetGOTarget()))
5207 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5208
5209 // get the lock entry
5210 uint32 lockId = 0;
5211 if (GameObject* go = m_targets.GetGOTarget())
5212 {
5213 lockId = go->GetGOInfo()->GetLockId();
5214 if (!lockId)
5215 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5216 }
5217 else if (Item* itm = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
5218 lockId = itm->GetTemplate()->LockID;
5219
5220 SkillType skillId = SKILL_NONE;
5221 int32 reqSkillValue = 0;
5222 int32 skillValue = 0;
5223
5224 // check lock compatibility
5225 SpellCastResult res = CanOpenLock(i, lockId, skillId, reqSkillValue, skillValue);
5226 if (res != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5227 return res;
5228
5229 // chance for fail at orange mining/herb/LockPicking gathering attempt
5230 // second check prevent fail at rechecks
5231 if (skillId != SKILL_NONE && (!m_selfContainer || ((*m_selfContainer) != this)))
5232 {
5233 bool canFailAtMax = skillId != SKILL_HERBALISM && skillId != SKILL_MINING;
5234
5235 // chance for failure in orange gather / lockpick (gathering skill can't fail at maxskill)
5236 if ((canFailAtMax || skillValue < sWorld->GetConfigMaxSkillValue()) && reqSkillValue > irand(skillValue - 25, skillValue + 37))
5237 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5238 }
5239 break;
5240 }
5241 case SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_PET:
5242 {
5243 Creature* pet = m_caster->GetGuardianPet();
5244
5245 if (pet && pet->IsAlive())
5246 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5247
5248 break;
5249 }
5250 // This is generic summon effect
5251 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON:
5252 {
5253 SummonPropertiesEntry const* SummonProperties = sSummonPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValueB);
5254 if (!SummonProperties)
5255 break;
5256 switch (SummonProperties->Category)
5257 {
5258 case SUMMON_CATEGORY_PET:
5259 if (m_caster->GetPetGUID())
5260 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5261 // intentional missing break, check both GetPetGUID() and GetCharmGUID for SUMMON_CATEGORY_PET
5262 case SUMMON_CATEGORY_PUPPET:
5263 if (m_caster->GetCharmGUID())
5264 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5265 break;
5266 }
5267 break;
5268 }
5269 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_TAMED_PET:
5270 {
5271 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5272 {
5273 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5274 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5275 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetPetGUID())
5276 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5277 }
5278 break;
5279 }
5280 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET:
5281 {
5282 if (m_caster->GetPetGUID()) //let warlock do a replacement summon
5283 {
5284 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->getClass() == CLASS_WARLOCK)
5285 {
5286 if (strict) //starting cast, trigger pet stun (cast by pet so it doesn't attack player)
5287 if (Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet())
5288 pet->CastSpell(pet, 32752, true, NULL, NULL, pet->GetGUID());
5289 }
5290 else
5291 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5292 }
5293
5294 if (m_caster->GetCharmGUID())
5295 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5296 break;
5297 }
5298 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER:
5299 {
5300 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5301 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5302 if (!m_caster->GetTarget())
5303 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5304
5305 Player* target = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTarget());
5306 if (!target || m_caster->ToPlayer() == target || (!target->IsInSameRaidWith(m_caster->ToPlayer()) && m_spellInfo->Id != 48955)) // refer-a-friend spell
5307 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5308
5309 // check if our map is dungeon
5310 MapEntry const* map = sMapStore.LookupEntry(m_caster->GetMapId());
5311 if (map->IsDungeon())
5312 {
5313 uint32 mapId = m_caster->GetMap()->GetId();
5314 Difficulty difficulty = m_caster->GetMap()->GetDifficulty();
5315 if (map->IsRaid())
5316 if (InstancePlayerBind* targetBind = target->GetBoundInstance(mapId, difficulty))
5317 if (InstancePlayerBind* casterBind = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBoundInstance(mapId, difficulty))
5318 if (targetBind->perm && targetBind->save != casterBind->save)
5319 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_LOCKED_TO_RAID_INSTANCE;
5320
5321 InstanceTemplate const* instance = sObjectMgr->GetInstanceTemplate(mapId);
5322 if (!instance)
5323 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_IN_INSTANCE;
5324 if (!target->Satisfy(sObjectMgr->GetAccessRequirement(mapId, difficulty), mapId))
5325 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5326 }
5327 break;
5328 }
5329 // RETURN HERE
5330 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND:
5331 {
5332 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5333 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5334
5335 Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer();
5336 //
5337 if (!(playerCaster->GetTarget()))
5338 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5339
5340 Player* target = playerCaster->GetSelectedPlayer();
5341
5342 if (!target ||
5343 !(target->GetSession()->GetRecruiterId() == playerCaster->GetSession()->GetAccountId() || target->GetSession()->GetAccountId() == playerCaster->GetSession()->GetRecruiterId()))
5344 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5345
5346 break;
5347 }
5348 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEAP:
5349 case SPELL_EFFECT_TELEPORT_UNITS_FACE_CASTER:
5350 {
5351 //Do not allow to cast it before BG starts.
5352 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5353 if (Battleground const* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
5354 if (bg->GetStatus() != STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
5355 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5356 break;
5357 }
5358 case SPELL_EFFECT_STEAL_BENEFICIAL_BUFF:
5359 {
5360 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget() == m_caster)
5361 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5362 break;
5363 }
5364 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEAP_BACK:
5365 {
5366 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ROOT))
5367 {
5368 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5369 return SPELL_FAILED_ROOTED;
5370 else
5371 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5372 }
5373 break;
5374 }
5375 case SPELL_EFFECT_TALENT_SPEC_SELECT:
5376 // can't change during already started arena/battleground
5377 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5378 if (Battleground const* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
5379 if (bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
5380 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_BATTLEGROUND;
5381 break;
5382 default:
5383 break;
5384 }
5385 }
5386
5387 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
5388 {
5389 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
5390 {
5391 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
5392 {
5393 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5394 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5395
5396 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5397 if (!pet)
5398 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5399
5400 if (pet->GetCharmerGUID())
5401 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5402 break;
5403 }
5404 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
5405 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
5406 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
5407 {
5408 if (m_caster->GetCharmerGUID())
5409 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5410
5411 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM
5412 || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS)
5413 {
5414 if (m_caster->GetPetGUID())
5415 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5416
5417 if (m_caster->GetCharmGUID())
5418 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5419 }
5420
5421 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5422 {
5423 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->IsVehicle())
5424 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5425
5426 if (target->IsMounted())
5427 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_CHARMED;
5428
5429 if (target->GetCharmerGUID())
5430 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5431
5432 if (target->GetOwner() && target->GetOwner()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5433 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER_CONTROLLED;
5434
5435 int32 value = CalculateDamage(i, target);
5436 if (value && int32(target->getLevel()) > value)
5437 return SPELL_FAILED_HIGHLEVEL;
5438 }
5439
5440 break;
5441 }
5442 case SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED:
5443 {
5444 if (m_caster->IsInWater())
5445 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_ABOVEWATER;
5446
5447 // Ignore map check if spell have AreaId. AreaId already checked and this prevent special mount spells
5448 bool allowMount = !m_caster->GetMap()->IsDungeon() || m_caster->GetMap()->IsBattlegroundOrArena();
5449 InstanceTemplate const* it = sObjectMgr->GetInstanceTemplate(m_caster->GetMapId());
5450 if (it)
5451 allowMount = it->AllowMount;
5452 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !allowMount && !m_spellInfo->AreaGroupId)
5453 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_MOUNTS_ALLOWED;
5454
5455 if (m_caster->IsInDisallowedMountForm())
5456 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
5457
5458 break;
5459 }
5460 case SPELL_AURA_RANGED_ATTACK_POWER_ATTACKER_BONUS:
5461 {
5462 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5463 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5464
5465 // can be cast at non-friendly unit or own pet/charm
5466 if (m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(m_targets.GetUnitTarget()))
5467 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_FRIENDLY;
5468
5469 break;
5470 }
5471 case SPELL_AURA_FLY:
5472 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED:
5473 {
5474 // not allow cast fly spells if not have req. skills (all spells is self target)
5475 // allow always ghost flight spells
5476 if (m_originalCaster && m_originalCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_originalCaster->IsAlive())
5477 {
5478 Battlefield* Bf = sBattlefieldMgr->GetBattlefieldToZoneId(m_originalCaster->GetZoneId());
5479 if (AreaTableEntry const* area = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(m_originalCaster->GetAreaId()))
5480 if (area->flags & AREA_FLAG_NO_FLY_ZONE || (Bf && !Bf->CanFlyIn()))
5481 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_NOT_HERE;
5482 }
5483 break;
5484 }
5485 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
5486 {
5487 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsTargetingArea())
5488 break;
5489
5490 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5491 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5492
5493 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || m_CastItem)
5494 break;
5495
5496 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->getPowerType() != POWER_MANA)
5497 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5498
5499 break;
5500 }
5501 default:
5502 break;
5503 }
5504 }
5505
5506 // check trade slot case (last, for allow catch any another cast problems)
5507 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
5508 {
5509 if (m_CastItem)
5510 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_ENCHANT_TRADE_WINDOW;
5511
5512 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5513 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADING;
5514
5515 TradeData* my_trade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData();
5516
5517 if (!my_trade)
5518 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADING;
5519
5520 // Item target guid contains trade slot until m_targets.UpdateTradeSlotItem() is called
5521 TradeSlots slot = TradeSlots(m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID().GetRawValue());
5522 if (slot != TRADE_SLOT_NONTRADED)
5523 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5524
5525 if (!IsTriggered())
5526 if (my_trade->GetSpell())
5527 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_ALREADY_ENCHANTED;
5528 }
5529
5530 // check if caster has at least 1 combo point for spells that require combo points
5531 if (m_needComboPoints)
5532 if (Player* plrCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
5533 if (!plrCaster->GetComboPoints())
5534 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_COMBO_POINTS;
5535
5536 // all ok
5537 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5538}
5539
5540SpellCastResult Spell::CheckPetCast(Unit* target)
5541{
5542 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS)) //prevent spellcast interruption by another spellcast
5543 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS;
5544
5545 // dead owner (pets still alive when owners ressed?)
5546 if (Unit* owner = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner())
5547 if (!owner->IsAlive() && !owner->IsGhouled())
5548 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_DEAD;
5549
5550 if (!target && m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5551 target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5552
5553 if (m_spellInfo->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
5554 {
5555 if (!target)
5556 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5557 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(target);
5558 }
5559
5560 // cooldown
5561 if (Creature* creatureCaster = m_caster->ToCreature())
5562 if (!creatureCaster->GetSpellHistory()->IsReady(m_spellInfo))
5563 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5564
5565 // Check if spell is affected by GCD
5566 if (m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryCategory > 0)
5567 if (m_caster->GetCharmInfo() && m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HasGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo))
5568 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5569
5570 return CheckCast(true);
5571}
5572
5573SpellCastResult Spell::CheckCasterAuras() const
5574{
5575 // spells totally immuned to caster auras (wsg flag drop, give marks etc)
5576 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_CASTER_AURAS))
5577 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5578
5579 uint8 school_immune = 0;
5580 uint32 mechanic_immune = 0;
5581 uint32 dispel_immune = 0;
5582
5583 // Check if the spell grants school or mechanic immunity.
5584 // We use bitmasks so the loop is done only once and not on every aura check below.
5585 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY))
5586 {
5587 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
5588 {
5589 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_IMMUNITY)
5590 school_immune |= uint32(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue);
5591 else if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY)
5592 mechanic_immune |= 1 << uint32(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue);
5593 else if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_DISPEL_IMMUNITY)
5594 dispel_immune |= SpellInfo::GetDispelMask(DispelType(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue));
5595 }
5596 // immune movement impairment and loss of control
5597 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 42292 || m_spellInfo->Id == 59752 || m_spellInfo->Id == 19574)
5598 mechanic_immune = IMMUNE_TO_MOVEMENT_IMPAIRMENT_AND_LOSS_CONTROL_MASK;
5599 }
5600
5601 bool usableInStun = m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_STUNNED);
5602
5603 // Glyph of Pain Suppression
5604 // there is no other way to handle it
5605 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 33206 && !m_caster->HasAura(63248))
5606 usableInStun = false;
5607
5608 // Check whether the cast should be prevented by any state you might have.
5609 SpellCastResult prevented_reason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5610 // Have to check if there is a stun aura. Otherwise will have problems with ghost aura apply while logging out
5611 uint32 unitflag = m_caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS); // Get unit state
5612 if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED)
5613 {
5614 // spell is usable while stunned, check if caster has only mechanic stun auras, another stun types must prevent cast spell
5615 if (usableInStun)
5616 {
5617 bool foundNotStun = false;
5618 Unit::AuraEffectList const& stunAuras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN);
5619 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = stunAuras.begin(); i != stunAuras.end(); ++i)
5620 {
5621 if ((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() && !((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & (1<<MECHANIC_STUN)))
5622 {
5623 foundNotStun = true;
5624 break;
5625 }
5626 }
5627 if (foundNotStun && m_spellInfo->Id != 22812)
5628 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5629 }
5630 else
5631 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5632 }
5633 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_CONFUSED && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_CONFUSED))
5634 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_CONFUSED;
5635 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_FLEEING && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_FEARED))
5636 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_FLEEING;
5637 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED && m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
5638 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_SILENCED;
5639 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED && m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_PACIFY)
5640 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_PACIFIED;
5641
5642 // Attr must make flag drop spell totally immune from all effects
5643 if (prevented_reason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5644 {
5645 if (school_immune || mechanic_immune || dispel_immune)
5646 {
5647 //Checking auras is needed now, because you are prevented by some state but the spell grants immunity.
5648 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = m_caster->GetAppliedAuras();
5649 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
5650 {
5651 Aura const* aura = itr->second->GetBase();
5652 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
5653 if (auraInfo->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & mechanic_immune)
5654 continue;
5655 if (auraInfo->GetSchoolMask() & school_immune && !auraInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE))
5656 continue;
5657 if (auraInfo->GetDispelMask() & dispel_immune)
5658 continue;
5659
5660 //Make a second check for spell failed so the right SPELL_FAILED message is returned.
5661 //That is needed when your casting is prevented by multiple states and you are only immune to some of them.
5662 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
5663 {
5664 if (AuraEffect* part = aura->GetEffect(i))
5665 {
5666 switch (part->GetAuraType())
5667 {
5668 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN:
5669 if (!usableInStun || !(auraInfo->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & (1<<MECHANIC_STUN)))
5670 return SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5671 break;
5672 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE:
5673 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_CONFUSED))
5674 return SPELL_FAILED_CONFUSED;
5675 break;
5676 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_FEAR:
5677 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_FEARED))
5678 return SPELL_FAILED_FLEEING;
5679 break;
5680 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
5681 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY:
5682 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
5683 if (m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_PACIFY)
5684 return SPELL_FAILED_PACIFIED;
5685 else if (m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
5686 return SPELL_FAILED_SILENCED;
5687 break;
5688 default: break;
5689 }
5690 }
5691 }
5692 }
5693 }
5694 // You are prevented from casting and the spell cast does not grant immunity. Return a failed error.
5695 else
5696 return prevented_reason;
5697 }
5698 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5699}
5700
5701bool Spell::CanAutoCast(Unit* target)
5702{
5703 ObjectGuid targetguid = target->GetGUID();
5704
5705 for (uint32 j = 0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
5706 {
5707 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
5708 {
5709 if (m_spellInfo->StackAmount <= 1)
5710 {
5711 if (target->HasAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, j))
5712 return false;
5713 }
5714 else
5715 {
5716 if (AuraEffect* aureff = target->GetAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, j))
5717 if (aureff->GetBase()->GetStackAmount() >= m_spellInfo->StackAmount)
5718 return false;
5719 }
5720 }
5721 else if (m_spellInfo->Effects[j].IsAreaAuraEffect())
5722 {
5723 if (target->HasAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, j))
5724 return false;
5725 }
5726 }
5727
5728 SpellCastResult result = CheckPetCast(target);
5729
5730 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK || result == SPELL_FAILED_UNIT_NOT_INFRONT)
5731 {
5732 SelectSpellTargets();
5733 //check if among target units, our WANTED target is as well (->only self cast spells return false)
5734 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
5735 if (ihit->targetGUID == targetguid)
5736 return true;
5737 }
5738 return false; //target invalid
5739}
5740
5741SpellCastResult Spell::CheckRange(bool strict)
5742{
5743 // Don't check for instant cast spells
5744 if (!strict && m_casttime == 0)
5745 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5746
5747 uint32 range_type = 0;
5748
5749 if (m_spellInfo->RangeEntry)
5750 {
5751 // check needed by 68766 51693 - both spells are cast on enemies and have 0 max range
5752 // these are triggered by other spells - possibly we should omit range check in that case?
5753 if (m_spellInfo->RangeEntry->ID == 1)
5754 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5755
5756 range_type = m_spellInfo->RangeEntry->type;
5757 }
5758
5759 Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5760 float max_range = m_caster->GetSpellMaxRangeForTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
5761 float min_range = m_caster->GetSpellMinRangeForTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
5762
5763 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
5764 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RANGE, max_range, this);
5765
5766 if (target && target != m_caster)
5767 {
5768 if (range_type == SPELL_RANGE_MELEE)
5769 {
5770 // Because of lag, we can not check too strictly here.
5771 if (!m_caster->IsWithinMeleeRange(target, max_range))
5772 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5773 }
5774 else if (!m_caster->IsWithinCombatRange(target, max_range))
5775 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT; //0x5A;
5776
5777 if (range_type == SPELL_RANGE_RANGED)
5778 {
5779 if (m_caster->IsWithinMeleeRange(target))
5780 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5781 }
5782 else if (min_range && m_caster->IsWithinCombatRange(target, min_range)) // skip this check if min_range = 0
5783 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5784
5785 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER &&
5786 (m_spellInfo->FacingCasterFlags & SPELL_FACING_FLAG_INFRONT) && !m_caster->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), target))
5787 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_UNIT_NOT_INFRONT : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5788 }
5789
5790 if (m_targets.HasDst() && !m_targets.HasTraj())
5791 {
5792 if (!m_caster->IsWithinDist3d(m_targets.GetDstPos(), max_range))
5793 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5794 if (min_range && m_caster->IsWithinDist3d(m_targets.GetDstPos(), min_range))
5795 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE;
5796 }
5797
5798 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5799}
5800
5801SpellCastResult Spell::CheckPower()
5802{
5803 // item cast not used power
5804 if (m_CastItem)
5805 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5806
5807 // health as power used - need check health amount
5808 if (m_spellInfo->PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
5809 {
5810 if (int32(m_caster->GetHealth()) <= m_powerCost)
5811 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
5812 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5813 }
5814 // Check valid power type
5815 if (m_spellInfo->PowerType >= MAX_POWERS)
5816 {
5817 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::CheckPower: Unknown power type '%d'", m_spellInfo->PowerType);
5818 return SPELL_FAILED_UNKNOWN;
5819 }
5820
5821 //check rune cost only if a spell has PowerType == POWER_RUNE
5822 if (m_spellInfo->PowerType == POWER_RUNE)
5823 {
5824 SpellCastResult failReason = CheckRuneCost(m_spellInfo->RuneCostID);
5825 if (failReason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5826 return failReason;
5827 }
5828
5829 // Check power amount
5830 Powers powerType = Powers(m_spellInfo->PowerType);
5831 if (int32(m_caster->GetPower(powerType)) < m_powerCost)
5832 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_POWER;
5833 else
5834 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5835}
5836
5837SpellCastResult Spell::CheckItems()
5838{
5839 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
5840 if (!player)
5841 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5842
5843 if (!m_CastItem)
5844 {
5845 if (m_castItemGUID)
5846 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5847 }
5848 else
5849 {
5850 uint32 itemid = m_CastItem->GetEntry();
5851 if (!player->HasItemCount(itemid))
5852 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5853
5854 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
5855 if (!proto)
5856 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5857
5858 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
5859 if (proto->Spells[i].SpellCharges)
5860 if (m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(i) == 0)
5861 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_CHARGES_REMAIN;
5862
5863 // consumable cast item checks
5864 if (proto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_CONSUMABLE && m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5865 {
5866 // such items should only fail if there is no suitable effect at all - see Rejuvenation Potions for example
5867 SpellCastResult failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5868 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
5869 {
5870 // skip check, pet not required like checks, and for TARGET_UNIT_PET m_targets.GetUnitTarget() is not the real target but the caster
5871 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_PET)
5872 continue;
5873
5874 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL)
5875 {
5876 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->IsFullHealth())
5877 {
5878 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_HEALTH;
5879 continue;
5880 }
5881 else
5882 {
5883 failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5884 break;
5885 }
5886 }
5887
5888 // Mana Potion, Rage Potion, Thistle Tea(Rogue), ...
5889 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE)
5890 {
5891 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue < 0 || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue >= int8(MAX_POWERS))
5892 {
5893 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_POWER;
5894 continue;
5895 }
5896
5897 Powers power = Powers(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue);
5898 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetPower(power) == m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetMaxPower(power))
5899 {
5900 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_POWER;
5901 continue;
5902 }
5903 else
5904 {
5905 failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5906 break;
5907 }
5908 }
5909 }
5910 if (failReason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5911 return failReason;
5912 }
5913 }
5914
5915 // check target item
5916 if (m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID())
5917 {
5918 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
5919 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_GONE;
5920
5921 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget()->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
5922 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
5923 }
5924 // if not item target then required item must be equipped
5925 else
5926 {
5927 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_EQUIPPED_ITEM_REQUIREMENT))
5928 if (!player->HasItemFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
5929 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
5930 }
5931
5932 // do not take reagents for these item casts
5933 if (!(m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetTemplate()->Flags & ITEM_PROTO_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST))
5934 {
5935 bool checkReagents = !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST) && !player->CanNoReagentCast(m_spellInfo);
5936 // Not own traded item (in trader trade slot) requires reagents even if triggered spell
5937 if (!checkReagents)
5938 if (Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
5939 if (targetItem->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
5940 checkReagents = true;
5941
5942 // check reagents (ignore triggered spells with reagents processed by original spell) and special reagent ignore case.
5943 if (checkReagents)
5944 {
5945 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; i++)
5946 {
5947 if (m_spellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
5948 continue;
5949
5950 uint32 itemid = m_spellInfo->Reagent[i];
5951 uint32 itemcount = m_spellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
5952
5953 // if CastItem is also spell reagent
5954 if (m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetEntry() == itemid)
5955 {
5956 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
5957 if (!proto)
5958 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5959 for (uint8 s = 0; s < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++s)
5960 {
5961 // CastItem will be used up and does not count as reagent
5962 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(s);
5963 if (proto->Spells[s].SpellCharges < 0 && abs(charges) < 2)
5964 {
5965 ++itemcount;
5966 break;
5967 }
5968 }
5969 }
5970 if (!player->HasItemCount(itemid, itemcount))
5971 return SPELL_FAILED_REAGENTS;
5972 }
5973 }
5974
5975 // check totem-item requirements (items presence in inventory)
5976 uint32 totems = 2;
5977 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
5978 {
5979 if (m_spellInfo->Totem[i] != 0)
5980 {
5981 if (player->HasItemCount(m_spellInfo->Totem[i]))
5982 {
5983 totems -= 1;
5984 continue;
5985 }
5986 }
5987 else
5988 totems -= 1;
5989 }
5990 if (totems != 0)
5991 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEMS; //0x7C
5992
5993 // Check items for TotemCategory (items presence in inventory)
5994 uint32 TotemCategory = 2;
5995 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
5996 {
5997 if (m_spellInfo->TotemCategory[i] != 0)
5998 {
5999 if (player->HasItemTotemCategory(m_spellInfo->TotemCategory[i]))
6000 {
6001 TotemCategory -= 1;
6002 continue;
6003 }
6004 }
6005 else
6006 TotemCategory -= 1;
6007 }
6008 if (TotemCategory != 0)
6009 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY; //0x7B
6010 }
6011
6012 // special checks for spell effects
6013 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
6014 {
6015 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect)
6016 {
6017 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM:
6018 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM_2:
6019 {
6020 if (!IsTriggered() && m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType)
6021 {
6022 ItemPosCountVec dest;
6023 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType, 1);
6024 if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
6025 {
6026 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType);
6027 /// @todo Needs review
6028 if (pProto && !(pProto->ItemLimitCategory))
6029 {
6030 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType);
6031 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6032 }
6033 else
6034 {
6035 if (!(m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_MAGE && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x40000000)))
6036 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM;
6037 else if (!(player->HasItemCount(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType)))
6038 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM;
6039 else
6040 player->CastSpell(m_caster, m_spellInfo->Effects[EFFECT_1].CalcValue(), false); // move this to anywhere
6041 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6042 }
6043 }
6044 }
6045 break;
6046 }
6047 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM:
6048 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType && m_targets.GetItemTarget()
6049 && (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->IsWeaponVellum() || m_targets.GetItemTarget()->IsArmorVellum()))
6050 {
6051 // cannot enchant vellum for other player
6052 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6053 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6054 // do not allow to enchant vellum from scroll made by vellum-prevent exploit
6055 if (m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetTemplate()->Flags & ITEM_PROTO_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST)
6056 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY;
6057 ItemPosCountVec dest;
6058 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType, 1);
6059 if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
6060 {
6061 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType);
6062 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6063 }
6064 }
6065 // no break
6066 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_PRISMATIC:
6067 {
6068 Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
6069 if (!targetItem)
6070 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
6071
6072 if (targetItem->GetTemplate()->ItemLevel < m_spellInfo->BaseLevel)
6073 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
6074
6075 bool isItemUsable = false;
6076 for (uint8 e = 0; e < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++e)
6077 {
6078 ItemTemplate const* proto = targetItem->GetTemplate();
6079 if (proto->Spells[e].SpellId > 0 && (
6080 proto->Spells[e].SpellTrigger == ITEM_SPELLTRIGGER_ON_USE ||
6081 proto->Spells[e].SpellTrigger == ITEM_SPELLTRIGGER_ON_NO_DELAY_USE))
6082 {
6083 isItemUsable = true;
6084 break;
6085 }
6086 }
6087
6088 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* enchantEntry = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue);
6089 // do not allow adding usable enchantments to items that have use effect already
6090 if (enchantEntry)
6091 {
6092 for (uint8 s = 0; s < MAX_ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_EFFECTS; ++s)
6093 {
6094 switch (enchantEntry->type[s])
6095 {
6096 case ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_USE_SPELL:
6097 if (isItemUsable)
6098 return SPELL_FAILED_ON_USE_ENCHANT;
6099 break;
6100 case ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_PRISMATIC_SOCKET:
6101 {
6102 uint32 numSockets = 0;
6103 for (uint32 socket = 0; socket < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SOCKETS; ++socket)
6104 if (targetItem->GetTemplate()->Socket[socket].Color)
6105 ++numSockets;
6106
6107 if (numSockets == MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SOCKETS || targetItem->GetEnchantmentId(PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT))
6108 return SPELL_FAILED_MAX_SOCKETS;
6109 break;
6110 }
6111 }
6112 }
6113 }
6114
6115 // Not allow enchant in trade slot for some enchant type
6116 if (targetItem->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6117 {
6118 if (!enchantEntry)
6119 return SPELL_FAILED_ERROR;
6120 if (enchantEntry->slot & ENCHANTMENT_CAN_SOULBOUND)
6121 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6122 }
6123 break;
6124 }
6125 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_TEMPORARY:
6126 {
6127 Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
6128 if (!item)
6129 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
6130 // Not allow enchant in trade slot for some enchant type
6131 if (item->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6132 {
6133 uint32 enchant_id = m_spellInfo->Effects[i].MiscValue;
6134 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(enchant_id);
6135 if (!pEnchant)
6136 return SPELL_FAILED_ERROR;
6137 if (pEnchant->slot & ENCHANTMENT_CAN_SOULBOUND)
6138 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6139 }
6140 break;
6141 }
6142 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_HELD_ITEM:
6143 // check item existence in effect code (not output errors at offhand hold item effect to main hand for example
6144 break;
6145 case SPELL_EFFECT_DISENCHANT:
6146 {
6147 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6148 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6149
6150 // prevent disenchanting in trade slot
6151 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6152 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6153
6154 ItemTemplate const* itemProto = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate();
6155 if (!itemProto)
6156 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6157
6158 uint32 item_quality = itemProto->Quality;
6159 // 2.0.x addon: Check player enchanting level against the item disenchanting requirements
6160 uint32 item_disenchantskilllevel = itemProto->RequiredDisenchantSkill;
6161 if (item_disenchantskilllevel == uint32(-1))
6162 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6163 if (item_disenchantskilllevel > player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
6164 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6165 if (item_quality > 4 || item_quality < 2)
6166 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6167 if (itemProto->Class != ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON && itemProto->Class != ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
6168 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6169 if (!itemProto->DisenchantID)
6170 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6171 break;
6172 }
6173 case SPELL_EFFECT_PROSPECTING:
6174 {
6175 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6176 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6177 //ensure item is a prospectable ore
6178 if (!(m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->Flags & ITEM_PROTO_FLAG_PROSPECTABLE))
6179 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6180 //prevent prospecting in trade slot
6181 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6182 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6183 //Check for enough skill in jewelcrafting
6184 uint32 item_prospectingskilllevel = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->RequiredSkillRank;
6185 if (item_prospectingskilllevel >player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING))
6186 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6187 //make sure the player has the required ores in inventory
6188 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetCount() < 5)
6189 return SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS;
6190
6191 if (!LootTemplates_Prospecting.HaveLootFor(m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry()))
6192 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6193
6194 break;
6195 }
6196 case SPELL_EFFECT_MILLING:
6197 {
6198 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6199 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6200 //ensure item is a millable herb
6201 if (!(m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->Flags & ITEM_PROTO_FLAG_MILLABLE))
6202 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6203 //prevent milling in trade slot
6204 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6205 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6206 //Check for enough skill in inscription
6207 uint32 item_millingskilllevel = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->RequiredSkillRank;
6208 if (item_millingskilllevel > player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_INSCRIPTION))
6209 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6210 //make sure the player has the required herbs in inventory
6211 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetCount() < 5)
6212 return SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS;
6213
6214 if (!LootTemplates_Milling.HaveLootFor(m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry()))
6215 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6216
6217 break;
6218 }
6219 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
6220 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
6221 {
6222 if (m_attackType != RANGED_ATTACK)
6223 break;
6224
6225 Item* pItem = player->GetWeaponForAttack(m_attackType);
6226 if (!pItem || pItem->IsBroken())
6227 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM;
6228
6229 switch (pItem->GetTemplate()->SubClass)
6230 {
6231 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_THROWN:
6232 {
6233 uint32 ammo = pItem->GetEntry();
6234 if (!player->HasItemCount(ammo))
6235 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6236 break;
6237 }
6238 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_GUN:
6239 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_BOW:
6240 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_CROSSBOW:
6241 {
6242 uint32 ammo = player->GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_AMMO_ID);
6243 if (!ammo)
6244 {
6245 // Requires No Ammo
6246 if (m_caster->HasAura(46699))
6247 break; // skip other checks
6248
6249 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6250 }
6251
6252 ItemTemplate const* ammoProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(ammo);
6253 if (!ammoProto)
6254 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6255
6256 if (ammoProto->Class != ITEM_CLASS_PROJECTILE)
6257 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6258
6259 // check ammo ws. weapon compatibility
6260 switch (pItem->GetTemplate()->SubClass)
6261 {
6262 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_BOW:
6263 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_CROSSBOW:
6264 if (ammoProto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARROW)
6265 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6266 break;
6267 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_GUN:
6268 if (ammoProto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_BULLET)
6269 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6270 break;
6271 default:
6272 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6273 }
6274
6275 if (!player->HasItemCount(ammo))
6276 {
6277 player->SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_AMMO_ID, 0);
6278 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6279 }
6280 break;
6281 }
6282 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_WAND:
6283 break;
6284 default:
6285 break;
6286 }
6287 break;
6288 }
6289 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_MANA_GEM:
6290 {
6291 uint32 item_id = m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ItemType;
6292 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item_id);
6293
6294 if (!pProto)
6295 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_AT_MAX_CHARGES;
6296
6297 if (Item* pitem = player->GetItemByEntry(item_id))
6298 {
6299 for (int x = 0; x < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++x)
6300 if (pProto->Spells[x].SpellCharges != 0 && pitem->GetSpellCharges(x) == pProto->Spells[x].SpellCharges)
6301 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_AT_MAX_CHARGES;
6302 }
6303 break;
6304 }
6305 default:
6306 break;
6307 }
6308 }
6309
6310 // check weapon presence in slots for main/offhand weapons
6311 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_EQUIPPED_ITEM_REQUIREMENT) && m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass >=0)
6312 {
6313 // main hand weapon required
6314 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_MAIN_HAND))
6315 {
6316 Item* item = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK);
6317
6318 // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
6319 if (!item || item->IsBroken())
6320 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6321
6322 // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
6323 if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
6324 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6325 }
6326
6327 // offhand hand weapon required
6328 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND))
6329 {
6330 Item* item = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(OFF_ATTACK);
6331
6332 // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
6333 if (!item || item->IsBroken())
6334 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6335
6336 // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
6337 if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
6338 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6339 }
6340 }
6341
6342 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6343}
6344
6345void Spell::Delayed() // only called in DealDamage()
6346{
6347 if (!m_caster)// || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6348 return;
6349
6350 //if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_DELAYED)
6351 // return; // spell is active and can't be time-backed
6352
6353 if (isDelayableNoMore()) // Spells may only be delayed twice
6354 return;
6355
6356 // spells not loosing casting time (slam, dynamites, bombs..)
6357 //if (!(m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_DAMAGE))
6358 // return;
6359
6360 //check pushback reduce
6361 int32 delaytime = 500; // spellcasting delay is normally 500ms
6362 int32 delayReduce = 100; // must be initialized to 100 for percent modifiers
6363 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_NOT_LOSE_CASTING_TIME, delayReduce, this);
6364 delayReduce += m_caster->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_REDUCE_PUSHBACK) - 100;
6365 if (delayReduce >= 100)
6366 return;
6367
6368 AddPct(delaytime, -delayReduce);
6369
6370 if (m_timer + delaytime > m_casttime)
6371 {
6372 delaytime = m_casttime - m_timer;
6373 m_timer = m_casttime;
6374 }
6375 else
6376 m_timer += delaytime;
6377
6378 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u partially interrupted for (%d) ms at damage", m_spellInfo->Id, delaytime);
6379
6380 WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELL_DELAYED, 8+4);
6381 data << m_caster->GetPackGUID();
6382 data << uint32(delaytime);
6383
6384 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
6385}
6386
6387void Spell::DelayedChannel()
6388{
6389 if (!m_caster || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || getState() != SPELL_STATE_CASTING)
6390 return;
6391
6392 if (isDelayableNoMore()) // Spells may only be delayed twice
6393 return;
6394
6395 //check pushback reduce
6396 // should be affected by modifiers, not take the dbc duration.
6397 int32 duration = ((m_channeledDuration > 0) ? m_channeledDuration : m_spellInfo->GetDuration());
6398
6399 int32 delaytime = CalculatePct(duration, 25); // channeling delay is normally 25% of its time per hit
6400 int32 delayReduce = 100; // must be initialized to 100 for percent modifiers
6401 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_NOT_LOSE_CASTING_TIME, delayReduce, this);
6402 delayReduce += m_caster->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_REDUCE_PUSHBACK) - 100;
6403 if (delayReduce >= 100)
6404 return;
6405
6406 AddPct(delaytime, -delayReduce);
6407
6408 if (m_timer <= delaytime)
6409 {
6410 delaytime = m_timer;
6411 m_timer = 0;
6412 }
6413 else
6414 m_timer -= delaytime;
6415
6416 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u partially interrupted for %i ms, new duration: %u ms", m_spellInfo->Id, delaytime, m_timer);
6417
6418 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
6419 if ((*ihit).missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6420 if (Unit* unit = (m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID) ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID))
6421 unit->DelayOwnedAuras(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID, delaytime);
6422
6423 // partially interrupt persistent area auras
6424 if (DynamicObject* dynObj = m_caster->GetDynObject(m_spellInfo->Id))
6425 dynObj->Delay(delaytime);
6426
6427 SendChannelUpdate(m_timer);
6428}
6429
6430bool Spell::UpdatePointers()
6431{
6432 if (m_originalCasterGUID == m_caster->GetGUID())
6433 m_originalCaster = m_caster;
6434 else
6435 {
6436 m_originalCaster = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCasterGUID);
6437 if (m_originalCaster && !m_originalCaster->IsInWorld())
6438 m_originalCaster = NULL;
6439 }
6440
6441 if (m_castItemGUID && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6442 {
6443 m_CastItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetItemByGuid(m_castItemGUID);
6444 // cast item not found, somehow the item is no longer where we expected
6445 if (!m_CastItem)
6446 return false;
6447
6448 // check if the item is really the same, in case it has been wrapped for example
6449 if (m_castItemEntry != m_CastItem->GetEntry())
6450 return false;
6451 }
6452
6453 m_targets.Update(m_caster);
6454
6455 // further actions done only for dest targets
6456 if (!m_targets.HasDst())
6457 return true;
6458
6459 // cache last transport
6460 WorldObject* transport = NULL;
6461
6462 // update effect destinations (in case of moved transport dest target)
6463 for (uint8 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
6464 {
6465 SpellDestination& dest = m_destTargets[effIndex];
6466 if (!dest._transportGUID)
6467 continue;
6468
6469 if (!transport || transport->GetGUID() != dest._transportGUID)
6470 transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*m_caster, dest._transportGUID);
6471
6472 if (transport)
6473 {
6474 dest._position.Relocate(transport);
6475 dest._position.RelocateOffset(dest._transportOffset);
6476 }
6477 }
6478
6479 return true;
6480}
6481
6482CurrentSpellTypes Spell::GetCurrentContainer() const
6483{
6484 if (IsNextMeleeSwingSpell())
6485 return(CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL);
6486 else if (IsAutoRepeat())
6487 return(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
6488 else if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
6489 return(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
6490 else
6491 return(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL);
6492}
6493
6494bool Spell::CheckEffectTarget(Unit const* target, uint32 eff, Position const* losPosition) const
6495{
6496 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[eff].ApplyAuraName)
6497 {
6498 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
6499 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
6500 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
6501 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
6502 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->IsVehicle())
6503 return false;
6504 if (target->IsMounted())
6505 return false;
6506 if (target->GetCharmerGUID())
6507 return false;
6508 if (int32 value = CalculateDamage(eff, target))
6509 if ((int32)target->getLevel() > value)
6510 return false;
6511 break;
6512 default:
6513 break;
6514 }
6515
6516 // check for ignore LOS on the effect itself
6517 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) || DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS))
6518 return true;
6519
6520 // if spell is triggered, need to check for LOS disable on the aura triggering it and inherit that behaviour
6521 if (IsTriggered() && m_triggeredByAuraSpell && (m_triggeredByAuraSpell->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) || DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS)))
6522 return true;
6523
6524 /// @todo shit below shouldn't be here, but it's temporary
6525 //Check targets for LOS visibility (except spells without range limitations)
6526 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[eff].Effect)
6527 {
6528 case SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW:
6529 // player far away, maybe his corpse near?
6530 if (target != m_caster && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(m_caster))
6531 {
6532 if (!m_targets.GetCorpseTargetGUID())
6533 return false;
6534
6535 Corpse* corpse = ObjectAccessor::GetCorpse(*m_caster, m_targets.GetCorpseTargetGUID());
6536 if (!corpse)
6537 return false;
6538
6539 if (target->GetGUID() != corpse->GetOwnerGUID())
6540 return false;
6541
6542 if (!corpse->IsWithinLOSInMap(m_caster))
6543 return false;
6544 }
6545
6546 // all ok by some way or another, skip normal check
6547 break;
6548 default: // normal case
6549 {
6550 if (losPosition)
6551 return target->IsWithinLOS(losPosition->GetPositionX(), losPosition->GetPositionY(), losPosition->GetPositionZ());
6552 else
6553 {
6554 // Get GO cast coordinates if original caster -> GO
6555 WorldObject* caster = NULL;
6556 if (m_originalCasterGUID.IsGameObject())
6557 caster = m_caster->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_originalCasterGUID);
6558 if (!caster)
6559 caster = m_caster;
6560 if (target != m_caster && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(caster))
6561 return false;
6562 }
6563 break;
6564 }
6565 }
6566
6567 return true;
6568}
6569
6570bool Spell::IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() const
6571{
6572 return m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_ON_NEXT_SWING);
6573}

6575bool Spell::IsAutoActionResetSpell() const
6576{
6577 /// @todo changed SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_AUTOATTACK -> SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_INTERRUPT to fix compile - is this check correct at all?
6578 return !IsTriggered() && (m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_INTERRUPT);
6579}
6580
6581bool Spell::IsNeedSendToClient() const
6582{
6583 return m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[0] || m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[1] || m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() ||
6584 m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f || (!m_triggeredByAuraSpell && !IsTriggered());
6585}
6586
6587bool Spell::HaveTargetsForEffect(uint8 effect) const
6588{
6589 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++itr)
6590 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6591 return true;
6592
6593 for (std::list<GOTargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++itr)
6594 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6595 return true;
6596
6597 for (std::list<ItemTargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++itr)
6598 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6599 return true;
6600
6601 return false;
6602}
6603
6604SpellEvent::SpellEvent(Spell* spell) : BasicEvent()
6605{
6606 m_Spell = spell;
6607}
6608
6609SpellEvent::~SpellEvent()
6610{
6611 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6612 m_Spell->cancel();
6613
6614 if (m_Spell->IsDeletable())
6615 {
6616 delete m_Spell;
6617 }
6618 else
6619 {
6620 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "~SpellEvent: %s %u tried to delete non-deletable spell %u. Was not deleted, causes memory leak.",
6621 (m_Spell->GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ? "Player" : "Creature"), m_Spell->GetCaster()->GetGUID().GetCounter(), m_Spell->m_spellInfo->Id);
6622 ABORT();
6623 }
6624}
6625
6626bool SpellEvent::Execute(uint64 e_time, uint32 p_time)
6627{
6628 // update spell if it is not finished
6629 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6630 m_Spell->update(p_time);
6631
6632 // check spell state to process
6633 switch (m_Spell->getState())
6634 {
6635 case SPELL_STATE_FINISHED:
6636 {
6637 // spell was finished, check deletable state
6638 if (m_Spell->IsDeletable())
6639 {
6640 // check, if we do have unfinished triggered spells
6641 return true; // spell is deletable, finish event
6642 }
6643 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6644 } break;
6645
6646 case SPELL_STATE_DELAYED:
6647 {
6648 // first, check, if we have just started
6649 if (m_Spell->GetDelayStart() != 0)
6650 {
6651 // no, we aren't, do the typical update
6652 // check, if we have channeled spell on our hands
6653 /*
6654 if (m_Spell->m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
6655 {
6656 // evented channeled spell is processed separately, cast once after delay, and not destroyed till finish
6657 // check, if we have casting anything else except this channeled spell and autorepeat
6658 if (m_Spell->GetCaster()->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, true, true))
6659 {
6660 // another non-melee non-delayed spell is cast now, abort
6661 m_Spell->cancel();
6662 }
6663 else
6664 {
6665 // Set last not triggered spell for apply spellmods
6666 ((Player*)m_Spell->GetCaster())->SetSpellModTakingSpell(m_Spell, true);
6667 // do the action (pass spell to channeling state)
6668 m_Spell->handle_immediate();
6669
6670 // And remove after effect handling
6671 ((Player*)m_Spell->GetCaster())->SetSpellModTakingSpell(m_Spell, false);
6672 }
6673 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6674 }
6675 else
6676 */
6677 {
6678 // run the spell handler and think about what we can do next
6679 uint64 t_offset = e_time - m_Spell->GetDelayStart();
6680 uint64 n_offset = m_Spell->handle_delayed(t_offset);
6681 if (n_offset)
6682 {
6683 // re-add us to the queue
6684 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, m_Spell->GetDelayStart() + n_offset, false);
6685 return false; // event not complete
6686 }
6687 // event complete
6688 // finish update event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6689 }
6690 }
6691 else
6692 {
6693 // delaying had just started, record the moment
6694 m_Spell->SetDelayStart(e_time);
6695 // re-plan the event for the delay moment
6696 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, e_time + m_Spell->GetDelayMoment(), false);
6697 return false; // event not complete
6698 }
6699 } break;
6700
6701 default:
6702 {
6703 // all other states
6704 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6705 } break;
6706 }
6707
6708 // spell processing not complete, plan event on the next update interval
6709 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, e_time + 1, false);
6710 return false; // event not complete
6711}
6712
6713void SpellEvent::Abort(uint64 /*e_time*/)
6714{
6715 // oops, the spell we try to do is aborted
6716 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6717 m_Spell->cancel();
6718}
6719
6720bool SpellEvent::IsDeletable() const
6721{
6722 return m_Spell->IsDeletable();
6723}
6724
6725bool Spell::IsValidDeadOrAliveTarget(Unit const* target) const
6726{
6727 if (target->IsAlive())
6728 return !m_spellInfo->IsRequiringDeadTarget();
6729 if (m_spellInfo->IsAllowingDeadTarget())
6730 return true;
6731 return false;
6732}
6733
6734void Spell::HandleLaunchPhase()
6735{
6736 // handle effects with SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH mode
6737 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
6738 {
6739 // don't do anything for empty effect
6740 if (!m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsEffect())
6741 continue;
6742
6743 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, NULL, i, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH);
6744 }
6745
6746 float multiplier[MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS];
6747 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
6748 if (m_applyMultiplierMask & (1 << i))
6749 multiplier[i] = m_spellInfo->Effects[i].CalcDamageMultiplier(m_originalCaster, this);
6750
6751 bool usesAmmo = m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
6752 Unit::AuraEffectList const& Auras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_CONSUME_NO_AMMO);
6753 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator j = Auras.begin(); j != Auras.end(); ++j)
6754 {
6755 if ((*j)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
6756 usesAmmo=false;
6757 }
6758
6759 for (std::list<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit= m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
6760 {
6761 TargetInfo& target = *ihit;
6762
6763 uint32 mask = target.effectMask;
6764 if (!mask)
6765 continue;
6766
6767 // do not consume ammo anymore for Hunter's volley spell
6768 if (IsTriggered() && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER && m_spellInfo->IsTargetingArea())
6769 usesAmmo = false;
6770
6771 if (usesAmmo)
6772 {
6773 bool ammoTaken = false;
6774 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; i++)
6775 {
6776 if (!(mask & 1<<i))
6777 continue;
6778 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].Effect)
6779 {
6780 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
6781 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
6782 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
6783 case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
6784 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_PERCENT_DAMAGE:
6785 ammoTaken=true;
6786 TakeAmmo();
6787 }
6788 if (ammoTaken)
6789 break;
6790 }
6791 }
6792 DoAllEffectOnLaunchTarget(target, multiplier);
6793 }
6794}
6795
6796void Spell::DoAllEffectOnLaunchTarget(TargetInfo& targetInfo, float* multiplier)
6797{
6798 Unit* unit = NULL;
6799 // In case spell hit target, do all effect on that target
6800 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6801 unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == targetInfo.targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, targetInfo.targetGUID);
6802 // In case spell reflect from target, do all effect on caster (if hit)
6803 else if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT && targetInfo.reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6804 unit = m_caster;
6805 if (!unit)
6806 return;
6807
6808 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
6809 {
6810 if (targetInfo.effectMask & (1<<i))
6811 {
6812 m_damage = 0;
6813 m_healing = 0;
6814
6815 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, i, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH_TARGET);
6816
6817 if (m_damage > 0)
6818 {
6819 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsTargetingArea() || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsAreaAuraEffect() || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA))
6820 {
6821 m_damage = int32(float(m_damage) * unit->GetTotalAuraMultiplierByMiscMask(SPELL_AURA_MOD_AOE_DAMAGE_AVOIDANCE, m_spellInfo->SchoolMask));
6822 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6823 m_damage = int32(float(m_damage) * unit->GetTotalAuraMultiplierByMiscMask(SPELL_AURA_MOD_CREATURE_AOE_DAMAGE_AVOIDANCE, m_spellInfo->SchoolMask));
6824
6825 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6826 {
6827 uint32 targetAmount = m_UniqueTargetInfo.size();
6828 if (targetAmount > 10)
6829 m_damage = m_damage * 10/targetAmount;
6830 }
6831 }
6832 }
6833
6834 if (m_applyMultiplierMask & (1 << i))
6835 {
6836 m_damage = int32(m_damage * m_damageMultipliers[i]);
6837 m_damageMultipliers[i] *= multiplier[i];
6838 }
6839 targetInfo.damage += m_damage;
6840 }
6841 }
6842
6843 targetInfo.crit = m_caster->IsSpellCrit(unit, m_spellInfo, m_spellSchoolMask, m_attackType);
6844}
6845
6846SpellCastResult Spell::CanOpenLock(uint32 effIndex, uint32 lockId, SkillType& skillId, int32& reqSkillValue, int32& skillValue)
6847{
6848 if (!lockId) // possible case for GO and maybe for items.
6849 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6850
6851 // Get LockInfo
6852 LockEntry const* lockInfo = sLockStore.LookupEntry(lockId);
6853
6854 if (!lockInfo)
6855 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
6856
6857 bool reqKey = false; // some locks not have reqs
6858
6859 for (int j = 0; j < MAX_LOCK_CASE; ++j)
6860 {
6861 switch (lockInfo->Type[j])
6862 {
6863 // check key item (many fit cases can be)
6864 case LOCK_KEY_ITEM:
6865 if (lockInfo->Index[j] && m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetEntry() == lockInfo->Index[j])
6866 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6867 reqKey = true;
6868 break;
6869 // check key skill (only single first fit case can be)
6870 case LOCK_KEY_SKILL:
6871 {
6872 reqKey = true;
6873
6874 // wrong locktype, skip
6875 if (uint32(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue) != lockInfo->Index[j])
6876 continue;
6877
6878 skillId = SkillByLockType(LockType(lockInfo->Index[j]));
6879
6880 if (skillId != SKILL_NONE)
6881 {
6882 reqSkillValue = lockInfo->Skill[j];
6883
6884 // castitem check: rogue using skeleton keys. the skill values should not be added in this case.
6885 skillValue = m_CastItem || m_caster->GetTypeId()!= TYPEID_PLAYER ?
6886 0 : m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSkillValue(skillId);
6887
6888 // skill bonus provided by casting spell (mostly item spells)
6889 // add the effect base points modifier from the spell cast (cheat lock / skeleton key etc.)
6890 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET || m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET)
6891 skillValue += m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].CalcValue();
6892
6893 if (skillValue < reqSkillValue)
6894 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6895 }
6896
6897 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6898 }
6899 }
6900 }
6901
6902 if (reqKey)
6903 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
6904
6905 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6906}
6907
6908void Spell::SetSpellValue(SpellValueMod mod, int32 value)
6909{
6910 switch (mod)
6911 {
6912 case SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT0:
6913 m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[0] = m_spellInfo->Effects[EFFECT_0].CalcBaseValue(value);
6914 break;
6915 case SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT1:
6916 m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[1] = m_spellInfo->Effects[EFFECT_1].CalcBaseValue(value);
6917 break;
6918 case SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT2:
6919 m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[2] = m_spellInfo->Effects[EFFECT_2].CalcBaseValue(value);
6920 break;
6921 case SPELLVALUE_RADIUS_MOD:
6922 m_spellValue->RadiusMod = (float)value / 10000;
6923 break;
6924 case SPELLVALUE_MAX_TARGETS:
6925 m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets = (uint32)value;
6926 break;
6927 case SPELLVALUE_AURA_STACK:
6928 m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount = uint8(value);
6929 break;
6930 }
6931}

6942
6943void Spell::InitEffectExecuteData(uint8 effIndex)
6944{
6945 ASSERT(effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS);
6946 if (!m_effectExecuteData[effIndex])
6947 {
6948 m_effectExecuteData[effIndex] = new ByteBuffer(0x20);
6949 // first dword - target counter
6950 *m_effectExecuteData[effIndex] << uint32(1);
6951 }
6952 else
6953 {
6954 // increase target counter by one
6955 uint32 count = (*m_effectExecuteData[effIndex]).read<uint32>(0);
6956 (*m_effectExecuteData[effIndex]).put<uint32>(0, ++count);
6957 }
6958}
6959
6960void Spell::CheckEffectExecuteData()
6961{
6962 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
6963 ASSERT(!m_effectExecuteData[i]);
6964}
6965
6966void Spell::LoadScripts()
6967{
6968 sScriptMgr->CreateSpellScripts(m_spellInfo->Id, m_loadedScripts);
6969 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end();)
6970 {
6971 if (!(*itr)->_Load(this))
6972 {
6973 std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator bitr = itr;
6974 ++itr;
6975 delete (*bitr);
6976 m_loadedScripts.erase(bitr);
6977 continue;
6978 }
6979 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::LoadScripts: Script `%s` for spell `%u` is loaded now", (*itr)->_GetScriptName()->c_str(), m_spellInfo->Id);
6980 (*itr)->Register();
6981 ++itr;
6982 }
6983}
6984
6985void Spell::CallScriptBeforeCastHandlers()
6986{
6987 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
6988 {
6989 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_BEFORE_CAST);
6990 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->BeforeCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->BeforeCast.begin();
6991 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
6992 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
6993
6994 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
6995 }
6996}
6997
6998void Spell::CallScriptOnCastHandlers()
6999{
7000 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7001 {
7002 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_ON_CAST);
7003 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnCast.begin();
7004 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7005 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7006
7007 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7008 }
7009}

7011void Spell::CallScriptAfterCastHandlers()

7014 {
7015 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_AFTER_CAST);
7016 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->AfterCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->AfterCast.begin();
7017 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7018 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);

7020 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();

7022}
7023
7024SpellCastResult Spell::CallScriptCheckCastHandlers()
7025{
7026 SpellCastResult retVal = SPELL_CAST_OK;
7027 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7028 {
7029 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_CHECK_CAST);
7030 std::list<SpellScript::CheckCastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnCheckCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnCheckCast.begin();
7031 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7032 {
7033 SpellCastResult tempResult = (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7034 if (retVal == SPELL_CAST_OK)
7035 retVal = tempResult;
7036 }
7037
7038 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7039 }
7040 return retVal;
7041}
