7043void Spell::PrepareScriptHitHandlers()
7044{
7045 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7046 (*scritr)->_InitHit();
7047}
7048
7049bool Spell::CallScriptEffectHandlers(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellEffectHandleMode mode)
7050{
7051 // execute script effect handler hooks and check if effects was prevented
7052 bool preventDefault = false;
7053 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7054 {
7055 std::list<SpellScript::EffectHandler>::iterator effItr, effEndItr;
7056 SpellScriptHookType hookType;
7057 switch (mode)
7058 {
7059 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH:
7060 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunch.begin();
7061 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunch.end();
7062 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_LAUNCH;
7063 break;
7064 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH_TARGET:
7065 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunchTarget.begin();
7066 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunchTarget.end();
7067 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_LAUNCH_TARGET;
7068 break;
7069 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT:
7070 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHit.begin();
7071 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHit.end();
7072 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_HIT;
7073 break;
7074 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET:
7075 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHitTarget.begin();
7076 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHitTarget.end();
7077 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_HIT_TARGET;
7078 break;
7079 default:
7080 ABORT();
7081 return false;
7082 }
7083 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(hookType);
7084 for (; effItr != effEndItr; ++effItr)
7085 // effect execution can be prevented
7086 if (!(*scritr)->_IsEffectPrevented(effIndex) && (*effItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex))
7087 (*effItr).Call(*scritr, effIndex);
7088
7089 if (!preventDefault)
7090 preventDefault = (*scritr)->_IsDefaultEffectPrevented(effIndex);
7091
7092 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7093 }
7094 return preventDefault;
7095}
7096
7097void Spell::CallScriptSuccessfulDispel(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
7098{
7099 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7100 {
7101 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_SUCCESSFUL_DISPEL);
7102 std::list<SpellScript::EffectHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnEffectSuccessfulDispel.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectSuccessfulDispel.begin();
7103 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7104 hookItr->Call(*scritr, effIndex);
7105
7106 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7107 }
7108}

7110void Spell::CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers()
7111{
7112 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7113 {
7114 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_BEFORE_HIT);
7115 std::list<SpellScript::HitHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->BeforeHit.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->BeforeHit.begin();
7116 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7117 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7118
7119 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7120 }
7121}

7149void Spell::CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
7150{
7151 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7152 {
7153 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_OBJECT_AREA_TARGET_SELECT);
7154 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectAreaTargetSelectHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.begin();
7155 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7156 if (hookItr->IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && targetType.GetTarget() == hookItr->GetTarget())
7157 hookItr->Call(*scritr, targets);
7158
7159 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7160 }
7161}

7190
7191bool Spell::CheckScriptEffectImplicitTargets(uint32 effIndex, uint32 effIndexToCheck)
7192{
7193 // Skip if there are not any script
7194 if (m_loadedScripts.empty())
7195 return true;
7196
7197 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++itr)
7198 {
7199 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectTargetSelectHandler>::iterator targetSelectHookEnd = (*itr)->OnObjectTargetSelect.end(), targetSelectHookItr = (*itr)->OnObjectTargetSelect.begin();
7200 for (; targetSelectHookItr != targetSelectHookEnd; ++targetSelectHookItr)
7201 if (((*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && !(*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)) ||
7202 (!(*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && (*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)))
7203 return false;
7204
7205 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectAreaTargetSelectHandler>::iterator areaTargetSelectHookEnd = (*itr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.end(), areaTargetSelectHookItr = (*itr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.begin();
7206 for (; areaTargetSelectHookItr != areaTargetSelectHookEnd; ++areaTargetSelectHookItr)
7207 if (((*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && !(*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)) ||
7208 (!(*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && (*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)))
7209 return false;
7210 }
7211 return true;
7212}
7213
7214bool Spell::CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(uint8 effMask, SpellInfo const* triggeredByAura) const
7215{
7216 bool only_on_caster = (triggeredByAura && triggeredByAura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_PROC_ONLY_ON_CASTER));
7217 // If triggeredByAura has SPELL_ATTR4_PROC_ONLY_ON_CASTER then it can only proc on a cast spell with TARGET_UNIT_CASTER
7218 for (uint8 i = 0;i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
7219 {
7220 if ((effMask & (1 << i)) && (!only_on_caster || (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)))
7221 return true;
7222 }
7223 return false;
7224}
7225
7226void Spell::PrepareTriggersExecutedOnHit()
7227{
7228 /// @todo move this to scripts
7229 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
7230 {
7231 SpellInfo const* excludeCasterSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell);
7232 if (excludeCasterSpellInfo && !excludeCasterSpellInfo->IsPositive())
7233 m_preCastSpell = m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell;
7234 SpellInfo const* excludeTargetSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->ExcludeTargetAuraSpell);
7235 if (excludeTargetSpellInfo && !excludeTargetSpellInfo->IsPositive())
7236 m_preCastSpell = m_spellInfo->ExcludeTargetAuraSpell;
7237 }
7238
7239 /// @todo move this to scripts
7240 switch (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
7241 {
7242 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
7243 {
7244 // Permafrost
7245 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00001000 || m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00100220)
7246 m_preCastSpell = 68391;
7247 break;
7248 }
7249 }
7250
7251 // handle SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras:
7252 // save auras which were present on spell caster on cast, to prevent triggered auras from affecting caster
7253 // and to correctly calculate proc chance when combopoints are present
7254 Unit::AuraEffectList const& targetTriggers = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER);
7255 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = targetTriggers.begin(); i != targetTriggers.end(); ++i)
7256 {
7257 if (!(*i)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
7258 continue;
7259 SpellInfo const* auraSpellInfo = (*i)->GetSpellInfo();
7260 uint32 auraSpellIdx = (*i)->GetEffIndex();
7261 if (SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(auraSpellInfo->Effects[auraSpellIdx].TriggerSpell))
7262 {
7263 // calculate the chance using spell base amount, because aura amount is not updated on combo-points change
7264 // this possibly needs fixing
7265 int32 auraBaseAmount = (*i)->GetBaseAmount();
7266 // proc chance is stored in effect amount
7267 int32 chance = m_caster->CalculateSpellDamage(NULL, auraSpellInfo, auraSpellIdx, &auraBaseAmount);
7268 // build trigger and add to the list
7269 HitTriggerSpell spellTriggerInfo;
7270 spellTriggerInfo.triggeredSpell = spellInfo;
7271 spellTriggerInfo.triggeredByAura = auraSpellInfo;
7272 spellTriggerInfo.chance = chance * (*i)->GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
7273 m_hitTriggerSpells.push_back(spellTriggerInfo);
7274 }
7275 }
7276}
7277
7278// Global cooldowns management
7279enum GCDLimits
7280{
7281 MIN_GCD = 1000,
7282 MAX_GCD = 1500
7283};
7284
7285bool Spell::HasGlobalCooldown() const
7286{
7287 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7288 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7289 return false;
7290
7291 return m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HasGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo);
7292}
7293
7294void Spell::TriggerGlobalCooldown()
7295{
7296 int32 gcd = m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime;
7297 if (!gcd)
7298 return;
7299
7300 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7301 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7302 return;
7303
7304 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7305 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_COOLDOWN))
7306 return;
7307
7308 // Global cooldown can't leave range 1..1.5 secs
7309 // There are some spells (mostly not cast directly by player) that have < 1 sec and > 1.5 sec global cooldowns
7310 // but as tests show are not affected by any spell mods.
7311 if (m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime >= MIN_GCD && m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime <= MAX_GCD)
7312 {
7313 // gcd modifier auras are applied only to own spells and only players have such mods
7314 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7315 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_GLOBAL_COOLDOWN, gcd, this);
7316
7317 // Apply haste rating
7318 gcd = int32(float(gcd) * m_caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
7319 if (gcd < MIN_GCD)
7320 gcd = MIN_GCD;
7321 else if (gcd > MAX_GCD)
7322 gcd = MAX_GCD;
7323 }
7324
7325 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->AddGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo, gcd);
7326}
7327
7328void Spell::CancelGlobalCooldown()
7329{
7330 if (!m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime)
7331 return;
7332
7333 // Cancel global cooldown when interrupting current cast
7334 if (m_caster->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL) != this)
7335 return;
7336
7337 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7338 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7339 return;
7340
7341 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->CancelGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo);
7342}

7346
7347WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(Unit* caster, Unit* referer, SpellInfo const* spellInfo,
7348 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList) : _caster(caster), _referer(referer), _spellInfo(spellInfo),
7349 _targetSelectionType(selectionType), _condList(condList)
7350{
7351 if (condList)
7352 _condSrcInfo = new ConditionSourceInfo(NULL, caster);
7353 else
7354 _condSrcInfo = NULL;
7355}
7356
7357WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::~WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck()
7358{
7359 delete _condSrcInfo;
7360}
7361
7362bool WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7363{
7364 if (_spellInfo->CheckTarget(_caster, target, true) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
7365 return false;
7366 Unit* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
7367 if (Corpse* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
7368 {
7369 // use ofter for party/assistance checks
7370 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
7371 unitTarget = owner;
7372 else
7373 return false;
7374 }
7375 if (unitTarget)
7376 {
7377 switch (_targetSelectionType)
7378 {
7379 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
7380 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7381 return false;
7382 if (!_caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7383 return false;
7384 break;
7385 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
7386 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7387 return false;
7388 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7389 return false;
7390 break;
7391 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
7392 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7393 return false;
7394 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7395 return false;
7396 if (!_referer->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
7397 return false;
7398 break;
7399 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
7400 if (_referer->getClass() != unitTarget->getClass())
7401 return false;
7402 // nobreak;
7403 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
7404 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7405 return false;
7406 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7407 return false;
7408 if (!_referer->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget))
7409 return false;
7410 break;
7411 default:
7412 break;
7413 }
7414 }
7415 if (!_condSrcInfo)
7416 return true;
7417 _condSrcInfo->mConditionTargets[0] = target;
7418 return sConditionMgr->IsObjectMeetToConditions(*_condSrcInfo, *_condList);
7419}
7420
7421WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck(float range, Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo,
7422 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7423 : WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(caster, caster, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _range(range), _position(caster) { }
7424
7425bool WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7426{
7427 float dist = target->GetDistance(*_position);
7428 if (dist < _range && WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator ()(target))
7429 {
7430 _range = dist;
7431 return true;
7432 }
7433 return false;
7434}
7435
7436WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(float range, Position const* position, Unit* caster,
7437 Unit* referer, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7438 : WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(caster, referer, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _range(range), _position(position) { }
7439
7440bool WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7441{
7442 if (!target->IsWithinDist3d(_position, _range) && !(target->ToGameObject() && target->ToGameObject()->IsInRange(_position->GetPositionX(), _position->GetPositionY(), _position->GetPositionZ(), _range)))
7443 return false;
7444 return WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7445}
7446
7447WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck(float coneAngle, float range, Unit* caster,
7448 SpellInfo const* spellInfo, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7449 : WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(range, caster, caster, caster, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _coneAngle(coneAngle) { }
7450
7451bool WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7452{
7453 if (_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_CONE_BACK))
7454 {
7455 if (!_caster->isInBack(target, _coneAngle))
7456 return false;
7457 }
7458 else if (_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_CONE_LINE))
7459 {
7460 if (!_caster->HasInLine(target, _caster->GetObjectSize() + target->GetObjectSize()))
7461 return false;
7462 }
7463 else
7464 {
7465 if (!_caster->isInFront(target, _coneAngle))
7466 return false;
7467 }
7468 return WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7469}
7470
7471WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck(float range, Position const* position, Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo)
7472 : WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(range, position, caster, caster, spellInfo, TARGET_CHECK_DEFAULT, NULL) { }
7473
7474bool WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7475{
7476 // return all targets on missile trajectory (0 - size of a missile)
7477 if (!_caster->HasInLine(target, target->GetObjectSize()))
7478 return false;
7479 return WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7480}
